title: applesauce oatmeal bars
directions: Combine flour, salt, soda and nutmeg.
Beat butter and sugar together in mixer until light and fluffy.
Add egg; beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in flour mixture alternately with applesauce.
Blend well until batter is smooth.
Stir in dates and oatmeal.
Spread in 10 x 15 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares.

title: lime pineapple salad
directions: Sprinkle dry jello over drained pineapple and mix well.
Add cottage cheese and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute broccoli in oil until tender.
Add soup, milk and Cheez Whiz.
Simmer until cheese has melted.
Pour rice in a casserole dish and pour the cheese mixture over it.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Put aside 1/3 of the grated cheese and 1 can tomato sauce for the top of the casserole.
Cook macaroni as directed on package until barely tender.
Drain and add butter.
Stir and set aside. Saute onions in small amount of oil.
Add beef, salt and pepper. Stir well or use potato masher.
Cook only until red in beef is gone.
Add 2/3 of the cheese to meat and stir until melted.
Add 1 can tomato sauce and 1 can mushroom soup.
Stir and mix with macaroni.
Put in casserole Pyrex baking dish.
Cover top with cheese and tomato sauce mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix capers in blender.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Makes small amount, about 1 cup.

title: chicken breasts in vinegar and caper sauce
directions: Season chicken breasts with salt and pepper; dredge in flour and shake off excess.
Melt 3 tablespoons margarine and the oil in a large skillet.
Add breasts and garlic and brown breasts 2 to 3 minutes on each side on high heat.
Remove food from pan and discard burnt garlic.
Add vinegar to hot pan and allow to boil until evaporated.
Add 1 cup stock; bring to boil and reduce by 1/3.
Add chicken breasts to pan; lower heat.
Cover and let cook 6 to 7 minutes.
Remove chicken; add remaining stock, leaving aside the 1/3 cup mixed with potato starch.
Add meat glaze.
Stir and blend thoroughly.
Bring to a boil.
Whisk in potato starch mix.
Add remaining margarine and capers.
Return chicken to pan and simmer until heated through.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: pumpkin rice dressing
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Mix all ingredients and place in buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: onion glorified chops
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot oil, cook onion and half of chops 10 minutes or until browned on both sides. Remove onion and chops; set aside.
Repeat with remaining chops. Pour off fat.
In same skillet, combine soup and water.
Heat to boiling.
Return onion and chops to skillet.
Reduce heat to low. Cover; cook 10 minutes or until chops are no longer pink, stirring occasionally.

title: corny chili
directions: Place
beans
in
colander
and
rinse with water until water runs
clear.
Chop onion into small pieces and place in pan. Squeeze
garlic
into
pan.
Place
pan
on
burner
and crumble in turkey.
Cook on medium-high heat; stir occasionally
for about 5 minutes, until turkey is no longer pink.
Add chili powder,
tomatoes (break them up with wooden spoon) and their liquids, chilies, corn and beans to pan.
Reduce heat to medium-low
and
simmer,
uncovered,
for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; debone and tear into pieces.
Put chicken in a 7 x 11-inch buttered casserole; mix the soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Crush the Ritz crackers and combine with the poppy seed.
Sprinkle over soup mixture.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Cook 40 to 45 minutes at 350°, until bubbly and brown. Serves 8.

title: egg salad sandwich filling
directions: Mix egg yolk, egg whites, celery, onion, mayonnaise, mustard, turmeric, salt, pepper and paprika until blended.
Spread on whole wheat bread.
Makes enough filling for 4 sandwiches.

title: honey oatmeal chews
directions: Cream butter, honey and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oatmeal, coconut and nuts.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
When cooled, cut into bars.
Makes 30 bars.

title: cold vegetable salad(this salad recipe is my sister, luella's, favorite.)
directions: In a large bowl, mix corn, peas and green beans.
Add onions, celery, green peppers and pimentos.
In a saucepan, mix remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Let cool, then pour over vegetables.
Stir occasionally, and refrigerate 24 hours before serving.
(It is possible to serve immediately, but the flavor is better if you wait.) Serves 8 to 12.

title: macaroni salad with italian cheese dressing
directions: Combine macaroni, ham, celery, carrots, 1/4 cup olives, the onion and pepper in a large bowl.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, Gorgonzola cheese and lemon juice.
Pour over macaroni mixture. Toss.
Refrigerate covered 2 or 3 hours.
Place about 1 1/4 cups salad mixture in each lettuce cup.
Garnish with sliced green olives.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: Saute the carrots and onions in 4 tablespoons of the butter for a few minutes in a large soup pot or Dutch oven.
Add the sugar, salt, potato and water.
Cover the pot and simmer until the vegetables are tender.
Puree the vegetables in a blender with the cream (half and half).
In a separate skillet, melt the rest of the butter and stir in the flour.
Cook, stirring constantly, until golden.
Heat the milk and stir into it the flour mixture slowly, using a whisk.
Cook this white sauce very slowly (small flame), stirring often, until it is thickened.
Combine carrot puree and white sauce in the soup pot.
Add pepper, paprika and garlic.
Simmer the soup 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Garnish with parsley and/or croutons.

title: lucy's broccoli cheese soup
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine water, bouillon cubes, chopped onion and celery.
Boil 10 minutes.
Add broccoli and boil 10 more minutes.
Add cheese and soup.
Stir occasionally, until cheese melts.
Serve hot or cold.
Freeze well.

title: crustless crab quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 8-inch glass pie plate with nonstick cooking spray.
In medium bowl, mix crabmeat, cheese and onions.
Use back of spoon to press crabmeat mixture over bottom and up sides of pie plate.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine sugar and flour; stir in reserved juice.
Add pineapple and cheese; mix well.
Spoon mixture in 1-quart casserole.
Combine melted butter and cracker crumbs; stir well.
Sprinkle over pineapple mixture. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat and stir constantly.
Boil for no longer than 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows, chocolate chips and margarine.
Stir until all is melted.
Add 2 cups pecans and vanilla flavoring.
Spread on ungreased pan.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil, salt and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix	well.
Add
milk
and
flour
alternately.
Add flavorings and
mix
well.	Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan.
Put in cold oven and set temperature at 300°.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.	Do not open door until time is up.

title: scalloped cheese
directions: Alternate layers of bread and cheese.
Beat eggs and milk with seasonings.
Pour over cheese and bread.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: eggless-applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes 3 layers.

title: oven baked bourguignonne
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a 2-quart casserole, toss beef with flour and bake 20 minutes.
Add carrots, tomatoes and soup mix, blended with the reserved tomato liquid, water or apple juice and bay leaf.
Cover; bake 1 1/2 hours or until beef is tender.
Add mushrooms and bake covered an additional 10 minutes.
Serve over noodles or rice.
Serves about 8.

title: aunt karen's potato casserole
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes according to package directions. Combine with rest of ingredients.
Dot butter on top and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.
May double recipe for more servings.

title: sweet zucchini or yellow squash pickles
directions: Place squash, onions and garlic in an enamel or crockery pan with salt added.
Cover with ice.
Let set 3 hours.
Drain off salt.
Pour vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and turmeric over squash. Bring to a boil.
Put in hot jars.
Heat lids and seal.

title: bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine water, yeast, sugar and salt.
Stir until yeast is dissolved. Add sourdough starter and 2 cups flour to yeast mixture.
Mix on high speed for 3 minutes.
(It may be necessary to scrape sides of bowl with rubber scraper and rotate bowl slightly by hand.)
Add 3 1/2 cups flour and continue kneading 3 more minutes.
If dough is sticky, knead in enough of remaining 1/2 cup flour to form a stiff dough.
Place dough in greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.

Punch down and divide into 2 equal parts. Shape each into a smooth ball. Cover and let rest 10 minutes. Shape into 2 loaves and place in 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans or shape into round loaves and bake on a cookie sheet sprinkled with cornmeal.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled.
Put pan of water on lower shelf of oven.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes. Cool on rack.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: ham and cheese biscuits
directions: Slice rolls open and put back into aluminum roll pan.
Place cheese and ham in between layers of rolls.
Pour over the top with melted butter, poppy seed and onion flakes.
Bake until cheese is melted and browned.
Delicious!!

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Microwave chips and 14 ounces white chocolate in bowl on High for 2 minutes.
Stir; continue until smooth.
Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour onto pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Top with cherries.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Microwave remaining white chocolate until smooth.
Drizzle over coconut. Refrigerate until firm.
Store at room temperature.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken with salt and pepper.
When done, debone chicken and break into bite size pieces. Place chicken into bottom of 9 x 14-inch buttered casserole.
Mix soup, sour cream and 1/4 cup chicken broth.
Pour over chicken. Mix stuffing and 1/2 cup broth. Spread over chicken and soup mixture. Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Excellent for raw cauliflower, celery, cherry tomatoes, radishes and carrots.
Best if made the day of use.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown beef. Drain and return to pan. Add 1 jar of your favorite spaghetti sauce.

Add oregano and garlic salt to taste. Stir in pepperoni slices and spaghetti noodles. Pour mixture into 7 x 11 or 8 x 8 baking dish. Cover with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 375° until heated through and cheese is melted. You can use the broiler after baking to get the cheese golden brown.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and shortening or margarine.
Add eggs, peanut butter and vanilla.
In extra large bowl, stir in with a spoon chocolate chips, M&M's, nut meats, oatmeal and soda.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield:
over 125 cookies.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Thoroughly mix sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Do not use mixer, then add dry ingredients.
Mix well, add fruit and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool completely before removing from pan.
This is a must.
May also be baked in 3 or 4 layers at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients including sugar.
Make a well in the dry ingredients and add all remaining ingredients.
Mix together until smooth.
Put batter into 3 bread loaf pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. May add chopped pecans or currants.

title: date and nut bars
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Chop up dates and nuts and mix into flour mixture with sugar and wheat germ.
Stir in eggs (after beating well) and vanilla.
Spread over bottom of greased, shallow pan and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cut into small bars while still hot.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix well.
Place in a greased baking dish and bake slowly until mixture is firm.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: In a jar, combine all ingredients.
Seal tightly and shake well.
Best if made 1 night prior to use.
Marinade will last up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: la horchata
directions: In a blender, add white rice, vanilla, and evaporated milk. Blend together well.
Pour into a gallon container and add water and sugar.
Shake very well.
Add more sugar if desired.
Serve over ice.
Keep refrigerated.

title: almond pie crust
directions: Grind nuts in blender or grinder.
Mix dry ingredients. Add water and mix well.
Press into pie pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
May use almond meal.

title: egg rolls
directions: Grind cabbage and carrots.
Dice onion and mix together with salt.
Let it set for 1 hour, then squeeze out all the juice (using hands), then throw all juice away.
Mix all other ingredients together including cabbage, carrots and onion.
Place mix diagonally on egg roll wrapper.
Fold mix in wrapper.
Cook. Use a deep frying pan.
Put 3 tablespoons of vegetable oil in. Set stove on medium or medium-high and cook slowly until golden brown.
It will take about 10 to 15 minutes.
Check and turn as it browns.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, sour cream and dry onion soup mix.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until set.

title: strawberry refrigerator cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water; add 1/2 cup cold water.
Punch holes in cake with fork.
Pour gelatin in holes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all together. Bake at 350 degrees for about 20 minutes. Serve immediately.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Brown hamburger, onions, garlic, celery and green mango with margarine in a big skillet.
Stir in paste, sauce, mushrooms, water, vinegar and grated cheese.
Simmer 15 minutes to make a rich sauce.
While sauce is cooking, cook noodles in salt water until tender.
Drain and mix with sauce.
Cook 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: red cedar bean soup
directions: Wash and sort beans; soak overnight in salted water (2 tablespoons).
Drain and add 2 quarts water and ham bone or 2 hocks.
Simmer for 3 hours.
Saute in 2 tablespoons butter, the minced vegetables.
Add the sauteed vegetables, tomatoes, bay leaf and seasonings.
Simmer for 1 more hour.
Remove bones and return meat.
Add 2 tablespoons horseradish and serve.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Pop corn and mix with other dry ingredients.
Melt butter and marshmallows; pour over popcorn mixture.
Stir.
Place in cake pan (tube or oblong).
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese balls
directions: Work all together.
Roll in small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Press down with fork.
Do not grease pan.
Bake until brown.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk over medium heat until it comes to a boil. Boil for 2 minutes and remove from heat.
Add cream and peanut butter and beat with a wooden spoon until blended.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan greased with butter and chill until firm.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Saute onion with 1/2 cup butter until golden.
Add livers and remaining butter.
Add chicken broth, wine, etc.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Add cognac.
Whirl in blender and add walnuts to blender or chop and add for crunch.

title: creole seasoning
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a small glass jar with lid. This is good to season gumbo and other Creole dishes.
Use this seasoning in the following recipe.

title: children's pizza
directions: Give each child a canned refrigerator dough biscuit.
Have child flatten out the biscuit.
(This becomes the pizza crust.) Spread with tomato sauce.
Each child chooses their own toppings. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: black forest cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in a 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Mix pie filling and almond flavoring together. While cake is still warm, poke top with fork and spread pie filling over cake.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add yeast; stir in rolled oats.
Mix in flour.
Toss out onto floured board.
Let stand 10 minutes. Knead.
Put in bowl to rise.
Punch down when doubled.
Knead. Divide in half.
Form into 2 loaves.
When risen to double, bake about 1 hour at 400°.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook vermicelli according to directions.
Drain and cool. Don't salt vermicelli when cooking.
Mix Accent, salt, lemon juice and vegetable oil.
Add cooked pasta and rest of ingredients. Keep in refrigerator, covered, for 24 hours before eating.
It is good for 4 or 5 days.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix beef, rice, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Make into balls. Put in baking dish.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over meatballs. Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pecan roll ring
directions: Put 1 cup pecans in pan.
Place 24 frozen yeast rolls in pan. Sprinkle with 1 package pudding.
Melt 1 stick of butter or margarine with brown sugar.
Pour over pudding.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with wet towel and let stand overnight (on counter).
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn onto plate.

title: white cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Shape in ball and serve with crackers.
Yield: 1 ball.

title: reunion potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done.
In very large bowl, combine cubed potatoes with sugars, vanilla, mustard, milk, salt and pepper. Add Miracle Whip and celery, radishes, onion, green pepper and eggs.
Stir all together and sprinkle paprika on top.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream shortening.
Add sugars gradually.
Beat until light; add eggs and vanilla.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix together and make into 8 patties.
Roll in flour and brown in shortening in skillet.
Put in baking dish and pour 1 can tomato soup over the meat.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: fruit or vegetable bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Combine bran flakes, milk, egg whites and oil; soak for 5 minutes.
Add to wet mixture the rest of the ingredients; stir by hand until well blended.
Spray muffin tins with cooking spray or use paper liners and fill tins 2/3 full of batter.
Bake in preheated oven for approximately 20 minutes or until done.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, sugar and vanilla with mixer until all sugar is dissolved.
Add 6 mashed bananas.
Pour into a gallon ice cream freezer.
Fill to full line with homogenized milk.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and put in a buttered greased medium size dish.

title: bubble and squeak
directions: Mix with hands all ingredients.
Place bacon drippings in skillet.
Pour mixture in skillet and pack down with hands.
Cook on medium heat until browned on bottom (about 20 minutes).
Turn upside down on plate, browned side up.
Serve hot.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Make sauce while fettucini is cooking.
Melt butter in 8-inch skillet.
Over medium heat, add coffee cream, pepper, parsley and cheese.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add beaten yolk.
Drain fettucini and return to hot pot; add sauce.

title: ham and okra roll-ups
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on sliced ham.
Cut ends off okra.
Place okra at narrow end of ham slice and roll up.
Place in the freezer for a few minutes to firm and make slicing easier. Slice and serve.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine	in
deep
pan
in
oven
Make batter of	flour, sugar and milk.	Mix well.
Pour over melted margarine. (Do not stir.) Pour peaches on top. Crust will rise during baking. Bake
in
a 350° oven for 1 hour or until crust is brown.

title: honey french dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients together in blender.

title: vegetable dipping sauce
directions: Whisk all ingredients together. Use as dip for your favorite vegetables.

title: peach pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan and set aside.
In large mixing bowl, cream sugar and butter well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well.

title: oven stew
directions: Quarter potatoes, cut celery and carrots in chunks.
Place in buttered baking dish with meat and onion.
Sprinkle with salt, tapioca and sugar.
Pour chosen liquid over the stew.
Cover and bake in 300° oven for 4 hours.

title: date chewies
directions: Mix
together and drop by spoon on greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli.
In a deep frying pan, saute apple and onion in margarine until mushy.
Pour in chicken broth; blend in remaining ingredients.
Cook 20 minutes.

title: walnut delights
directions: Bottom Crust:
Mix margarine and 1 cup flour together and spread in a 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: family pie
directions: Put in large or small home and let bake until your heart is content.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Beat well and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, uncovered.
Heat salsa sauce to serve on top.

title: poppy seed salad dressing
directions: Slowly add oil to first 5 ingredients and mix gradually with spoon.
Add poppy seed.
Shake well and refrigerate.

title: pecan squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and confectioners sugar. Blend in 1 1/2 cups flour.
Press evenly in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread over hot baked layer and bake 20 minutes longer.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: mr. b's scrambled eggs
directions: In a bowl mix together ingredients.
Spray skillet with non-stick coating and pour in egg mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until done.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: pear nut bread
directions: Dice pears to get 1 cup fruit.
Beat oil and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time, then sour cream and vanilla.
Sift flour with dry ingredients.
Add to wet mixture.
Beat until blended, then add nuts and pears.
Mix well.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in large bowl (with lid) and set aside. Then mix together sugar, vinegar, oil, celery seed and salt. Bring to a boil. Pour over cabbage immediately. Cover tightly; do not uncover or stir. Let stand at room temperature for 2 hours. Then stir to mix well and refrigerate. Will keep up to 10 days in refrigerator.

title: shrimp special
directions: In medium size bowl, beat all ingredients except shrimp until smooth. Stir in shrimp.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.
Makes about 2 cups of spread.

title: bryan bacon veggie dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator for 5 hours.
Best when made one day before used. Yields one cup.

title: ham-cheese potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, heat cheese and cream, stirring constantly until cheese is melted and sauce is creamy.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 45 minutes.

title: tom's famous seafood recipe
directions: Thaw scallops and shrimp (if frozen).
Cut in half.
Peel and devein shrimp.
In a medium bowl, combine scallops and shrimp; set aside.
Thaw pea pods; cut in half.
Set aside.
In a skillet, cook onions and garlic in hot oil and butter over medium-high heat for 30 seconds.
Add 1/2 the scallop and shrimp mixture.
Add parsley, basil and red pepper.
Cook and stir for 3 to 4 minutes until the scallops are opaque and shrimp pink.
Remove cooked scallops and shrimp with slotted spoon and add other half of scallops and shrimp and repeat cooking.
Return all scallops and shrimp to skillet.
Add pea pods and tomatoes.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes more.
In a large bowl, toss scallop mixture with linguine.
Transfer to large platter; sprinkle with cheese. Serves 3 to 4 people.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugars and mix to blend.
Add butter and oil.
Beat well.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar and baking soda.
Add to sugar mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in vanilla.
Form into balls.
Dip cookie tops into small amount of granulated sugar and flatten with bottom of a glass.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes 8 dozen.

title: hearty chicken rice soup
directions: Spray large saucepan or Dutch oven with nonstick cooking spray.
Heat over medium-high heat until hot.
Add celery; cook and stir 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Add chicken breast halves, broth and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 to 12 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender and juices run clear, stirring occasionally.
Remove chicken from saucepan; cool slightly.
Cut into bite-sized pieces.
Bring broth mixture in saucepan to a boil over medium-high heat; stir in frozen vegetables.
Return to a boil.
Stir in rice, chicken, parsley and lemon and herb seasoning.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 minutes or until rice and vegetables are tender.
Makes 4 (1 3/4 cup) servings.

title: ham and chicken casserole
directions: In a skillet, saute onion in butter until tender.
In a large bowl, combine ham, chicken, peppers, olives, soup, sour cream, salt, pepper and onions.
Fold in noodles.
Pour into greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat.
In a large bowl, tear lettuce into small to medium size pieces.
Chop onion.
Chop tomatoes.
Mix meat, lettuce, onion, tomato, kidney beans and cheese in a large bowl. Pour in Paul Newman's dressing and mix well.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, mix in nacho chips.

title: salad with chicken
directions: For top layer, take the Miracle Whip and add the dill weed. Spread over the top of salad. Make the day before and when ready to serve, toss the amount you need for the meal. Refrigerate the rest.

title: banana pudding
directions: Put milk in large mixing bowl.
Add pudding mix and mix on low speed until it thickens.
Add the sour cream and mix well (about 2 minutes).
With spoon, gently fold in the Cool Whip, until it is well blended.
Place a layer of vanilla wafers in bottom of deep bowl.
Then layer of bananas (sliced), then layer of pudding. Repeat layers until all is used.
Sprinkle some wafer crumbs on top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: congo bars
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Beat softened oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well.
Add dry ingredients; mix.
Add nuts and chocolate bits.
Bake in a jelly roll pan (greased) at 350° for 20 minutes. Take out when bars look undercooked.
Cut into squares when almost cool.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix flour and sugar and beat in eggs.
Add corn and milk.
Dot with butter.
Cook at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: christmas cranberry relish
directions: Add water to cranberries and simmer 10 minutes.
Press cranberries through a sieve to eliminate skins.
Add sugar and stir.
Add jello.
Remove from stove and partially cool.
Add pineapple and a little of the pineapple juice, apple and nuts. Pour into a mold or dish and chill.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease pan.
Spread each ingredient in order listed.
Pour melted butter evenly over this.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cover with foil first half hour.

title: blue cheese walnut bites
directions: Combine flour and pepper in a medium bowl. Use a pastry blender to cut in cheese and butter until it resembles coarse crumbs. Add walnuts and egg yolks. Stir until combined. Form the mixture into a ball. Knead until combined. Divide dough in half. Shape each half into
a log about 9-inches long. Wrap logs in plastic wrap. Chill at least 2 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together until thoroughly blended and foamy.
Add remaining ingredients (except pecans) and blend thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Starting at outer edge, arrange pecans in concentric circles, ending with one or two pecans in the middle.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: In large kettle over medium heat, heat all ingredients (except orange juice). Simmer for 10 minutes. Add orange juice; drain off spices if desired. Serve hot. Makes 36 3/4 c. servings.

title: fruit slush
directions: Place yogurt and sugar in blender.
Blend for 5 seconds.
Add berries and almond extract.
Process at high until smooth.

title: hawaiian veggies
directions: Brown hamburger in a large skillet; add onion and 1 cube of garlic while meat is browning.
When brown, add 1 cup soy sauce; let simmer for 5 minutes.
Add carrots, celery, garlic and 1/2 cup soy sauce.
Cook until almost done but still have a little crunch. Serve 2 cups cooked rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: quick and easy company chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate bars in double boiler.
Mix with Cool Whip and pour into pie crust.
Chill at least 45 minutes.
Then ready to serve.

title: corn puff crisps
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix sugars, peanut butter, margarine, shortening, egg, baking soda and baking powder.
Stir in cereal and chocolate chips.
Shape dough by rounded tablespoonfuls into balls.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until golden, 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: mrs. alma's cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in Bundt pan, greased good, for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: butter roll
directions: Mix all together with fingertips. Knead until smooth. On a biscuit board, roll out 1/4-inch thick. Spread with 3/4 cup soft fresh churned butter. Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups sugar on top. Roll up jelly roll fashion. Cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces. Stand in a large pudding pan. Slowly pour enough boiling water over the rolls to cover. Sprinkle 1 teaspoon vanilla or use nutmeg. Bake at 350° until brown, about 1 hour. Serve with whipped cream.

title: fletcher's special brisket
directions: First, put flour in browning bag and shake well.
Set aside. Mix the dry ingredients.
Sprinkle the mixture over the brisket. Poke holes all over brisket with a fork and place in the browning bag.
Add the Italian dressing and mushrooms.
Close the browning bag and cut a few small slits in it.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes per pound.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients but crackers; mix thoroughly.
Crumble up crackers 5 at a time until it gets firm.
Grease a loaf pan; cook at least 30 minutes.
Cover the top with ketchup.
Cook for another 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Take it out.
Let cool for 10 minutes before serving.

title: lentil-barley-vegetable soup
directions: *Can be chopped in food processor.

title: cherry wink cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Blend butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in milk and vanilla. Add sifted dry ingredients together with nuts, dates and cut cherries; mix well.
Crush cornflakes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Cream white sugar and eggs.
Add fruit cocktail.
Sift together flour and soda.
Add to first mixture; mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Stir and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients. Melt 1 stick of butter in an 8 x 13 pan or deep Corning Ware dish. Add one 29 ounce can of sliced peaches, slightly drained. Gently stir in batter. Cook in a 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix all together until well blended and chill.

title: diabetic chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 1 graham cracker crust.
Spread extra Cool Whip on top of filling, if desired. Chill and serve.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Coat beef with flour mixture. Heat oil in Dutch oven until hot; add beef and remaining flour mixture.
Cook and stir until beef is well-browned.
Add water. Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add bay leaf, parsley, thyme and vegetables.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: swedish tea ring
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm; add one cup of the flour and beat well.
Add softened yeast, egg and vanilla.
Mix in enough flour to make dough soft.
Knead lightly on floured surface.
Place in greased bowl.
Turn once to grease surface.
Cover, let rise until double (1 1/2 to 2 hours).

title: mister lobster tails
directions: Boil water and salt in large saucepan.
Add tails.
Cover and boil again.
Lower heat and simmer 15 minutes. Drain and cut away undershell (covering meat of tails) using scissors.
Keep tails from curling by inserting long metal skewers from meat side through tail to shell side, then back through shell and meat at opposite end.
Arrange tails, meat side up, on broiler rack and brush with butter.
Set oven to broil or at 550°.
Broil a few inches from heat til hot, 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove skewers and serve with lemon sauce.
3 to 4 servings.

title: blueberry cheese torts
directions: Put paper liners in muffin pans, place wafer in each.
(Makes 18 to 36.)
Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth, about 3 minutes.
Put mix over wafers and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool and top with blueberry, cherry, strawberry or pineapple pie filling.

title: irish bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a bowl. Add remainder of ingredients in order given until batter is smooth. Pour into 2 greased and floured 1-quart casserole bowls. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake another 30 minutes.

title: turkey-vegetable pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook vegetables according to directions; drain.
In 2-quart saucepan, saute onion, celery and thyme in margarine.
Add soups and milk; stir until smooth.
In 8 x 12-inch baking dish, combine turkey, cooked vegetables and pepper.
Add soup mixture, stirring gently to mix.
Unroll crescent rolls without separating pieces.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Cut dough lengthwise into 8 strips, about 3/4-inch wide.
Arrange dough strips over chicken mixture to form a lattice.
Press ends of strips to baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown. Cover edges with foil if pastry browns too quickly.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of broccoli soup

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix dry pudding mix with Cool Whip.
Serve with fresh fruit pieces or with fruit salad.

title: lemon pudding cake with berries
directions: Place a buttered 5 to 6 cup souffle or other straight sided baking dish in a larger baking pan (at least 2 inches deep); set aside.
In a deep bowl, whip egg whites on high speed until foamy. Continue to beat, gradually adding 1/4 c. sugar, until whites hold short, distinct peaks; set aside.
In another bowl, beat (no need to wash beaters) remaining 1/2 c. sugar, 2 Tbsp. butter, peel and egg yolks on high speed until mixture is thick and lighter in color.
Stir in buttermilk, lemon juice and flour.
Add about 1/4 of whites to batter; stir to mix well.
Gently but thoroughly fold in remaining whites.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and add water to juice to make 1 cup.
Stir into pudding mix.
Microwave until thick and bubbly.
Add pineapple and drained oranges.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Stir in bananas and garnish with cherries.

title: crock-pot roast with gravy
directions: Place roast in crock-pot.
Pour in soup and 1/2 soup can of water.
Add 1 package Lipton onion soup mix.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours or until done.

title: homemade salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in airtight container.
Keep refrigerated.

title: smoked sausage and cabbage
directions: Fry chopped onions in a large skillet.
Add sausage and cabbage.
Add water and vinegar and cook about 1 hour.
Add rest of cabbage and cook about 1/2 hour.
Add sugar and remove lid to brown.
Serve with boiled potatoes.

title: aunt katie's gumbo
directions: Mix oil and flour in large pot over high heat until very brown, stirring frequently to avoid scorching.
Add water, okra, chicken, tomatoes, peppers, green onions, celery and salt to taste.
Simmer over medium heat for 2 hours.
Add sausage; continue to simmer for 1 hour.
Serve hot over rice, if you choose.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Combine first 3 items.
Boil 20 minutes slowly.
Add jello after removing from heat.
Stir until dissolved.
Put in jars. Store in refrigerator.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes, peel and whip by mixer until light and fluffy. Add rest of ingredients and mix and mix and mix; very well.
Bake at 350° until pie shell is done.

title: greek vegetable soup
directions: Make broth by boiling bones, water and salt for 1 hour.
Skim off frothy scum which floats to top.
Strain broth and return to clean pot.
If using butter to flavor broth, eliminate these first steps.
Add all vegetables and boil 1 hour.
Dilute flour in 1/2 cup cold water and add to broth to thicken.

title: sheila's punch
directions: Combine sugar and water; heat to boiling and boil 3 minutes. Add remaining ingredients, except ginger ale.
Put mixture into 2 rinsed 1/2-gallon milk cartons and freeze.
Remove and let thaw some.
Put in serving bowl and pour ginger ale over.
Should be slushy when served.
Makes 50 servings.

title: irv's turkey stuffing
directions: Use either 3/4 pound of skinned link sausages or sausage meat shaped like links.
I usually cook the meat part way first.
Use either Short Crust or Flaky Pastry.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, soda, fruit cocktail and flour.
Pour into ungreased pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Prepare pie crust according to the package directions and line an 8-inch pie pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 425° and cool.
Using some of the bacon fat, saute onion until tender and spread with bacon, ham and cheese in pie shell.

title: onion-rice bouillon
directions: Put rice and soups together in deep dish.
A Teflon loaf pan is ideal.
Slice butter and place on top.
Cover and cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Line a loaf pan with plastic wrap.
Mix all ingredients and pour into loaf pan.
Freeze until firm.
To serve, turn out onto platter and slice.
Serve over a lettuce leaf.

title: fig preserves
directions: Wash and remove stems from firm but ripe figs.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain, rinse in cold water and pull off peeling.

title: dirty rice (dressing)
directions: Saute meat until brown; add onion, celery, green pepper and garlic.
Cook, stirring and scraping bottom of pan.
Saute livers and green onions in butter until done.
Finely chop livers; stir livers mixture and chicken broth, salt, pepper and red pepper sauce into meat mixture.
Reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes, covered.
Simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Stir in as much as needed to make a moist dressing.

title: crusty apple cobbler
directions: Place apples and 1/4 cup brown sugar in a greased casserole. Mix well.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix all together and empty into a buttered casserole dish. Add more crushed cracker crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for approximately 1/2 hour or until brown on top.

title: lemon pie
directions: Cook
sugar,
flour, egg yolks, milk and salt for a few minutes,
then
add
lemon	juice and rind.
Let cook a little longer.
Add butter and pour in baked pie shell.
Add meringue and brown.

title: oriental cabbage salad
directions: Chop cabbage, pepper and scallions and combine in bowl.
Mix soy sauce, oil, sugar and vinegar and add to cabbage.
Bake almonds, sesame seed and noodles with oil in hot oven until brown, stirring often.
Remove, cool and add to cabbage.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar, baking soda, salt, vanilla, vinegar, Wesson oil and cocoa.
Mix well.
When smooth, add flour and water.
Mix until smooth.
Put in an 8 or 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mariam's chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, drained pineapple (reserve juice), grapes, celery and nuts.
Taste for salt.
(Salted nuts may furnish enough.)
Stir in tarragon leaves.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice and 2 tablespoons of pineapple juice into chicken mixture.
Serve on lettuce with parsley or small celery leaves for garnish.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients with water; bring to a boil and cook about 3 minutes, stirring.
Add butter; stir.
Add 1 1/2 to 2 cups sliced peaches.
Pour into a baked deep dish pie shell.
Refrigerate. Serve with whipped topping.

title: ground turkey balls(healthy)
directions: Mix together ground turkey, onion, chopped green or red pepper, pepper and bread crumbs.
Form into balls and roll in flour.

title: joanie's italian stuffed peppers
directions: Chickpeas are the stretcher here instead of the usual.

title: herbed rice
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a medium size saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 to 45 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Remove from heat and discard bay leaves.
Stir in thyme.
Top with sliced, green onions.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients together, adding broccoli last.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes until golden brown.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Place chicken (undrained) in bowl and add sour cream.
Cream until creamy.
Place portion on tortilla shell and sprinkle with jalapeno cheese.

title: apple squares
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle top with sugar and cinnamon mixture before baking.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: classic crab casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as package directs; drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: baked deviled eggs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash.
Combine yolks, sour cream, mustard and salt.
Mix well.
Refill egg whites.
Saute green pepper and onions in butter for 5 minutes.
Stir in pimento, soup and sour cream.
Pour sour cream mixture in baking dish.
Place deviled eggs on top. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple pudding cake
directions: Grease a 2-quart square baking dish; set aside.
Using the egg and the pineapple juice or water, prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Turn batter into the prepared dish.
In a medium mixing bowl, stir together the pudding and undrained crushed pineapple.
Pour over batter.
Bake in a 350° oven about 50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean.
(Be careful not to insert the toothpick into the pudding at the bottom.)
Cool the cake in the pan on a wire rack.
Serve warm with whipped cream.
Makes 9 servings.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Drain peas.
Combine first 6 ingredients in order given in a buttered glass baking dish.
Crush crackers and sprinkle over top. Dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: suppli di riso(rice croquettes)
directions: Melt the butter in a saucepan.
Add rice and brown for a few minutes over high heat.

title: fresh apple butter cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix butter and sugar; cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour, a little at a time; beat well.
Add soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add vanilla. Fold in apples and walnuts.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan 1 1/2 hours.
After baked, top with powdered sugar.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash, mash and drain well.
Add next 10 ingredients and mix.
Pour into buttered 2-quart dish.
Top with bread crumbs (or crackers), drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: laurine's dumplings
directions: Mix flour, Crisco, salt and baking powder.
Use a pastry cutter and work with it until Crisco is mixed well with rest of ingredients, like coarse meal.
Add enough milk to make a medium soft dough.
Let stand for a short while.
Roll out on a floured board as thin as you can.
Cut into squares; drop into very hot broth and allow to boil over each other before adding another layer.
Cover and cook 12 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until foamy. Add salt and gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in nuts and chips. Line cookie sheet with foil. Drop by teaspoon on foil.
Put in oven. Turn oven off and let cookies remain in oven at least 5 hours or overnight.

title: kraut salad
directions: Combine all.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.
Serve with hot dogs, vegetable or meat dish.
Yields 1 quart.

title: shucks if i know cake
directions: In an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan, mix crushed pineapple and juice with pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix on top along with coconut and nuts.
Thinly slice margarine and place evenly over the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: fat-free noodle spinach toss
directions: In 10-inch skillet, combine oil and butter; heat until butter is melted.
Add spinach, mushrooms, tomatoes and garlic.
Saute over high heat until mushrooms are lightly brown (2 to 3 minutes). Add broth and stir to combine.
Reduce heat and cook until flavors blend (3 to 4 minutes).
Add noodles to skillet and toss to combine with a fork.

title: bar cookies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Put in greased oblong pan. Sprinkle with the sugar, then the butterscotch chips and walnuts or pecans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab-broccoli bake
directions: Blend soup and milk.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Set aside.
In buttered 8-inch square baking dish, place half the broccoli. Top with half the crab or shrimp.
Cover with half the stuffing.
Pour over half the soup mixture. Top with half the cheese. Layer with remaining broccoli, crab or shrimp, stuffing and soup.
Cover with rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in salt water until tender.
Drain well and mash with butter, sugar, vanilla and milk.
Then put mixture in baking pan.
Top with following Topping.

title: satiny beige frosting
directions: Mix in saucepan the brown sugar, water and corn syrup.
Cover saucepan; bring to rolling boil.
Remove cover and cook to 242°, or until syrup spins a 6 to 8-inch thread.
Just before syrup is ready, beat the 2 egg whites until stiff enough to hold a point. Pour hot syrup very slowly in a thin stream into the beaten egg whites.
Continue to beat until frosting holds peaks.
Blend in the vanilla.
Frosts two 8 or 9-inch layers or one 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: anonymous cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs. Process oatmeal until powder-like in blender or food processor. (Measure oatmeal before processing.)
With oatmeal, mix in flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix all of these ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips and grated Hershey bar.
(Add three cups chopped nuts, if desired.)
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cookies may look undercooked.
May microwave 20 seconds to warm.
Makes 112 cookies.

title: camptown brownies
directions: Melt butter and choc. together. Beat eggs and sugar. Add to choc. Add vanilla. Fold in flour and marshmallows. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kielbasa bean soup
directions: In large saucepan, bring vegetables and water to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until tender.
Add kielbasa and bean soup.
Heat thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash fresh picked cucumbers and crisp in ice water.
Sterilize jars and lids while bringing water, vinegar and salt to a boil. In each jar, place 1 slice of onion, 1 clove of garlic, 1 carrot, 1 red chili, 1 bay or grape leaf and 1 stalk of fresh dill.
Pack cucumbers. Cover with boiling mixture. Seal one jar at a time.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease muffin tins. Sift flour and add all other dry ingredients. Break egg and beat until light.
Add milk to egg. Stir egg and milk into dry ingredients. Add shortening just enough to mix ingredients.
Add blueberries just before you put into muffin cups. Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken ole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add chili peppers, salt, soup and milk.
Add chicken and bring to a boil.
When mixture boils, turn off heat.
Layer quartered tortillas, chicken mixture and cheese in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; alternate layers and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until mixture bubbles.
Serves 4.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in first 4 ingredients, mixing constantly for 30 minutes or until rice is cooked.
Pour into 8 1/2 x 13-inch pan. Beat egg;
add
vanilla
and lemon.
Pour over rice mixture. Sprinkle in
raisins.
Stir with a fork.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Refrigerate until cool.

title: squaw corn
directions: Cook bacon to delicate brown in heavy saucepan. Remove from fat and cut in small pieces.
Add green pepper and onion.
Cook 3 minutes over medium heat.
Add corn, bacon and pimiento.
Reheat. Yields 6 servings.

title: red bean sandwich
directions: Blend the first 7 ingredients in a food processor, adding more catsup if needed for desired consistency.
Spread on toasted whole grain bread and top with lettuce, onion and your favorite vegetables.
Serves 4.

title: ratatouille nicoise
directions: Peel and cube eggplant and zucchini.
Boil in water 10 minutes; drain.
Peel and cut tomatoes.
Brown onion in olive oil. Add vegetables, garlic, parsley, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Cook 10 minutes and move to shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup Italian cheese and brown.

title: chinese clusters
directions: Melt bits over hot water.
Stir in peanuts and noodles.
Mix. Drop by spoon on waxed paper.
Cool.
Yields 60 servings.

title: water chestnut appetizers
directions: Wrap chestnuts with a slice of bacon and secure with a toothpick.
Bake, uncovered, 1/2 hour at 350°.
Drain fat.
Mix catsup and brown sugar.
Spoon over appetizers and bake another 1/2 hour.

title: rice krispy bars
directions: Mix Karo and sugar.
Cook just to boil, then remove and add peanut butter.
Stir until dissolved.
Then add cereal.
Stir and press into greased pan.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Cook slowly first 2 ingredients until vegetables are transparent.
Add chicken broth.
Blend in sour cream.
Store in refrigerator until needed.
Heat and serve hot.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oleo and 1 egg and press into the bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cheese, powdered sugar, 2 eggs and vanilla; pour over cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.
Cake will fall.

title: homemade rolls
directions: In bowl, put sugar, salt and lukewarm water and mix well.
Add yeast cake.
Blend in shortening and egg.
Add enough sifted, plain flour to make a soft dough.
Store in refrigerator.
Punch out and shape into rolls as needed.
Let rolls rise and bake at 450° until brown.
Dough should stay in refrigerator at least 6 hours before using.

title: sweet-sour won bok rolls
directions: Combine
pork,	green
onion,
water
chestnuts, egg, 1 tablespoon of the soy sauce and salt; mix well.
Place 1/4 cup of filling
on each won bok leaf;
roll.
Place won bok rolls in skillet; add water and simmer 45 minutes, covered.	Arrange rolls on serving platter.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to	liquid in skillet.
Simmer until gravy thickens, stirring constantly. Pour over won bok rolls.
Makes 6 servings.

title: miracle cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into buttered dish.
Pour 2 cups fresh fruit over batter.
Bake 30 minutes or until brown.

title: green pepper beef
directions: Mix together 1 tablespoon soy sauce, wine, 1 tablespoon peanut oil and cornstarch.
Marinate steak in this marinade for 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: all-day stew
directions: Mix together soup, water and flour until smooth.
Combine with remaining ingredients in covered roasting pan.
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
Serve with French bread.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: lime jello
directions: Add the lime Jell-O to boiling water.
Mix together; add crushed pineapple.
Let jell in refrigerator until medium jelled. Beat Dream Whip and blend into Jell-O.
Mix well.

title: crunchy fried tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 3/4-inch slices.
Dip into egg and then into crumbs.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Add tomato slices and cook until golden brown on each side.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Melt milk and chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Add marshmallows.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Let cool.

title: 7 layer mexican salad
directions: Layer and pour dressing over top.
Top with crushed tostado chips, if desired.
Refrigerate and toss lightly before serving. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: wackie cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Make holes with a spoon in the dry mix and in each hole put the wet ingredients.
Mix with fork well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
For larger cake, double recipe.

title: ham-potatoes au gratin (diabetic)
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour and pepper.
Add milk all at once and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Add cheese and salad dressing; stir until cheese melts.
Combine potatoes and ham with sauce. Bake in a 10 x 6 x 1.5-inch baking dish in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Put a little oil in a frying pan. Heat oil and spoon batter into pan.
Turn when browned and brown the other side.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Mix margarine, flour and chopped nuts and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in 1 1/2-quart dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk. Pour into melted oleo.
Pour fruit on top of this.
Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with ice cream, if desired, and serve hot.

title: fluffy orange salad
directions: *Reserve 1/4 cup syrup.

whites until frothy. Gradually add sugar

or at least 5 hours. Do not open oven door until after 5 hours.
Yield: 30 cookies.

title: cranberry nut mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with 2 cups of boiling water.
Add cranberries, then pineapple and oranges with nuts.
Mix well. Pour into a 6-cup mold or 2 small molds.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and granulated sugar.
Blend in 1 egg at a time until mixed well, then add vanilla.
Measure sifted flour and add to oil mixture with baking powder and salt.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop by spoonfuls into powdered sugar and shape into balls (completely cover with powdered sugar).
Place about 2 inches apart on greased cookie pan for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: mexican stew
directions: Put all canned ingredients in a large pot. Add cooked meat. When soup is hot, mix in seasoning packets. Top with shredded cheese, tortilla chips and sour cream.

title: traditional southern dressing
directions: Saut onions and celery in margarine.
Crumble egg bread and mix in the stock until the mixture is very moist.
Add sauteed onions and celery, then mix in salt, pepper, and sage.
Add the four eggs and blend well.
Bake 30 minutes at 400 degrees.	Serves 10-12.

title: cracker spread
directions: Beat together.
Serve with snack crackers or party rye.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in salted water until tender.
Drain well.
In skillet, saute onion in 5 tablespoons margarine or butter until tender.
Add soup; mix well.
Add cheese; heat and stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cabbage and seasonings.
Place in a 2-quart baking dish.
Melt rest of butter and put in bread crumbs and brown lightly.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix and add enough milk to make gallon.
Place in ice cream churn.

title: meatballs to nibble
directions: Shape into small balls.
Fry in hot oil until brown.
Remove from pan and pour off excess fat.
Add garlic, soy sauce, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add meatballs and simmer for 5 minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch, mixed with water.
Cook until liquid thickens and gets clear.
Makes about 100 meat balls.

title: manda's helper
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add rice, water and beef consomme to ground beef and onion.
Cook on low for 10 to 15 minutes or until desired consistency.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Boil the last 2 ingredients together for one minute and cool before pouring over vegetables.
Store tightly covered in refrigerator.

title: curried ground meat with peas
directions: Heat the oil in a wide, medium sized pan over a medium-high flame.
When hot, add onion.
Stir and fry them until they are lightly browned.
Add the garlic.
Stir and fry for a minute.
Add ground meat, ginger, green chilies, ground coriander and cumin. Stir and fry meat for 5 minutes.
Add 6 ounces of water and bring to a boil.
Cover, turn heat to low and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add the peas, salt and lemon juice.
Cover and cook on low heat until peas are tender (about 5 minutes).
Remove excess fat.
Serve ground meat with steamed rice.

title: 7-layer lettuce salad
directions: Place
ingredients
in
salad	bowl
in
order
given: lettuce, onion, green
pepper,
celery,
carrot and peas, then spread salad dressing over	the top.
Make sure to seal in all edges, this keeps
it
fresh.
Sprinkle
sugar over top.
Then sprinkle 8 ounces shredded Cheddar cheese.	Seal and refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken in a large pot and add all ingredients, except rice.
Cook for 45 minutes.
When chicken is almost done, add rice and cook for 15 minutes.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook onions and pepper in a little hot fat until tender; add meat.
Brown lightly.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes until thick.
Add cheese.
Pour into greased baking dish.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
(Use only 1/2 cup pecans.)
Put 1 cup pecans on wax paper.
Shape mixture into a large ball (refrigerate if too soft) and roll in pecans.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: plum glaze for pork
directions: Drain purple plums, setting aside 1/2 cup juice. Puree the plums and then add juice and Worcestershire sauce.

title: frosted liver pate
directions: Mash braunschweiger with fork.
Mix in mayonnaise, onion, 1 clove of garlic and basil.
Mound mixture on plate.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Combine the cream cheese, 1 clove garlic, Tabasco and mayonnaise.
Frost braunschweiger with cheese mixture.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Just before serving, garnish with pimento and parsley.
Serve with dark rye snack bread or crackers.
Refrigerate any leftovers.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Drain juice from beets and add enough water to make one cup. Put beet juice, vinegar, brown sugar and salt in pan and bring to a boil.
Pour over beets and cool.
Put in refrigerator overnight. Add your hard-boiled eggs and let it stand overnight again.

title: eagle brand dessert(or salad)
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, mixing well. Fold in Cool Whip. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: bubble bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in quarters.
Combine granulated sugar and cinnamon in a sack.
Shake the biscuits in the mixture.
Place in greased Bundt pan.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix egg and milk together.
Sprinkle lemon pepper on chicken. Dip in egg and milk mixture and shredded cheese.
Brown in butter approximately 10 minutes and turn over for another 10 minutes. Add some white wine during the last 3 minutes.

title: cookie cutter breakfast
directions: Press the cookie cutter into the middle of the slice of bread and take out the center.
Butter what is left of the bread and the cutout piece.
Spread some butter in frying pan or griddle.
Place the unbuttered side down in the pan.
Break an egg into a small bowl and pour into the hole.
Fry until ready to turn over.
Also fry the cutout piece of bread.
Serves 1.

title: country spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef in 10-inch skillet; drain.
Return to pan. Add tomato sauce and paste, onions and peppers to meat.
Stir occasionally and cook 10 minutes.
Season to taste.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain canned fruits in colander.
While draining, mix lemon juice with condensed milk.
Stir in sour cream, then nuts and drained fruit.
Then fold in Cool Whip.
Put into pretty dish and chill.
Stick a stemmed maraschino cherry in the center.

title: microwave apple crisp
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients in medium bowl with a fork to make a crumbly mixture.
Set aside.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugars and the margarine together.
Combine all other ingredients and mix until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Drop by spoonfuls the size of walnuts onto greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Use the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar to flatten balls; add extra sugar to cookies if needed.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: peanut butter carb bars
directions: Microwave corn syrup and peanut butter in large microwavable bowl on High 2 minutes or just until mixture boils, stirring every minute. Add cereal. Mix to coat well.

title: lace cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Lightly grease two cookie sheets.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: If desired, serve on top of a thin slice of pineapple, which has been placed on top of lettuce leaf.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Pour 1/2 the batter into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Place 8 thick slices of cheese evenly over the batter and top with jalapeno peppers.
Pour remaining batter over the filling.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet-n-sour smoked sausage
directions: Mix jelly and mustard in saucepan on top of range.
Stir constantly until mixture is dissolved and comes to boil.
Add sausages.
Cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: barbecue dogs
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Put in wieners.
Simmer in sauce until wieners are cooked.

title: doritos casserole
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef and drain.
Set aside.
Mix soups and Ro-Tel together; heat.
In a 9 x 13-inch dish, spread Doritos in bottom of dish.
Spread meat over Doritos; pour soup mixture over meat.
Lay sliced cheese over this.
Put it in the oven until cheese melts and is good and hot, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients into blender; fill container to top with ice.
Blend until ice is finely chopped.
Serve in chilled glasses.

title: do ahead lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef in large frypan; drain fat.
Stir tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, oregano and pepper into ground beef.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Cook lasagna noodles; drain well.
Alternate layers of noodles, Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese, meat sauce and Parmesan cheese in ungreased 11 x 7-inch pan or 9-inch square pan.
Cover and refrigerate.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until hot and bubbly, about 40 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bread of germany(hutzelbrod)
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly mix 2 cups flour, sugar, salt, anise seeds, cinnamon, cardamon, cloves and undissolved yeast. Add softened margarine.
Gradually add very hot tap water to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add 1 cup flour or enough flour to make a thick batter.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover; let rise in warm place, free from draft, until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.
Punch dough down; turn out onto lightly floured board.
Knead in almonds, English walnuts, pears, figs, prunes and orange peel.
Divide dough in half; form into round balls.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Cover; let rise in warm place, until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until done.
Remove from baking sheets and place on wire racks to cool.
Brush with honey while warm.
Makes 2 large loaves.

title: cherry tart
directions: Bake pie shell at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Drain cherries and slice, reserving 6 for garnish.
Mix sliced cherries with the preserves, lemon peel and juice.
Spread over bottom of pie shell.
Beat the egg whites with salt until stiff but not dry. Combine the egg yolks and sugar and beat until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in flour and filberts.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream and reserved cherries.

title: pizza crust
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt, then add milk and oil. Knead until smooth.
Roll out on about 4 (12-inch) cookie sheets. Mine doesn't go so far.

title: cheddarburger skillet
directions: Brown and drain the Hamburg and add the onion.
Stir in the Soups and Water.
Add the Potatoes.
Heat; stir occasionally. Serve with Tomato Wedges.

title: scandinavian salad
directions: Drain vegetables.
Mix other ingredients.
Will keep in refrigerator.
Chill for at least 6 hours before serving.

title: down-home potato slices
directions: Scrub potatoes and cut lengthwise into 1/2-inch slices.
Do not peel.
Place a single layer on a greased baking sheet.
Mix butter, onion, salt and pepper.
Brush on potato slices and cover with foil.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: los patios cheese soup
directions: Melt margarine over low heat and saute onions, celery and carrots.
Add chicken broth, cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add potato soup, cheese, parsley, Tabasco, salt and pepper.
Stir in sour cream.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add sherry, stir and serve!
Total cooking time:
45 minutes.

title: ring tum tiddy
directions: Melt butter in electric skillet at 275°.
Saute onions until soft.
Reduce heat to 160° to 180°.
Add cheese and cook slowly until melted.
Then add soup.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Stone the cherries.
Keep aside the syrup.
To the cherry syrup, add corn flour, jam and sugar.
Boil for a little time. Add the lemon
juice, cochineal and the stoned cherries. Fill a bowl with the hot cherry mixture. Warm the brandy in a large spoon.
Set it alight and pour the burning brandy over the cherries. Mix well.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in bacon fat.
Spread cheese, onion, mushrooms and bacon evenly in pie shell.
Mix other ingredients. Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350°.
Bake until knife will come out clean.

title: jalapeno pepper jelly
directions: You will also need 2 dozen pint jars.
I wear rubber gloves when doing this project!

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Heat oven to 200°.
Divide popped corn between 2 ungreased baking pans.
In saucepan, heat sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt, stirring occasionally, until bubbly around edges.
Continue cooking over medium heat 5 minutes.

title: casserole special
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown meat; drain.
Add onion.
Cook until tender.
Stir in cheese and soup; mix well.
Add corn, pimiento and seasonings; pour into 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Place biscuits around edge of baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in 2 cups ice and dissolve in jello for 3 minutes.
Remove ice.
Add yogurt, pineapple and oranges.
Mix well.
Let congeal.
Add 1/2 to 1 carton Cool Whip after congealed.
Re-congeal.

title: barbara's white bread
directions: Melt shortening in a large kettle.
Add the warm water; add the salt, sugar and yeast.
Beat in the flour (add extra to knead as needed).
Turn on floured board and knead eight minutes.
Recipe makes 15 rolls and two double loaves of bread.
Bake at 350° oven. May use some for doughboys (fried dough).

title: fineran's flaky crust
directions: Combine ingredients until moist.
Divide in half; each half makes one pie crust.
Roll out between two pieces of wax paper.

title: miracle cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa and baking soda.
Mix well.
Add cold water and mix. Add salad dressing.
Mix well. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. This can be made ahead and refrigerated.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Cut up lettuce and onion.
Add peas.
Cover with salad dressing and sprinkle with sugar.
Crumble up crisp fried bacon. Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, mix well.

title: boiled oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine milk, margarine, sugar and cocoa.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and oats.
Also, add peanut butter and nuts if desired.
Beat until well blended; drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let set until firm.

title: sourdough apricot spice bars
directions: Cream
together
the
margarine, brown sugar and honey. Add eggs,
one at a time, mixing thoroughly after each.
Stir in baking
powder,
salt,
soda and spices.
Mix in flour and starter;
mix well.
Stir in nuts and apricots.
Spread batter in greased
and floured 10 x 15 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Brush with glaze made of
3/4 cup powdered sugar and 1 tablespoon lemon juice;
beat together until smooth.
Cool completely;
cut into squares.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Stew the chicken.
Add all the vegetables and seasonings if using raw vegetables.
If using canned corn and lima beans do not add
at this time.
Add about 2 cups water or more, canned tomatoes and the bacon.
Cook slowly for about 2 hours, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking.
If using cooked or canned corn and canned lima beans add them about 30 minutes before stew is finished.

title: rolls
directions: Scald milk. While heating, combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Add the milk.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine milk mixture and yeast.
Add flour and shortening.
Mix well.
Let rise, then cut in pie shape and rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix cooled pasta and vegetables together.
Mix dressing ingredients together; add to pasta mixture and keep chilled.
Best if made the night before.

title: peanut brittle(microwave candy)
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in a 2-quart glass measuring cup.
Cook, uncovered, 8 minutes at High power in microwave.

Stir peanuts and butter into mixture. Cook uncovered 17 to 18 minutes at High power or until mixture forms threads when dropped in cold water or measures 300° on a candy thermometer (oven should not be in operation when candy thermometer is inserted).
Stir 4 to 5 times during cooking.
Stir in remaining ingredients and blend until smooth.
Pour mixture onto 2 buttered baking sheets.
Spread in thin layer with a knife.
Let stand until hard (about 1/2 hour).
Break into pieces.
Makes about 2 pounds candy.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, melted margarine and cinnamon. Mix until crumbly.
Add oatmeal.
Press half of crumb mixture into greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cover with diced rhubarb. Combine sugar, cornstarch, hot water and vanilla.
Cook until clear and thick.
Pour over rhubarb and top with remaining 1/2 of crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° 40 to 45 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine cukes, onion and green peppers.
In a saucepan, combine celery seed,
salt,
sugar	and
vinegar.
Bring
to a boil.
Pour liquid	over
cukes.
Let
cool, then store in the refrigerator.
Recipe makes 2 1/2 quarts.
Will keep up to one year.

title: karen's favorite x-lint chili
directions: Brown meat with bell pepper and onion; drain.
Add cooked meat with all other ingredients to crock-pot.
Do not drain any of the beans, add all juices to the chili.
Break up the X-Lint and add it last.

title: hershey's chocolate mint dessert(serves 12)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch). In large mixer bowl, beat flour, sugar, butter, eggs and syrup until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan; bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until top springs back when lightly touched.
(Top may still appear wet.)
Cool completely in pan.
Spread Mint Cream Layer on cake (see below); chill.
Pour Chocolate Topping over dessert (see below).
Cover; chill.

title: japanese puff pancakes(serves 2 to 4)
directions: Mix milk, flour and eggs together.
Melt butter in pie plate in oven.
When melted, remove plate and immediately add mixture. Sprinkle nutmeg on top and place in oven.
Edges will rise.
It is cooked when rising stops and cake is golden brown (not golden crisp), about 10 minutes or so.
Serve with syrup or powdered sugar or jams.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Steam broccoli until almost tender. Arrange in greased 2-quart casserole. Top with chicken.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and cheese.
Pour over chicken. Combine bread crumbs with melted butter and put on top. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Can be prepared the day before, but do not bake.

title: cherry salad
directions: Drain juice from pie cherries.
Squeeze juice from oranges and lemon.
Should be about 2 1/2 cups altogether.
Cook sugar and all three juices to a good boil.
Pour over Jell-O.
When cool, add cherries and pecans.
Chill until firm.

title: zucchini stuffing
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in pan until soft.
Drain.
Add cooked zucchini and onion to sour cream, soup and carrots.
Melt butter and add to stuffing.
Layer 1/2 stuffing on bottom of large baking dish, layer zucchini mixture, layer other half stuffing. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cheese soup
directions: Simmer celery, onions, bouillon cubes for 20 minutes in boiling water.
Add carrots, mixed vegetables, potatoes and simmer 40 minutes.
Add soup and cheese and blend well.
(At the beginning, I use more water, so it isn't too thick).
(My husband can even make this soup, so it can't be too difficult!)

title: minnie pearl's chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes an excellent salad.

title: pesto  chicken
directions: Slather chicken breasts with pesto sauce.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 55
minutes. Check for doneness. Can't get much simpler for a busy family.

title: pineapple-carrot salad
directions: Combine ingredients; toss lightly.
Chill before serving.

title: oreo cake
directions: Crush Oreos and place in buttered bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt butter and sprinkle over cookies.
Slice ice cream and layer over cookies.
Spoon hot fudge over ice cream and spread.
Add Cool Whip to top of hot fudge.
Sprinkle Oreo crumbs on Cool Whip. Freeze and serve.

title: quick sweet-sour beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid.
In saucepan, combine liquid, water, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Add drained beets (1 pound). They may be cut in half or quartered.
Bring to a boil and simmer for a few minutes.
Chill for several hours; best if 24 hours. Will keep in refrigerator for two weeks.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: scramble mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in large roaster pan.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.
Bake 1 hour, covered and 1 hour, uncovered, stirring and turning with wooden spoon every 15 minutes.
Makes 8 quarts.

title: beef lo mein
directions: Cook beef in a large, deep, nonstick skillet or a 3-4 qt. pot over medium high heat 3-4 minutes until browned. Remove to a bowl. In same skillet, bring 1 3/4 c. water and contents of seasoning packets to a boil over high heat. Break noodles into skillet and stir to coat with the boiling liquid. Stir in carrots and bok choy. Return to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 6 to 8 minutes, stirring occasionally, until vegetables and noodles are tender. Stir in beef and sesame oil.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Wash and break cauliflower and broccoli into small pieces. Let drain in colander.
Mix together onion, mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar and cheese.
Pour mix over cauliflower and broccoli. Refrigerate.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Lightly brown pork chops in a pan.
Place pork chops in an oven-safe pan.
Prepare the stuffing as directed on package. Place a scoopful of stuffing on each pork chop.
Pour milk into the pan.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Uncover for last 15 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water and chill until partially firm.
Add remaining ingredients and chill until firm.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain. If using ham, chop. Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch dish. Tear bread into small pieces over butter. Sprinkle sausage or ham over bread; sprinkle cheese over meat. Beat eggs and other ingredients. Pour over mixture. Chill overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Lay foil over top to keep from browning too quick.

title: pizza crust
directions: Preheat oven.
Mix water and yeast.
Add flour; stir.
Roll and knead until not sticky.
Spread out on pizza pan.
Add topping.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in ungreased loaf pan 9 x 5 x 3 inch.
Cook uncovered in 350 degree oven until done, about 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: paprika pork roast
directions: Combine garlic salt, ginger, pepper and paprika; rub over the entire roast. Place roast with fat side up on a greased rack in a roasting pan. Top with onion. Pour water into pan. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until a meat thermometer reads 160°-170°. Let stand for 10-15 minutes before slicing.

title: egg and caviar hors d'oeuvres
directions: Finely chop eggs. Cream eggs with butter. Add chives, Tabasco and Lea & Perrins sauce. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Serve on your choice of crackers with a top layer of sour cream and a topping of red caviar. (You may need 2 small jars of red caviar.)

title: hawaiian ham
directions: Blend 1/3 cup juice (drained from pineapple), soy sauce and ginger.
Pour over ham in shallow container.
Marinate 30 minutes turning once.
Remove ham from marinade and grill over hot coals until browned.
Brush occasionally with reserved marinade.
Heat pineapple slices last 2 minutes and serve with ham.

title: uncooked green tomato relish
