directions: Grind tomatoes, peppers and onions and sprinkle with salt. Let stand overnight.
Morning:
Drain well; add vinegar, sugar and mustard.
Mix well and put into sterilized jars.
Put on lids and seal bottle; do not process or cook.
Set on shelf.
This makes good meat loaf or Sloppy Joes mix.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onions in olive oil.
Add sofrito and other seasonings. Add water and bring to boil.
Add rice and cook on high temperature for 2 to 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Lower temperature and let simmer for 10 to 15 minutes or until rice is cooked.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together well.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour gradually and blend alternating with milk when adding each cup of flour.
Pour cake into a tube pan and bake at 350° until done.

title: heavenly hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate over very low heat. Stir in sugar, about 3/4 cup at a time. Be sure to blend well.

Mixture will become very thick and dry. Add salt and stir in milk gradually. Continue to cook 7 to 8 minutes to blend and dissolve sugar. Remove from heat and add vanilla. Serve hot or cold over ice cream. Refrigerate.

title: fruit salad
directions: Save juice from peaches and pineapple and pour in pan, then add pudding.
Cook to boil, then let it cool.
Mix all fruit except banana.
Mix fruit and cooled pudding together.
Cut up banana and mix.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: lemon bisque pie
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Chill and whip.
Chill thoroughly the evaporated milk and whip.
Fold in jello mixture and fill 2 vanilla wafer crumb crusts.
Top with a bit of crushed vanilla wafers (toasted with a bit of butter and baked in 375° oven and cooled).
Chill pie and serve.

title: chicken supreme dijon
directions: In large skillet, cook chicken in butter.
Remove the heated platter.
Keep warm.
To drippings in pan, add garlic, onion and mushrooms.
Cook, stirring, until onion is tender.
Stir until slightly thickened.
Add chicken, turning to coat in sauce.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: Melt butter in a pan and saute scallions, garlic, mushrooms for 3 minutes.
Stir in flour, then add catsup, wine and stock. Whisk gently.
Cook, stirring constantly until sauce is slightly thickened.
Good with fish.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix dry ingredients, then blend with water.
Spread over chicken pieces.
Place in nonstick baking pan. Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Contains 227 calories.

title: oyster pie
directions: Combine crumbs and pour butter over it.
Put layer of crumbs, oysters, salt, pepper and lemon juice, then add another layer.
Add cream.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: 7-layer overnight salad(ala diane hogan)
directions: In large bowl, layer lettuce, celery, green pepper, onion and peas.
Spread mayonnaise completely over peas with spatula. Sprinkle sugar lightly over mayonnaise.
Layer Cheddar cheese. Layer crumbled bacon over top.
Seal tightly with Saran Wrap. Refrigerate overnight.
(If leftovers are anticipated, drain various vegetables before layering to decrease eventual sogginess.)

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies.
Reserve 1/3 cup.
Press cookies in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour melted margarine over crumbs.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Mix cheese and sugar.
Blend in 1 Cool Whip.
Spread over cookie crumbs.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Prepare pudding according to directions.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Spread 2nd layer of Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with remaining cookie crumbs.

title: chili rellenos appetizer(terrific!)
directions: Place bread, buttered side down, in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex; place chili peppers over bread.
Cover with cheese mix.
Beat eggs, milk and flour.
Dribble egg mix over bread, chili and cheese layers. Bake approximately 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Mix together and cook until thick.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir beef and onion over medium heat until beef is brown; drain. Spread in plate.
Beat milk, biscuit mix, eggs, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour into the pie plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until inserted knife comes out clean, 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: applesauce spice mini muffins
directions: Cream
together
the first 3 ingredients. Sift together the next
ingredients, then add to creamed mixture and set aside. Heat
the
next
2	ingredients until foamy and add to batter. Stir
in
the chopped nuts. Bake in greased miniature muffin tins on	350°
for 15 to 20 minutes.
Roll or toss hot muffins in powdered sugar.
(Good served warm or room temperature).
Makes several.

title: yellow squash puffs
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Drain and mash.
Combine squash, onion and egg; add flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
Mix well and drop by level teaspoon into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.
(These make great hushpuppies for eating with fish.)

title: e-z brownies
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Watch time, do not overbake.)

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well and form into a loaf. Place mixture in a loaf pan and bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: bonnie's famous broccoli dish
directions: Cook and drain broccoli and put in buttered casserole dish. Mix 1/2 cup butter, bouillon cubes and milk in saucepan and cook until thick.
Add this mixture to broccoli.
Make stuffing with water and butter; mix with nuts and spread on top of broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: wild polk salad greens with bacon and eggs
directions: In a large pot, heat polk salad greens to boiling; add salt. Boil until tender or done.
Drain; add more water. Repeat boiling procedure, except don't add any more salt.
Drain again; add cool water and let cool.
Then squeeze out excess water into balls; set aside.

title: hazelnut cake(to make one 10-inch cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
In a large bowl, beat the egg yolks and the whole egg.
Beat until the mixture is thick and light in color.
Gradually beat in 1/2 cup of the sugar, then the nuts and the breadcrumbs.
Continue to beat until mixture forms a dense, moist mass.

title: broccoli crumb casserole
directions: Put broccoli into boiling water and let thaw; separate with fork and put in strainer (do not cook broccoli).
Put cheese in pan and add soup.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted.
Put broccoli in dish.
Cover with sauce and then croutons.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cover if croutons get
too brown.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Pour mushroom soup in large bowl.
Add milk and 1 cup of potato chips, onions, tuna, pepper and sauce.
Mix well.
Pour in greased casserole dish. Sprinkle paprika over top.
Bake at 450° in oven for 30 minutes.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer in bowl.
Cover with mayonnaise and chill.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour in casserole dish.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Two cups of cornflakes may be crumbled on top after baking, if desired.
A good dish to prepare for Sunday dinner.

title: cornish hens stuffed with wild rice
directions: Add stock to water; cook rice in this, covered, until water is absorbed, about 50 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup of butter, basil leaves, cinnamon, parsley, 2 teaspoons Bon Appetit, onion, salt and pepper; mix well.
Fill cavities of hens.
Cover exposed stuffing with aluminum foil to prevent drying.
Brush hens with a mixture of 1/4 cup of butter and remaining Bon Appetit.
Roast in a 450° oven for 20 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°; roast 45 minutes.

title: mixed nuts bars
directions: Combine flour, salt, brown sugar and margarine.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch slightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.
Spread 2 cups of nuts on top.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a heavy saucepan; stir with a wire whisk until well blended.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and smooth.
Stir in flavoring.
Chill thoroughly.
Stir in coconut.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook noodles according to package; drain well.
Add butter and cream and then add grated cheese.
Serve hot.

title: triple peanut cookies
directions: In a large bowl cream sugars, shortening and 1/2 cup of the peanut butter with an electric mixer.
Blend in the corn syrup, milk and vanilla.
Mix together the flour, baking soda and salt; add to the creamed mixture, mixing well.
Shape dough into a 1 1/2-inch roll about 18-inches long.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill for 2 hours.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs 15 minutes.
After eggs are cool, crack off shell; cut egg long ways in half.
Take all yolks out of eggs.
Place yolks in bowl.
Mix mayo, mustard and relish with yolks.
Mix to taste.
Place back in eggs and sprinkle with paprika.

title: apricot salad
directions: Combine jello, sugar and water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil,
stirring
to
dissolve
sugar and jello.
Remove from heat. Stir
in
fruit.
Set
aside to cool.
Combine milk and cream cheese,
beating until smooth.
Stir in gelatin mixture, then the nuts.
Pour into mold or bowl.
Chill until firm.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together except stuffing mix and butter. Top vegetables with stuffing mix and melted butter that have been mixed.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is good and brown.

title: rotisserie chicken or pork
directions: Brush meat with bottled Italian salad dressing.
Mix spices and sprinkle on meat while turning on the rotisserie.
Cook until done.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve warm as a dip with Tostitos or other corn chips.

title: every day chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and egg.
Add milk, soda, cocoa, flour and vanilla, then the boiling water.
Pour into pan and bake.

title: cheese vegetable chowder
directions: Saute cabbage, onion, celery, peas and carrots in butter in a 3 quart saucepan for 8 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring frequently.
Add corn, milk and seasonings; heat over low temperature for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add cheese; stir until melted.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash and pick over beans, cover with cold water and soak overnight.
Cover beans with 2 or 3 inches of water, using the water they soaked in.
Add ham bone, onion, bell pepper, garlic, cumin powder, red pepper and Tabasco sauce.
Cook slowly for several hours, about 3 or 4.
Add salt after beans are tender. (The beans will make thick gravy.)
About 20 minutes before beans are done, add sliced sausage.
Serve over rice.
Serves 8.

title: grandma olson's pound cake(a very light cake)
directions: Combine all ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Beat for 15 minutes.
Flour and grease tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place corn in baking dish; set aside. Melt margarine in skillet over medium heat.
Add flour and blend. Add whipping cream; mix well.
Add hot mixture to corn and blend well.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Butter bread on both sides and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook sausage and drain.
Spoon sausage over the bread and sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs, half and half and salt.
Mix well.
Pour over cheese.
Cover and chill overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Bake uncovered 45 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion for 5 minutes; drain.
Pour melted margarine into a casserole dish; add squash.
Combine egg, milk, salt, pepper and sugar; mix well and pour over squash.
Sprinkle evenly with cheese.
Spread cracker crumbs over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy lemon pie(makes one 8 or 9-inch pie)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks with Eagle Brand, ReaLemon brand and food coloring, if desired.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool; chill.
Spread with whipping cream.
Garnish as desired.
Preparation time:
10 minutes.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: france's chicken casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Blend in flour, soup and milk.
Add mushrooms and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook wild rice according to directions on box.
Layer rice, chicken, sauce and cheese. Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes at 350° in oven.

title: banana cake
directions: Combine bananas, oil and sugar.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately to banana mixture with buttermilk.
Stir in nuts, if desired.

title: sausage balls
directions: Crumble the sausage and mix with cheese.
Add biscuit mix one cup at a time.
Form into small balls around 1-inch in diameter. Place on ungreased pan and bake at 350° to 375° until light brown, approximately 13 to 15 minutes.
May be made ahead and frozen.
If so, cook a little longer.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat cake mix, oil, eggs, and oranges for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into three 9-inch cake pans.
(Line the bottom with wax paper and spray sides and bottom with no-stick cooking spray.) Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, egg and oil on low speed.
Add flour and baking powder.
Fold in by hand raw apples and nuts.
Bake in oblong pan at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach.
Drain.
Squeeze water out.
Mix all ingredients together.
Form golf ball size.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Serve plain or with a dip (Spicy Mustard Sauce).

title: eggplant appetizer
directions: Bake the eggplant in a preheated 350° oven until tender (about 1 hour).
Cool slightly.
Peel the eggplant.
Mash, leaving a lumpy texture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Adjust the seasonings to your taste.
Serve with rye bread, pita or crackers.

title: vegetables with creamy garlic sauce
directions: In a small bowl, fold together yogurt, garlic and oil. Transfer to a small serving bowl.
Arrange the artichoke, potatoes, carrots, beets and chickpeas on a large platter.
Serve the vegetables with sauce.
(Tear off artichoke leaves and dip in sauce.)

title: dill bread
directions: Warm cottage cheese and butter slightly.
Add dill seed, onion, sugar, baking soda, salt and eggs.
Beat until blended.
Combine water and yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir into cottage cheese mixture.
Stir in as much flour as possible, then knead in the rest.
Continue kneading until dough becomes smooth and elastic. Place dough in greased bowl.
Turn to grease top.
Cover and let stand until double in bulk.
Punch down.
Shape into 2 loaves and place in 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Cover and let rise until dough reaches top of pans.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until loaves are browned and sound hollow when tapped.
Remove from pans.
Cool on racks.

title: impossible bacon quiche
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease 10-inch quiche dish. Sprinkle bacon, cheese, onion and vegetables in dish. Beat remainder until smooth. Pour over all and bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes. Cool 5 minutes. Serves 6.

title: mom's sugar cookies
directions: In a very large mixing bowl, cream sugar, shortening and eggs. Put soda in sour cream and let foam up.
Add to sugar, shortening and egg mixture.
Add nutmeg.
Add flour, a couple cups at a time. Take a little dough at a time on a floured board.
Roll and cut out.
Can decorate or sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cut broccoli into small pieces and parboil until tender; drain.
Saute onion in butter; add soup.
Beat well.
Line baking dish with crumbs.
Layer broccoli, mushrooms and cheese.
Pour soup mixture over this.
Save 1/2 cup crumbs for topping.
Bake at 350° until mixture starts to bubble (about 30 minutes).

title: creamy lemon pudding cheesecake
directions: Mix wafers, 1 tablespoon of sugar and butter; press firmly into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan. Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: "wendy's frosty" chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: oatmeal chocolate cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and cook to a rolling boil for about 2 minutes.
Add coconut, nuts, vanilla and oatmeal.
Mix well and drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: cucumber sauce
directions: Grate 1/3 cup cucumber and onion slice (1 teaspoon). Press in strainer to remove juice.
Add mayonnaise, vinegar, sour cream, parsley and seasonings.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Makes 18 small muffins.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: In small bowl, mix cream cheese, 2 cups whip cream, sugar and 2 tablespoons of milk.
Spread on bottom of graham cracker crust. Put fruit on top.

title: pork chop supper
directions: Heat shortening in a large skillet or electric frypan.
Brown pork chops on both sides.
Season with salt and pepper and add bouillon cube, dissolved in water.
Place vegetables on top of chops.
Cover tightly, reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: norwegian nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Toast pecans in oven for 8 minutes to warm them.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Add salt. Continue beating until slightly stiffened.
Add sugar gradually until stiff peaks form.
Add vanilla and beat until well blended. Fold warmed pecans into meringue mixture.

title: festive popcorn
directions: After popcorn is popped, open bag.
Sprinkle on dressing; re-close bag.
Shake vigorously.
Serve.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press out cookie dough and bake until golden brown.
Cream sugar, cream cheese and vanilla.
Spread over baked cookie. Arrange fruit on top.
Cut into small pieces.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil together.
Add eggs and pumpkin; mix well. Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with water.

title: pork chop quickie
directions: Place pork chops in baking dish.
Salt and pepper; slice onion into rings and place on pork chops.
Mix mushroom soup with milk until smooth and pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° if glass pan).
Grease square pan. Thoroughly mix all ingredients and bake for 45 minutes.

title: chinook berry shortcake(modern)
directions: Mash berries slightly.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar and set aside.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all
ingredients together and pour into greased and floured pan.
Makes
loaf
pan.
Bake at 300° about 1 hour. Pecans may be sprinkled on top of cake before baking.

title: golden wassail
directions: Heat in large pan to boiling.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and strain.
Garnish with orange slices.
Good cold, too. Makes 10 (1/2) cups.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: Wash cauilflower, broccoli and green pepper.
Cut cauliflower and broccoli into flowerets and put into large bowl.
Dice green pepper and onion; cut in fine pieces.
Mix all together with cauliflower and broccoli.
Add cheese and bacon.
Cream together mayonnaise with sugar, adding milk, if desired.
Pour on the ingredients in bowl and toss.
Let set several hours.
Toss again before serving.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and molasses.
Sift flour, soda and salt. Add alternately with milk to first mixture. Add spices and vanilla. Bake in layer pans.
Frost with favorite frosting.

title: pineapple lime velvet salad
directions: Add jello to water and stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese and beat until cheese is well blended.
Chill until slightly congealed.
Add pineapple and celery.
Fold in Dream Whip, lightly but thoroughly.
Add nuts and cherries.
Pour into mold that has been rinsed with cold water.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, flour, salt, soda and spices.
Stir lightly.
Cut in shortening to resemble coarse crumbs.
Stir in molasses and egg.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll them in sugar.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Remove immediately from cookie sheets when done.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: pepper steak caribou
directions: You need a Dutch oven or a frying pan with a tight cover for this recipe.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: *To sour milk, add 1 tablespoon vinegar plus milk to equal 1 cup.

title: mud cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together. Remove from heat and stir in eggs and sugar. Mix well. Add flour, salt, nuts, and vanilla; mix well. Spoon batter into a 13 x 9 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35-45 minutes. Sprinkle marshmallows on top of warm cake; let stand in warm oven (turned off) for a few minutes. Cover with frosting.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Put chocolate and milk in a bowl.
Stir with a mixer.
Put in refrigerator for 3 minutes.
Put in dishes.
Eat.
"When Daddy and I make chocolate pudding, it tastes chocolate good."

title: apple butter cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl cream together brown sugar and lard; beat in eggs.
In a separate bowl sift together flour and spices. Stir flour mixture, buttermilk and soda mixture into sugar and lard alternately.
Add apple butter and stir lightly.
Pour into a 9 x 5-inch glass loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until it tests done.

title: cheese ring
directions: Use a 3 1/2 cup ring mold sprayed with Pam.
Mix all ingredients.
Press firmly into mold.
Chill until firm.
Invert onto plate and fill center with strawberry preserves.
Especially good with Triscuits crackers.

title: malone's salad dressing
directions: Put all
ingredients in a quart jar in the order given. Shake well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: world's simplest candy
directions: Place chocolate chips in a microwave-safe bowl and microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes, stirring 1/2 way through cooking, until melted.
Stir in the nuts or dried fruits (or a combination of them).
Drop the mixture by teaspoonful onto waxed paper-lined baking sheet and refrigerate until firm.
Store in cool room temperature.
Makes about 15 candies.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crust:
graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick butter (melted). Press in covered dish.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Melt oleo in skillet.
Add onions, celery and carrots.
Saute for 10 minutes or so.
Add boiling water with chicken bouillon cube or chicken broth.
Simmer until vegetables are done.
Combine flour, salt, pepper and milk.
Cook until thick.
Add to cooked vegetables.
Line casserole with chicken.
Top with vegetables. Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Put mashed potatoes on top of vegetables and serve.
Chicken and vegetable sauce can be made ahead and refrigerated or frozen until ready to use.

title: bread dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Hollow out 1 round loaf.
(Use these as bread pieces for dip.)
Cut other loaf into cubes for dipping.
Fill center of hollow loaf with dip.
Arrange cubes around filled loaf.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar and Karo syrup; cook 4 minutes.
Add peanuts; cook 4 minutes.
Add vanilla and butter; cook 2 minutes.
Add soda; stir well and pour quickly onto well-greased cookie sheet. Cool; break.

title: mock sour cream
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender until smooth.
Use in place of sour cream for potatoes, dips, salads and fruits.
Yields 1 pint.

title: veggie layered salad
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer in order:
lettuce, green pepper, chopped onion, celery, peas and water chestnuts.
Cover with equal parts of Miracle Whip and sour cream, the sugar and Worcestershire sauce, sealing edges.
Refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, add grated Cheddar cheese and bacon bits (optional).
Garnish with cherry tomatoes.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Cook potatoes until tender and mash.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Add other ingredients.
Melt butter and pour into buttered Pyrex dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Make Topping.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potato finely.
Sift flour, salt, pepper and sugar together.
Add eggs, potato, sour cream and onion.
Add parsley.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Mold into oblong loaf. Place in preheated oven of 375° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Debone chicken and break up in the oleo, which has been melted in the casserole dish.
Drain Veg-All and pour over top of chicken.
Mix broth with soup and pour over vegetables.
Mix Bisquick and milk real good and pour over all.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: oat bran delight
directions: Grease	and
flour
a
13 x 9-inch baking pan.	Preheat oven to	350°.
In 2 quart saucepan, melt margarine and remove from heat.
Stir
in brown sugar until well-mixed, then blend in
eggs and yogurt.
Add whole wheat and all-purpose flours, bran,	orange peel,
vanilla,
salt and baking soda.
Fold in prunes.
Spread batter into greased pan.
If desired, sprinkle top with
2 tablespoons
oats.	Bake
30 minutes or until top springs back when lightly pressed with fingertip.
Cool in pan on wire rack. Cut into bars; makes about 3 dozen.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Prepare creamy garlic noodle mix according to directions on package.
Combine prepared noodle mix, chopped onion and fake crab in casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 30 to 40 minutes until heated.
Or cook in microwave about 15 minutes, turning dish every 15 minutes.

title: rosamarina salad
directions: Drain fruit, mix juice, sugar, salt, flour and eggs.
Cook until thick.
Add cooked macaroni and mix gently.
Let set overnight.
Add Cool Whip and drained fruit in morning.

title: mason county yeast rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix sugar, shortening and salt; pour boiling water over mixture.
When water is lukewarm, sprinkle yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add eggs and slowly add flour mixing as you add.
Mix well.
Cover and let rise 30 minutes in a warm area. Punch down.
Roll out onto lightly flour surface.
Cut with round cutter.
Place into 3 buttered cake pans.
Brush top with melted butter, cover (wax paper works well) and let rise again for 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes 30 to 36.
Freezes well.

title: broccoli casserole with rice
directions: Over low flame, saute onion in butter until tender; combine with remaining ingredients.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; slice while warm.
In small bowl mix mayonnaise, red wine vinegar, sugar and milk.
In large bowl mix potatoes, celery, onions and mayonnaise mixture together. Garnish with paprika and green pepper.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Drain green beans.
Pour beans into a casserole dish and mix in soup.
Sprinkle cheese over mixture. Place onion rings on cheese.
Cover and cook for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Uncover and cook for 5 minutes.

title: strawberry charlotte russe
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add marshmallows and partially defrosted strawberries, stirring until marshmallows dissolve.
Add lemon juice and chill until partially congealed.
Beat until fluffy.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Blend in whipped cream and nuts.
Pour into dish and chill until firm.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: irish bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Cream together margarine and sugar.
Beat in egg, sour cream and milk.
Fold in the flour mixture and raisins.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: noodles
directions: Mix ingredients and drop into hot beef or chicken broth.

title: peppery hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, water, margarine and egg.
Mix well.
Stir in onion and peppers.
Carefully drop batter by teaspoonfuls into hot oil (375°).
Fry 3 to 5 minutes, turning once, until golden brown.
Drain well on paper towels.
Yields about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: blueberry buttermilk pancakes
directions: In a large bowl, whisk together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Whisk in egg, buttermilk, vanilla and 2 1/2 tablespoons oil, whisking until smooth. Fold in blueberries gently.

title: hidden valley ranch cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients except pecans.
Put in freezer for 30 minutes.
Roll into a ball and then roll in chopped pecans.

title: tortillas for any occasion
directions: Mix together flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening. Add warm water, little at a time and stir with fork until dough forms a ball but is not sticky.
Knead 5 times and let rest for 10 minutes.
Roll out any size you want.
Cook in an ungreased black cast-iron skillet until dotted with golden spots on both sides. Cool and freeze or serve warm.
Use with breakfast foods, lunch, dinner, beef, cheese, tomatoes, tuna salad, sausage, eggs, etc.

title: baked ham
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Shake flour in Reynolds oven bag.
Place in large roasting pan at least 2-inches deep.
Trim skin and fat from ham, leaving a thin layer of fat.
Score surface of ham in diamond pattern and insert cloves.
Place ham in bag.
Close bag with nylon tie.
Cut 6 (1/2-inch) slits in top.
Insert meat thermometer through slit in bag into thickest part of ham, not touching bone.
Bake until thermometer reads 140° (2 to 2 1/2 hours).
Let stand in bag 15 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: vegetable chicken delight
directions: Cut all vegetables first and place in large mixing bowl.
Add vinegar, olive oil, basil and oregano (salt to taste is purely optional).
Toss so that all vegetables are coated.
Set aside to briefly marinate.
Prepare your chicken.
Heat a large skillet or electric frypan with 2 tablespoons additional olive oil.
When hot, brown garlic in oil.
When done, add chicken and toss until it just turns white.
Add vegetables with all the liquid.
Toss to mix and turn down heat.
Cover and let simmer, stirring occasionally, for approximately 15 to 20 minutes, or until veggies are just tender and not soggy.
Spoon over rice or pasta.

title: sweet potato slaw
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, honey, lemon juice, lemon peel, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Mix until smooth.
In a large serving bowl Combine potatoes, apple, pineapple and nuts.
Mix well.
Add mayonnaise mixture and toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Serve cold.

title: rolls
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Melt butter and heat liquid to 115°.
Beat eggs and add, with liquid, to flour mixture; stir.
Turn onto a floured board; knead 7 to 8 minutes.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Form rolls.
Let rise and bake about 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes about 2 dozen rolls.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Beat egg.
Dip chicken breasts in egg and then roll in bread crumbs.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and cover with spaghetti sauce.
Bake 45 minutes (30 minutes if boneless breasts) at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Return to oven until melted (15 minutes at most).

title: pound cake
directions: Cream
together
whipped margarine and sugar.
Add eggs (one at	a
time),
flavoring, flour and milk.
Spray tube pan with Baker's Joy.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: esterina's pasta
directions: In large skillet, add onions, garlic and red pepper to oil. Cook until onions become transparent.
Add pasta to boiling water.

title: cocoa chiffon cake
directions: Mix cocoa and boiling water.
Stir until smooth, set aside. Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until very stiff.
Sift dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center.
Add oil, egg yolks and cocoa.
Mix and add vanilla.
Beat well.
Fold in egg whites.
Use angel food pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 55 minutes. Raise heat to 350° and continue 10 minutes.

title: ham-potato au gratin
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in oleo until tender.

Stir in flour and pepper. Add milk and bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Add shredded cheese and Miracle Whip. Stir until cheese melts. Combine potatoes and ham with sauce; bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: black beans and jalapenos
directions: Saute jalapenos in olive oil with garlic and cumin.
Add beans and broth, then cook for 5 minutes at medium heat.
Mash beans. Boil and stir for 10 minutes.
Season beans with salt, pepper and lime juice.
Top with cilantro and onions.
Serve as a side dish or in burritos.

title: pineapple meringue cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Mix in the flour, baking powder, vanilla and milk.
Make two layers and add Meringue Topping before baking.

title: edna's buttermilk fudge
directions: Let buttermilk and soda sit in black iron skillet for 15 minutes.
Add the sugar, butter and syrup and bring to a boil. Turn down heat and stir to keep from sticking.
When it reaches soft ball stage, add nuts.
Stir until well mixed and pour into buttered dish.
Cut when cool.

title: white grape punch
directions: Freeze a ring with juice and add some fresh grapes or mint for effect.

title: yogi's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Drain juice off mushrooms.
Combine tomato paste, sauce and both kinds of Chef Boyardee sauce.
Stir in mushrooms and hamburger.
Heat over medium heat and serve.
Freezes well.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and freeze in muffin pans or pour into a large plastic container to freeze.
Pop out of pans to serve or drop into bags and return to freezer to serve later.
Cut salad in plastic containers into squares to serve.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix butter and bouillon cubes then add soup mix, rice, and water.
Mix and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Salt and pepper chicken and place on top of rice mixture.
Cover and bake at 350 degreed for 1 1/2 hours, or for boneless chicken, 1 hour.

title: texas pan cake
directions: On top of the stove mix the ingredients.
Heat thoroughly and stir well.
Pour over cake and spread, then sprinkle with about 1 cup chopped pecans.

title: lasagna di bologna
directions: Prepare lasagna according to package directions; drain.
In large skillet, heat oil.
Add zucchini and onion; cook until tender.
Stir in Pasta Sauce and oregano.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
In medium bowl, blend Ricotta, eggs and Parmesan.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Chop all vegetables finely, divide broccoli and cauliflower into very small pieces.
Add dressing and put bacon (crumbled) on top just before serving.

title: cheesy broccoli rice
directions: Chop onion and set aside. Dice red bell pepper and set aside. Lightly spray a medium saucepan with nonstick cooking spray and heat over medium heat. Add chopped onion and diced red bell pepper to saucepan. Cook, stirring often, until tender. Add instant rice to saucepan; stir well to combine. Add the water, undiluted broccoli and cheese soup, minced fresh parsley and salt. Mix well. Bring the rice mixture to a boil. Reduce the heat. Cover and cook rice mixture until liquid is absorbed and the rice is tender, about 10 minutes.
Serve rice immediately.

title: chicken el paso
directions: On waxed paper, combine crumbs and chili powder.
In shallow dish, dip chicken into dressing.
Coat with crumb mixture.
On baking sheet, arrange chicken.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, turning once during baking. Serve with salsa.

title: missouri (crock-pot) chicken
directions: Combine French dressing, jam and soup mix in saucepan and bring to simmer.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Brown chicken in oil.
Place in slow cooker.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add sauce.
Cover and cook on low 4 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken marengo
directions: Place chicken in a greased casserole and put sliced mushrooms on top.
Mix together remaining ingredients, except pasta or noodles, and pour over the chicken. Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over pasta or noodles.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Beat egg yolks, sugar and juice together.
Add flour and mix well.
Fold in egg whites.
Use a 16 x 11-inch pan lined with wax paper and oiled well.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes. Wet dish towel in ice water and squeeze out well.
Pour cake out on dish towel and roll up in wet towel.
Put in refrigerator and let cool well.

title: lima bean and egg casserole
directions: Cook beans and one very small onion in boiling water until tender.
Melt fat; add flour.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook until thick.
Add 1/4 cup cheese; cook until melted.
Add mustard.
Arrange eggs and beans in alternate layers using 8-inch casserole and cover with sauce.
Top with crumbs mixed with rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if skin is tough.
Otherwise, just scrub and rinse them.
Cut potatoes into thin slices.

title: sour cream yeast dough
directions: Heat sour cream over low heat until lukewarm; stir frequently. Dissolve yeast in water in large mixing bowl.
Add warm sour cream, margarine, sugar, salt, eggs and 2 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Add enough of the remaining flour until dough cleans side of bowl.
Knead until smooth.
Cover and let rise in a warm place, about an hour or until doubled.
Punch down dough.
Shape into loaves, let rise until double and bake 30 minutes.
Also can be made into pecan rolls.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Then add eggs and milk.
Stir until smooth.
Fry in oil.
Makes 7 servings.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Lay rolls out flat on baking sheet, pressing seams together. Bake according to directions.
Mix the cream cheese, dressing mix and mayonnaise together; spread mixture over cool crescent dough. Shred broccoli, cauliflower and carrots; sprinkle vegetables over top.
Cut into squares; keep in refrigerator.

title: hidden valley cheese puffs
directions: Cut 10 (1-inch) slices of bread.
Mix ingredients.
Spread mixture onto slices and put under broiler until golden and puffy.

title: apple pie
directions: Cook apples until tender, sweeten to taste.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix together the flour, sugar and milk, then pour over butter.
Add fruit on top of mixture, but not stir in.
Bake at 350° until crust comes to the top and browns.

title: cheese-chili casserole
directions: Grate cheese and reserve 1/2 cup.
Drain and pat chilies dry. Layer 9 x 13-inch pan with chilies and cheeses.
Pour beaten mixture of eggs, milk and flour over layers.
Refrigerate at this point if you want to prepare before baking.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread pan with crescent rolls (push up on sides of pan). Sprinkle cooked sausage over rolls, then Cheddar cheese.
Beat eggs with salt and pepper. Pour over cheese. Add hash brown potatoes and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, water and cornstarch. Cook until thick. Add strawberry jello.
Mix well.
Let set for 10 minutes. Mix in strawberries.
Pour into baked and cooled pie shell. Top with Cool Whip.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cut shortening and cheese into flour.
Add milk.
Mix until forms ball. Knead on floured surface about 20 times.
Roll into 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.

title: date sticks
directions: Mix and bake at 350° in an 11 x 7-inch pan.
Let cool slightly. Cut into bars, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: taco bar
directions: In skillet, cook and stir ground meat over medium heat 8-10 minutes or until it is no longer pink, breaking it into small pieces.
Add taco mix and amount of water as directed on pkg. Continue cooking according to pkg. directions.
Remove skillet from heat.
Stir in one cup of salsa.
Place all ingredients in small containers on a table and allow guests to make their own taco.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pig eating cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes for round layer pans or 35 to 40 minutes or sheet cake.

title: garden patch pancakes
directions: Stir together flour, salt and sugar.
Add sour cream, cottage cheese and eggs; gently beat, just until flour mixture is moistened.
Drop by 1/4 cup well apart onto a hot, oiled griddle. Cook until bubbles break, turn and brown other side.
Serve with maple syrup.

title: chocolate or lemon squares
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 egg and butter.
Mix well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
With a mixer, mix remaining eggs, cream cheese, vanilla and powdered sugar until smooth and creamy. Spread on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: dirty rice
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oleo.
Mix rest of ingredients in. Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 375°.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Add wine; simmer a couple minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except pecans.
Spoon mixture into a 8 inch square baking dish and sprinkle with pecans. Bake at 350°.
Serve hot with your favorite crackers.

title: soy-soy chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Soak chicken pieces 2 to 4 hours.
Bake until done at 350° about 1 hour.

title: baked breaded fish
directions: Grease pan with oleo.
Put fish in bottom, sprinkle mixture on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for half an hour.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine all but bacon, parsley, Tabasco, cream and cheese in a large kettle.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours or until vegetables are tender. Blend half of soup (to thicken) in blender and return to kettle. Add bacon, parsley, Tabasco and cream.
Bring just to a boil. Adjust seasonings.
Serve topped with cheese.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: christmas star cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, salt and flavoring. Stir in flour and blend thoroughly. Chill 1/2 hour. Roll small portion of dough on floured board to 1/8 to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut in stars or other shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet about 1-inch apart.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Decorate with colored frosting and colored sugar.
Makes 2 to 4 dozen.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Pare eggplant and cut into small pieces. Cook in boiling water with salt until tender. Drain and mash.
Place bacon in skillet and cook until brown. Add onion; cook gently 15 minutes.

Add tomatoes and seasonings; cook another 15 minutes. Combine eggplant to tomato mixture. Add 1 cup bread crumbs and 1/2 the cheese. Place in greased casserole dish and sprinkle with remaining crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken in water with celery stalks, sliced onion, 1 tablespoon whole pepper, 2 bay leaves and 1 tablespoon salt.
Boil broccoli 5 minutes; line baking dish with broccoli and add diced chicken.
Mix other ingredients together except cheese and crumbs. Pour over; sprinkle on cheese and cover with crumbs (dressing crumbs can be substituted).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: flour frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk over low heat, stirring until thick. Remove from heat, add a pinch of salt and cool.
Beat shortening, margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add flour mixture and vanilla; then beat until fluffy.
Tastes a lot like Cool Whip.

title: sandwich filling
directions: Chop raisins in a blender or food processor. Mix all ingredients with enough mayo to moisten. Spread on your choice of bread.

title: old-fashioned almond crunch candy
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine butter, sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Boil to brittle stage (300°) on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Stir in almonds.
Pour into foil-lined 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate morsels over brittle.
Let stand 5 minutes until morsels become shiny and soft.
Spread evenly over crunch.
Cool to room temperature.
Chill 1 hour.
Break into bite-size pieces.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well with hand.
Form into balls, drop into sauce and cook until done.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Put all fresh seasonings in water and boil until tender.
Add chicken broth.
Fry chicken in small amount of oil until brown. Season chicken and roll in flour before cooking.
Put chicken and chicken broth in water and let boil on high for a few minutes. Turn heat to low.
Make a gravy, deep brown with flour and bacon fat.
Put gravy in water gradually to mix well.
Let mixture cook 1/2 hour.
Add ham and other seasonings.
Cook on low for 1/2 hour. Add crabs, oysters and shrimp 15 minutes before serving.
Serve over rice.

title: barbecue hamburger
directions: Brown the meat in a heavy skillet, stirring to keep crumbly. Add salt.
In another skillet, melt shortening and saute onion and celery until tender.
Add to hamburger.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve on hot hamburger buns.
Serves 50.

title: pumpkin custard
directions: Combine eggs, sweetener and pumpkin.
Blend well.
Add salt, spices and milk; mix well.
Pour into 8-inch pie pan.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Cut and serve like pie pieces, although it has no pastry crust.

title: ebelskievers
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix together milk, margarine and beaten egg yolks; add to dry ingredients, stirring until blended.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites into mixture, stirring sparingly.
Put heaping tablespoon mixture in hot greased Ebelskiever tins or cook on greased pancake griddle. Serves 4.

title: hot wings my way
directions: Fry chicken wings.
While frying, mix melted butter and hot sauce.
Immediately upon removing chicken from frying pan, dip each piece in hot sauce mixture.
Drain and serve hot.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes and salt in large pot.
While potatoes are cooking, combine broth, water, onions, celery, carrots and pepper in heavy large saucepan.
Cook separate until all veggies are soft. Drain potatoes.
Add broth mixture, 2 cans milk and cheese to potatoes.
Simmer on low for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream all ingredients well.
Form into ball.
Wrap in tinfoil. Freeze.
Unthaw 1/2 hour before using.
Roll in crushed walnuts and serve with crackers.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar, eggs and vanilla. Blend in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and the cinnamon.
Roll cookies in the cinnamon sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 minutes at 375°.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours.
Top with cherry pie filling before serving.

title: impossible pie
directions: In blender, combine milk, eggs, sugar, vanilla, coconut, margarine and the biscuit mix.
Cover blender; blend 1 minute. Pour batter into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350° or until done (when knife comes out clean).

title: camp vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat quickly with onion.
Add tomato juice.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer until veggies are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grandma rose's 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: A very versatile plain cake recipe.
Combine butter and sugar until creamy, add eggs and beat well.
Add half the flour and half of the milk; beat, then add rest of the ingredients.
Mix well. Place in 2 greased layer pans or 1 Bundt pan.
Bake.
Cool and frost.

title: maine blueberry slump
directions: Getting out a cookbook is fun, but no picnic.
If we print jokes, people say we are silly.
If we don't they say we are too serious.
If we clip things from other magazines, we are too lazy to write them ourselves.
If we don't, we are too fond of our own stuff.
If we don't print contributions, we don't appreciate true genius.
If we do print them, the pages are filled with junk. Now, very likely, someone will say we swiped this from some other cookbook.......we did!!!!!!!!

title: frozen salad
directions: Let milk come to a boil and drop marshmallows in.
Stir until melted.
Let cool and mix with whipping cream, fruit and nuts. Pour into casserole; sprinkle top with crushed vanilla wafers. Place in refrigerator and chill.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Fry hamburger and onion until brown.
Add salsa.
Simmer until heated thoroughly.
Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and garlic.
Then add in cooked egg noodles.
Pour hamburger and cheese noodle mix in oblong glass dish.
Bake at 350° until thoroughly heated.

title: cheese cake tarts
directions: Mix together and press into paper-lined tart pans.

title: vegetable mousse
directions: Steam or microwave each vegetable separately.
Drain and pat dry with a paper towel.
Butter a glass ovenware loaf pan and line the bottom with buttered wax paper.

Using a processor or blender, puree each vegetable separately, adding 2 eggs, 1/2 teaspoon lemon juice and 1 tablespoon heavy cream (salt, pepper, nutmeg to taste, I use a large pinch of pepper, nutmeg and salt substitute) to each batch, blending well.
Layer in loaf pan and cover with the waxed paper.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for approximately 1 hour. Serve sliced.
The colors of the vegetable layers present a pretty addition to your table.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: caramel fudge
directions: Put sugar, butter and milk in pan and boil until soft ball forms; remove from heat.
Add vanilla and soda.
Soda will make it caramel.
Add chopped English walnuts.

title: seaside chicken
directions: Pound chicken breasts to 1/2-inch thick.
Saute in 3 tablespoons butter for abut 2 minutes, each side.
Remove chicken and place in baking dish.
Brown onion and mushroom in same pan and saute until tender and slightly browned.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour over chicken and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until brown on top.
Serve with rice.

title: bold (best of leftovers)
directions: Will also need a deep glass casserole.

title: chocolate delight bites
directions: Heat chocolate in large microwave bowl at High speed for 2 minutes.
Stir until completely melted.
Beat in cream cheese and vanilla.
Cool to room temperature.
Gently stir in Cool Whip and refrigerate one hour.
Shape into balls about 1-inch size and gently roll in nuts, coconut or chocolate.
Store in covered dish in refrigerator.

title: microwave sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger in microwave in casserole dish until desired doneness, about ten minutes on High power.
Add rest of ingredients.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Remove cover and microwave for 25 minutes on 50% power.
Stir at least once.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Pour off excess grease and place mixture in baking dish.
Add sauce, rice, beans, 1 1/4 cups cheese and chips (save enough chips to sprinkle on top).
Mix well. Cover with remaining cheese and chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: farmers strata
directions: In skillet, cook bacon until crisp. Add ham and onion. Cook and stir until onion is tender. Drain.

title: eggplant souffle
directions: Chop eggplant; cook and drain.
Mix eggplant and onion together.
Add soup.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites, salt and pepper.
Place all ingredients in a casserole dish; add shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 275° for about 40 minutes.

title: ho-ho cake
directions: Make according to box instructions.
Bake in 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until tender.
Cool, peel and mash. Measure exactly 4 cups.
Stir in brown sugar, orange rind and orange juice.
Mix well.
Chill mixture until stiff enough to handle.
Shape 1/4 c. potato mix around 1 large marshmallow.
Roll in coconut or pecans and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
May be frozen at this point.
Thaw before baking.

title: candied peanuts
directions: Dissolve sugar and water over heat.
Add peanuts and cook until mixture is absorbed on peanuts.
Then bake for 30 minutes at 300°, stirring about every 5 minutes.

title: watergate cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan.
Remove from pan after 1/2 hour.
Let cake completely cool before icing.

title: strawberry coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan to be cooked in.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: rhubarb torte
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, oats and melted butter.
Pack firmly into an ungreased 7 x 11-inch pan.

title: mexican eight layered dip
directions: 1st Layer: Bean dip.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place flour, salt and pepper in a paper bag and shake well. Add loin chops and shake well.
Place chops in shallow baking dish. Combine catsup, brown sugar and mustard.
Blend and place 1/4 of this mixture on each chop heart.
Add water to cover bottom of pan. Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove cover for the last 15 minutes to brown.
Place chops on serving platter and garnish each with a crab apple.

title: egg casserole
directions: Slit peppers (scrape seeds out) and lay in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Grate cheese and lay on top of peppers.
Beat eggs with a fork.
Put 5 heaping tablespoonfuls sour cream in eggs and beat with fork until mixed well.
Pour on top of cheese and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Check and if eggs are not done in the middle, bake for 5 minutes more.
Salt and pepper top of eggs.

title: everlasting rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in first amount of water.
Add sugar.
Mix well and let rise 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Mix remaining ingredients and add the first mixture.
Cover with greased waxed paper and place in refrigerator.
After chilled, make rolls as needed.
Shape, brush with butter and let rise at least 2 hours. Bake at 425° in a preheated oven.

title: apple twists
directions: Cut each apple into 8 wedges.
Unroll crescent dough into 8 triangles and cut each in half.
Put apple wedge on each dough piece and roll it up.
Paste the dough around the apple piece any way you can.
Neatness not necessary.
Arrange in 9 x 9-inch pan or 9-inch pie plate.
Snug up against each other.
Drizzle melted butter over them.
Sprinkle with combined sugar and cinnamon.
Pour orange juice into pan, not over them.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm, plain or with ice cream.

title: pineapple-angel food cake
directions: Slice
angel
food cake into 3 layers.	Combine crushed pineapple
and instant pudding.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread on angel
food cake layers.
Refrigerate.
You can use sugar-free pineapple and instant pudding mix for dieters.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes, peel and slice.
Mix vinegar, sugar, water and salt and pepper; add to onion and celery.
Mash eggs.
Add water mixture to potatoes and marinate.
Add eggs.
Mix mayonnaise and milk.
Add to potatoes.

title: aunt elizabeth's sticky rolls
directions: Rip bread dough into 1-inch pieces.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix 1/2 of cheese with the rest of the ingredients and pour into an 8-inch greased casserole.
Top with the rest of the cheese and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lila's congealed salad
directions: With an electric mixer, combine jello and cottage cheese. Then add crushed pineapple and oranges.
When thoroughly mixed, fold in Cool Whip.
Put in serving dish and top with chopped pecans.

title: apple strudel
directions: Dough:
Mix water, oil, egg, salt and flour together well. Roll it thin.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat until fluffy.
Add mashed bananas.
Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to banana mixture.
Add nuts if desired. Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Serve with cream cheese.

title: outstanding oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar, margarine, vanilla and egg in large bowl until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 3 minutes before removing from cookie sheet. Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: rose leway's cranberry macaroon torte
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat until thick and lemon colored.
Mix in crumbs, vanilla and almond extract.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Continue beating and add 1/2 cup sugar until mixture is shiny and stands in peaks.
Fold into egg yolk mixture along with nuts.
Spread into two greased 8-inch pie pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mushrooms stuffed with spinach and chevre
directions: Wash mushrooms; twist off stems.
Heat oil and butter in skillet over medium heat.
Saute chopped stems, garlic and shallots, 7 to 10 minutes.
Remove liquid from spinach (press). Add to pan and cook for 3 minutes.
Add all spices and goat cheese.
Mix until smooth and heat.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Cook brownies according to directions on box.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips when pan is removed from oven and very hot.
Melt caramels and milk in microwave.
Pour mixture over brownies.
Add nuts and lightly press into toppings.
Cool at least 2 hours.
Cut and serve.

title: small golden pretzels
directions: In a large bowl dissolve yeast in warm milk.
Melt butter and add to mixture.
Add salt, egg and crumbled saffron, and 2 cups flour.
Knead dough on floured surface for a couple of minutes until smooth.
Add more flour as needed.
Let dough rise in warm place for 30 minutes.
Punch dough down and knead dough again on floured surface.
Form into long roll, cut dough into 24 pieces. Roll each piece into a 10 inch string.
Form pretzels and place on a baking sheet.
Let rise 20 minutes.
Beat egg and milk and brush pretzels.
Bake at 425° - 450° for 8 minutes.

title: brandon's chocolate banana bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter a 10-inch Bundt cake pan and dust with flour.
Toss the chocolate chips with 2 tablespoons flour and set aside.
In a medium bowl, stir together the remaining flour, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl stir together the bananas, milk and vanilla.
In a large bowl beat together the butter and sugar.
Beat in the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
In three additions each mix in the flour and banana mixtures, mixing until just combined.
Using a wooden spoon, stir in the chocolate chip mixture.
Pour batter into the Bundt pan, bake for 65 to 75 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan to rack to cool completely.
For garnish, sift confectioners sugar over top or drizzle with melted chocolate chips.

title: winter cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and serve.

title: johnny's favorite cobbler
directions: Toss fruit in 1/2 cup sugar and let set until liquid forms. Stir occasionally. In bowl, combine 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, salt.
Add milk, stir until smooth. (I sometimes double this batter mixture.)
Melt margarine in 9X13 dish.
Spoon berries over melted margarine.
Pour batter on top. Bake at 350 degrees 40-45 minutes or until golden brown. (If you double the batter recipe, you might need to let it cook a bit longer.
Make sure it gets done in the center.) Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: dreamy lemon jello
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water until dissolved.
Add lemonade concentrate.
Mix and cool in refrigerator until it starts to gel. If desired, fresh sliced strawberries or pineapple tidbits and frozen strawberries can be added.
Beat in Cool Whip with a hand beater or fold in.
Pour into mold.
Chill until set.
For a group, double this recipe and mold in a Bundt pan.
Serve on a pedestal cake dish.
Decorate with fresh strawberries.

title: crystallized apples
directions: Make a syrup of sugar, water and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil.
Add peeled, halved and cored apples to syrup and cook until just tender.
Dip out and put on plate.
You can color them red or green.
Be sure to add coloring, one drop at a time, before adding apples.
You can serve them around the edge of a plate of cold turkey, alternating red and green ones.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put Lipton onion soup in bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Mix cream of chicken soup and water and pour over onion soup.
Add rice and put chicken breasts on top.
Add mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Cover with foil and after 1-1/2 hours take foil off.

title: hash brown bake
directions: Remove any excess moisture from potatoes (pat with paper towels). Press potatoes into bottom and up sides of an ungreased 9-inch pie plate; drizzle with butter. Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned; cool on a wire rack 10 minutes.

title: orange julius(fruit drink)
directions: Mix in blender and drink.

title: cream of zucchini soup
directions: Cook zucchini, onion and bouillon cubes in water for 12 to 15 minutes.
In a frying pan, melt butter and stir in flour;
cook until bubbly.
Add milk and seasonings; cook until thick.
Add to cooked vegetables and heat until hot.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: cajun cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and pineapple together.
Add the flour, salt and baking soda; mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix sour cream, soup mix and mayo in bowl. Squeeze spinach until dry then add to mixture. Stir in green onions, crabmeat and water chestnuts. Cover and chill for 2 hours. Stir before serving; serve with Hawaiian Bread.

title: walnut brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Mix ingredients.
Stir just enough to mix well.
Pour in pan. Bake about 30 minutes.
Cut into 2-inch squares while warm.
Makes 16.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, stir well.
Place in freezer tray; freeze.
Cut into servings.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream softened margarine and brown sugar.
Add eggs and beat. Gradually add flour and soda (will be hard to stir), then vanilla and pecans.
When thoroughly blended, shape in rolls (size of desired cookies), roll in wax paper and chill or freeze before thinly slicing.
Bake at 350° until light tan in color.
Can be stored in chilled or frozen state indefinitely.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Blend cocoa into melted butter.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach chicken salad(yields 10 servings)
directions: In a large bowl, combine chicken, grapes, peas, spinach, celery, pasta, artichoke hearts, cucumber and green onions. Cover and refrigerate.
Combine oil, sugar, vinegar, salt, dried minced onion, lemon juice and minced fresh parsley for dressing. Place in a jar or small bowl; mix well and refrigerate.
Just before serving, pour dressing over salad and toss.
If desired, serve on a spinach leaf and garnish with oranges.
(I used the different colored corkscrew pasta and it made a very pretty salad.)

title: uncle terry's creamy creamed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until just tender.
Be sure not to overcook. Drain well.
Pour in mixing bowl add oleo, salt & pepper and enough evaporated milk until thick and creamy.
No gravy needed for these thick rich yummy potatoes.

title: ed's famous bean soup
directions: In a large soup pot, combine all ingredients.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat; cook all day.

title: green cooler
directions: Add all ingredients in a tall parfait glass in order listed and enjoy.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: You can either mash berries or leave them whole.
Combine berries and vinegar. Start mixture on low heat.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Add sugar and butter or margarine; boil for 25 minutes, stirring often to prevent sticking.
Pour into large, shallow pan to cool, stirring occasionally.
Dip preserves into jars and seal.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Saute meat, onions and green pepper in the margarine until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Add the rest of the ingredients except noodles.
Cover and simmer for about 2 hours until the meat is tender.
Add extra broth if needed while cooking.
Serve over noodles.

title: bass' peppermint ice cream
directions: Blend peppermint sticks and milk; liquefy.
Blend eggs, salt and milk.
Add to freezer can and stir together.
Add milk, vanilla and food color to within 1 1/2-inches of top.
Freeze as per freezer instructions.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: six bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
In a large bowl, mix beans.
Separate onions into rings; add to bean mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients in a separate bowl.
Blend well.
Add to bean and onion mixture.
Mix well and chill overnight.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli in baking dish.
Place chicken on top. Combine other ingredients, except cheese, crumbs and butter, and pour over broccoli and chicken.
Combine last three ingredients and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Dice cold bacon into 1/2-inch squares and fry.
Drain all grease.
Reserve 1/4 cup.
Add diced onion and 1/4 cup reserved grease to bacon.
Mix well.
In a 3-quart casserole mix potatoes, Velveeta cheese and bacon/onion mix. Bake at 350° for 1 hour uncovered.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 30 minutes in a 325° oven.
Any cheese may be spread on top before baking, if desired.

title: lentils, lentils, lentils, lentils
directions: Dry lentils; pick out the bad ones.
Put them in a large pot; cover under 1/2 pot with water.
Cook until lentils are almost soft, slightly hard.
Add rice or barley.
When rice or barley is almost done, add carrots, peppercorns, garlic, onions and celery. Cook until they are done.
If it's dry, add more water.
In the end, add oil or some vinegar, however much you want to.

title: cream baked trout
directions: Wash and pat fish dry.
Brush inside and out with lemon juice. Sprinkle with dill weed, salt and pepper.
Place in lightly buttered baking dish.
Pour whipping cream over fish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily when probed with a fork.
If fish is frozen, bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Good served with herbed new potatoes, green vegetable and salad.

title: hamburger goulash
directions: In a 5-quart pot, brown meat and onion.
Drain any excess fat. Stir in rest of ingredients plus tomato can of water.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes or until mixture thickens.
I usually serve this with fresh onion and cornbread.

title: italian nut cookies
directions: Crush and measure nuts.
Mix eggs, sugar, spices, juice and rind.
Add flour, oil and baking powder.
Mix well and add nuts. Refrigerate 1 hour or more.
Grease 2 cookie sheets and hands. Make 4 long strips 1 1/2 to 2 inches wide (they will spread). Brush top with egg and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 20 minutes.
After 10 minutes, exchange positions of cookie sheets.
Cool and cut.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Make yellow cake according to box.
Pour into pan; set aside. Mix together eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in Ricotta cheese. Spread mixture over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with strawberries and whipped cream, if desired.

title: sausage grits casserole
directions: Cook grits according to package.
Set aside.
Crumble sausage in large skillet.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook over medium heat until meat is browned and vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Drain well.

title: bonnie's salsa
directions: Chop canned tomatoes, with liquid, into small uneven pieces. Chop fresh tomato, onions, jalapeno and green pepper into small pieces. Add to bowl. Chop a handful of fresh cilantro; add to bowl. Squeeze lime, season with salt and pepper. Salsa will get hotter the longer that it sits.

title: dressing
directions: Mix soup, onion, sage, cornbread and margarine.
Add enough water for mixture to resemble soft cornbread batter.
Pour into baking pan.
Bake at 375° until brown and firmly set.

title: aunt bess' dill pickles
directions: Put first five ingredients in quart jar.
Boil together last three ingredients.
Pour vinegar mixture over cucumbers in
hot jars and seal.

title: chocolate chips
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil and spray each pan.
Use saltines laid in pan.
Boil butter and brown sugar together about 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers, spreading to cover all.
Bake 7 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove and spread chocolate chips over all and spread until melted.
Refrigerate until cool and cut in squares.

title: special yellow loaf cake
directions: Beat egg whites in small mixing bowl.
Add 1/8 teaspoon salt. Cream oleo in large mixing bowl.
Add vanilla, powdered sugar. Add egg yolks.
Mix thoroughly.
Add flour.
Add egg whites and mix thoroughly.
Pour into two loaf pans, ungreased, wax paper on bottom of pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: woopie-do potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes, diced, in butter and onion until almost done. Add pepper and milk.
Simmer until done.
Serves approximately 5 people.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and brown sugar.
Sift cake flour with baking soda and baking powder.
Add oil, sifted cake flour and cinnamon to cream mixture.
Add vanilla flavoring, Granny Smith apples, pecans and chopped dates or raisins.
Bake in tube pan approximately 1 hour or until done at 350°.

title: rosa marina fruit salad
directions: Cook macaroni for 10 to 12 minutes.
Rinse and drain well. Put 2 beaten eggs, sugar, flour, salt and juice of pineapple in saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Pour over macaroni.
Let stand overnight.

title: apricot-nut salad
directions: Cook, drain and puree dried apricots.
Add sugar to hot apricots.
Mix until sugar is dissolved.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir into apricot mixture and pour into square pan.
Chill until firm.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and milk.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from stove and add peanut butter, cocoa, oats and vanilla.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and let cool.
Do not refrigerate.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Blend thoroughly first 6 ingredients to make marinade.
Place chicken in a baking dish and cover with marinade.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: orange-glazed pumpkin cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 10-cup Bundt pan.
For cake; beat sugar and Crisco until fluffy.
Mix in pumpkin, eggs and water. Combine remaining cake ingredients, mixing well.
Gradually add to pumpkin mixture; mix well.
Spread into pan.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: fried cucumbers
directions: Peel cucumber; cut in lengths and remove seeds.
Cook in boiling water for 3 minutes; drain and cool.
Dip carefully in beaten egg, then roll in crumbs.
Fry in very little amount of cooking oil until brown on both sides.
Serve at once.
Yields 2 servings.

title: 25 minute spaghetti
directions: Melt shortening in 4-quart saucepan; add onion and ground beef and brown.
Add green pepper, celery, tomato juice, tomato paste and spices.
Bring to a boil.
Add uncooked spaghetti.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes.
Just before serving, stir to blend spaghetti with sauce.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Place roast in crock-pot.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over roast. Spoon mushroom soup on top, then fill can with water and pour into crock-pot.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer all day.
This roast will make its own gravy.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions until tender; drain.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Add seasonings to taste.
Cook in a 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: congealed pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple including juice. Add Cool Whip.
Mix together. Add pecans and marshmallows.
Put in a large bowl and refrigerate several hours for flavors to mix before serving.
This is a nice Christmas salad because of its green color.
You can top with drained red cherries.

title: banana split cake
directions: Make crumb mix with crackers and margarine.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer bananas, pudding, pineapple, whipped topping and then strawberries.
Chill.
Serves 8.

title: crabmeat margueritte
directions: To the crabmeat, add the eggs, celery and green onions (chopped very fine).
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Have the crabmeat only moist enough to be served on Melba toast rounds. Best when made a bit "spicy."

title: peppermint pinwheels
directions: Mix shortening, eggs, sugar and flavorings.
Mix flour and salt; blend into creamed mixture.
Divide dough in half and mix food coloring in half; chill both portions.

title: chicken and rice soup
directions: Place chicken in a large cooker with seasonings and cover with water.
Cook for 1 to 2 hours.
Remove meat from broth. Remove skin and bones from meat and chop meat into small chunks. Combine the 2 soups and blend in blender until mixed well and there are no lumps.
Add canned soups and bouillon to the broth and bring to a boil.
(Add more water if needed.)
Add rice and boil for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add chopped chicken.
Simmer for 10 to 20 minutes. Serve with crackers and garnish with grated hard-cooked eggs.

title: danish cardamon crowns
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, blend butter, sugar and flavorings, mixing well.
Stir in salt, flour and nuts.
Shape into balls (use teaspoonful of dough).
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: jam cake
directions: Bake for 2 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: williamsburg sweet potato muffins
directions: Mash sweet potatoes; cream the butter and sugar and beat in egg and sweet potatoes.
Sift the flour with the baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add dry ingredients alternately by hand with milk, chopped nuts and raisins, mixing until just blended.
Do not overmix.
Bake at 400° in greased muffin pan. Makes 12 muffins.

title: dr.  cookie
directions: Per cookie:
64 calories, 2 grams fat and 28% of calories from fat.

title: cheese cake cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, nuts and flour and stir in margarine and mix well until crumbly.
Save 1 cup for topping.
Put rest in 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Beat cheese and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour over crust and bake for 25 minutes.

title: ham and cheese muffins
directions: Grease and flour 12 medium muffin cups.
Beat milk, oil and egg slightly in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients with fork just until moistened.
Divide batter evenly among cups. Bake until golden brown, 15 to 20 minutes. Serve warm. Good for breakfast with scrambled eggs.

title: jello whip
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Add the reserved pineapple juice. Cool until the consistency of egg whites.
Prepare Dream Whip as per package directions. Fold Jell-O into Dream Whip and beat for at least 15 minutes until light and fluffy. Fold in pineapple.
Pour in bowl and chill overnight.

title: st. paul's meat sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Put tomatoes in food processor and blend.

title: cookie crumble cheesecake
directions: In blender, sprinkle gelatine over cold milk; let stand for 2 minutes.
Add hot milk and process at low until dissolved, about 2 minutes.
Add cream cheese, sugar and vanilla and process until blended.
Arrange chocolate in bottom of crust.
Pour in gelatine mixture.
Sprinkle with crushed cookies.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Makes 10 servings.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in zucchini, grated orange peel and nuts.
Spoon into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Boil eggplant in water for 25 minutes.
Drain and mash. Combine with onion, bell pepper, 1 cup bread crumbs, 1 1/2 cups of cheese, melted butter, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Add crabmeat and eggs.
Mix and pour into buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs and cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: plum cake
directions: Blend ingredients together, except nuts, for 3 minutes or until smooth. Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar (add sugar gradually).
Blend in chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, beating in one at a time.
Beat for 5 minutes after each addition.
Pour into a graham cracker crust.

title: bean bread
directions: Mix raisins and boiling water. Set aside.
Beat eggs, oil, sugar and beans until beans are broken. Mix in remaining ingredients.
Beat until well mixed. Fold in raisin mixture. Divide batter into 3 well-greased bread pans. Bake at 325° for 60 minutes. Can use 10 mini pans at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: cheese tortellini soup
directions: Melt butter over medium heat; add garlic and saute for two minutes.
Stir in chicken broth and tortellini; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and mix in Parmesan cheese.
Simmer 5 minutes (do not boil).
Stir in spinach, basil and tomatoes.
Simmer 2 minutes. Serve with fresh Parmesan cheese.

title: graham cracker confections
directions: Mix together and put in a 9-inch square pan.
(If recipe is doubled, put in cookie sheet.)
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cut when almost cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Heat the sugar, water and salt almost to boiling.
Take off stove and add vinegar.
Cool.
Add to shredded cabbage as needed. Keeps well in the refrigerator.

title: egg bread
directions: Mix all ingredients real good.
Add a little water if it's too dry.
Mix again.
You will probably have better results if you mix by hand.
Then you take the first 3 fingers of the right hand, dig into the grease can and scoop up a little to grease the bottom of the pan so the bread won't stick.
Pour in pan and cook for about 30 to 45 minutes at 350° or 400°.

title: spinach and chestnut dip
directions: Squeeze excess liquid from the spinach.
In a large bowl, stir together the sour cream, Miracle Whip and soup mix.
Then stir in the spinach, water chestnuts and green onions.
Cover and chill in the refrigerator, about 2 hours or overnight before serving. Stir before serving.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil water, potatoes, celery, onion and carrots.
Do not drain.

title: slenderizing salad
directions: Put marshmallows in large bowl and cut.
Add pineapple, which is at room temperature.
Let stand about 20 minutes.
Beat in electric beater, slowly until smooth.
Add cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Beat whipping cream and fold into other ingredients. Freeze in ice cube trays.
Cut into squares and put maraschino cherry on top of each square.
Very rich.
Can be used as a dessert.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out part of dough about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter or round glass dipped in flour. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
