title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: cabbage rolls with kraut and sausage
directions: Cook cabbage leaves in small amount of boiling, salted water for 3 to 4 minutes; drain and dry on paper towels.

title: eggplant dip
directions: Saut onion, bell pepper, and garlic in olive oil until onions are clear.
Mix in eggplant.
Add rotel and cook until thick. Serve on rye bread party squares.

title: cherry candy
directions: Mix sugar, vanilla, milk and butter with hands.
Drain and freeze cherries about 1 hour.
Take out and wrap dough around cherries, forming into balls.
Re-freeze again, about 30 minutes. Then melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax together.
When well melted, dip cherries in this mixture.
Place on waxed paper until set.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: confetti slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Add finely chopped pepper, onion and carrot. Combine with salad dressing.
Add celery seed, vinegar, salt and sugar.
Garnish with paprika.

title: goulash
directions: Cook onion until transparent.
Add ground beef, stirring to break up.
Cook until done.
Into large pan, combine all ingredients; heat for 5 minutes.
Serve hot or at room temperature.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Mix sour cream with pudding.
Add milk to consistency of well whipped cream.

title: chili three bean salad(very spicy)
directions: Drain beans well. Combine sour cream and chili seasoning.
Mix and fold into beans; chill.
Makes 8 cups.

title: gooey butter squares
directions: Mix together cake mix, 1 egg and butter. Press onto greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend molasses and water.
Melt and cream shortening.
Add beaten egg and sugar and whip full mixture vigorously.
Next sprinkle flour through sifter, adding salt, soda and spices to flour.
Repeat sifting process several times before adding to molasses and egg mixture.
Stir in oats, raisins and pecans.
Mix thoroughly.
Spoon the dough on greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 15 minutes.
Makes 30 to 40 cookies.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix according to directions on box.
In a separate bowl, mix eggs, cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Beat to custard consistency.
Using a 9 x 13-inch pan, pour cake batter. Pour cheese mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
The top will brown lightly.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream butter in large mixer bowl at high speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
At low speed, gradually add flour, then sugar until well blended.
By hand, stir in frosting and walnuts; blend well.
Pour batter into greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 65 minutes.
Cool 2 hours, then remove from pan. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: coney island sauce
directions: Cook meat and onion until red is out of meat.
Add salt and pepper, tomato sauce and chili powder; simmer 10 minutes.
This recipe can be cut in half for a smaller amount.

title: cracker salad
directions: Mix the ingredients with mayonnaise and top with grated cheese.
Garnish with pimentos and olives.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Simmer 1/2 hour.
Before done, add can of tomato soup and meat balls.
Takes about 4 to 5 hours.

title: garlic pasta appetizer
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a glass bowl; microwave at High 1 minute.
Add spaghetti and olives; toss well.
Divide evenly among arugula-lined plates.
Yield:
4 appetizer servings (35 calories per serving).

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until top bubbles and begins to brown.

title: glenda's chicken supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients except cornstarch.
Cook until vegetables are tender. Mix cornstarch with small amount of water and stir into mixture (should be consistency of chili).
Serve over rice, toast points or noodles.
My mom's recipe.

title: shrimp and rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Saute onions and bell pepper.	Mix all ingredients together.
Bake, covered,
in 9 x 13-inch dish for an hour at 350°.

title: stuffed pizza loaf
directions: Try it, you'll like it.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour, whipping cream and walnuts.
Mix 5 to 6 minutes with electric mixer.
Put batter in a Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
In blender, mix egg, onion and milk or buttermilk.
Add milk mixture to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop in deep hot fat by spoonfuls and brown on both sides.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° until done.

title: cream cheese roll
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into a ball and refrigerate until serving time.

title: baked pork chops and potatoes
directions: Roll chops in flour, salt and pepper. Fry in greased skillet on one side, then add onion and brown.
Add potatoes, cut in 1/2-inch slices and each slice floured heavily. Salt and pepper. Cover with water. Bake in oven at 350° until potatoes are done, about 1 hour.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl, except tortillas.
Spread thin layer of mixture onto each tortilla.
Roll up.
Wrap each rolled tortilla individually with Saran Wrap, tightly. Refrigerate, preferably overnight.
Before serving, slice each "roll up" into approximately 10 pinwheels.
Serve and enjoy. Yield:
approximately 80 appetizers.

title: "very moist" spice cake
directions: Mix spice cake according to package directions.
Add pumpkin mix and kraut.
Blend well.
Pour into two 8-inch round pans or a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for two round pans and 40 to 45 minutes for an oblong pan. Test for doneness with toothpick.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix water, sugar, corn starch and corn syrup in a sauce pan; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add the strawberry Jell-O; mix well and cool.

title: main stay of any meal
directions: Place rice, water and salt in 2-quart saucepan. Cook on low heat until fluffy. Serve with gravy of course.

title: saute of scallops
directions: Saute scallops in butter with wine.
Add garlic powder and salt.
Add onion, green pepper and mushrooms when scallops are half done.
Stir in tomato just before serving.
Serve with rice (wild rice is best).
Sprinkle with paprika and garnish with lemon.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: chopped apple cake(quick, easy and yummy!!)
directions: Peel and chop apples.
Mix apples, sugar, oil and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and put in ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix ingredients. Cook, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Combine chicken, celery, onion, eggs, almonds, chicken soup, mayonnaise, chicken broth, salt and pepper together.
Spoon into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch lightly greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: olive appetizers
directions: Slice all bacon slices in half. Wrap each olive in bacon slice. Secure with toothpick.
Grill until done, turning each to broil evenly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: ham coneys
directions: Shred Cheddar cheese and add finely chopped eggs, onions, chili sauce, mayonnaise and ham.
May add 1/2 cup stuffed olives, if desired.
Place filling in buns.
Wrap buns separately in aluminum foil.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: brandied coffee
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon and cloves with 2 cups water in a saucepan. Bring to boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Remove cover. Add remaining 2 cups water and coffee powder. Return to boil, then strain into serving container. Pour 1 ounce brandy into each warmed coffee cup. Pour in hot spiced coffee. Stir. Top with Brandy Cream. Do not stir after adding cream. Sip brandied coffee through cream for true flavor. Makes 5 servings.

title: ciacci di ricotta(ricotta griddle cakes)
directions: Dissolve the yeast in 3 tablespoons of the milk.
Put the Ricotta in a bowl and gradually add the remaining milk, stirring constantly.
Stir in enough flour to give a smooth paste.
Mix in the yeast and salt to taste.

title: reuben grill
directions: Spread 1000 Island dressing on bread.
On half, place equal amounts of cheese, beef and sauerkraut. Top with remaining bread. In skillet, grill until browned.

title: special k cookies
directions: Boil the sugar and Karo syrup together.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Add
the corn flakes.
Stir.
Drop spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: peach blueberry pie
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice over fruit in a large bowl.
Mix sugar, tapioca and salt then toss lightly with fruit.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Turn into pie shell, mounding in center.
Dot with butter.
Cover with pie crust.
Brush top with beaten egg yolk and 1 tablespoon water.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 425°.

title: water chestnut hors d'oeuvres
directions: Wrap 1/2 sliced water chestnuts in 1/3 slice bacon.
Secure with toothpick.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Pour off grease. Combine ketchup and vinegar.
Pour over chestnuts.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef.
Add other ingredients except sour cream.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Just before serving, stir in 16 oz.
package cooked noodles and sour cream.

title: pig lickin cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 box pudding, eggs, oil and oranges. Bake in two 9 x 13 pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Mix pineapple, 1 box pudding and Cool Whip together. Put between layer and cover the cake with the topping.

title: orange oatmeal cookies
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup flour.
Using floured scissors, cut orange slice candy into small pieces into reserved flour.
Sift remaining flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Cream margarine and sugars together.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add oatmeal, coconut and floured candy pieces.
Mix well.
Shape into balls, using tablespoon of dough for each ball. Place on greased cookie sheet and flatten slightly.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: tomato bacon cheese sandwiches
directions: Microwave bacon; cover with paper towel.
While bacon is standing, toast the buns.
Place 2 tomato slices on each bun half. Add 2 slices of bacon and top with 1 cheese slice and 1/4 of green onions.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Mix together sugar, vinegar and oil.
Pour over salad.
Store in refrigerator 1 to 2 hours before serving, mixing occasionally.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add mushrooms; cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Blend flour, salt, chicken broth and milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Combine chicken and spaghetti in shallow baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken mixture.
Sprinkle buttered bread cubes and cheese over top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: seasoning mix
directions: Mix all together and let stand for 2 days before using.

title: reese's pieces cookies
directions: Cut roll of cookies into slices.
Add Reese's Pieces.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine flour, nuts and butter and pat in baking dish.
Bake slowly until brown; cool.
Combine sugar, cream cheese and half of Cool Whip.
Spoon over cooled crust.
Follow pudding directions and layer each over cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: joyce's casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef; set aside.
Melt butter in bottom of casserole dish.
First put layers of sliced carrots, then large chunk potatoes, then sliced onion.
Next, spread ground beef over vegetables.
Then spread mushroom soup over beef.
Pour tomato soup on top.
Place foil over dish and cook at 350° for 1 hour. Sprinkle each layer with salt.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter until soft.
Beat eggs.
Add all ingredients, including juice from can of salmon.
Bake in a glass loaf pan at 350° for about 55 minutes.

title: pink divinity
directions: Combine sugar, water and corn syrup in a 3-quart saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring constantly unti sugar dissolves.
Cook over high heat, without stirring until mixture reaches hard ball stage, about 260°.
Place egg whites (at room temperature) in a large mixing bowl; beat until stiff peaks form.
Pour hot sugar mixture in a very thin stream over whites, while beating constantly at high speed of an electric mixer.
Add vanilla and food coloring. Continue beating 3 to 5 minutes or until mixture holds its shape. Quickly drop mixture by heaping teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper; press a pecan half on top of each.
Cool.
Yields 3 dozen pieces of divinity.

title: coconut kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.

Line cookie sheet with greased brown paper. In small bowl of electric mixer, at high speed, beat egg whites just until soft peaks form when beater is slowly raised. Beat in sugar in thirds, beating until stiff peaks are formed when beater is slowly raised.
Fold in lemon extract and coconut until well blended.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls, 1 inch apart, onto prepared cookie sheets.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until light-golden.
Remove from paper at once; let cool completely on a wire rack.
Makes about 12.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into crust.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Cook until tender, drain and place in fruit jars and add syrup and seal (boil in water bath for a few minutes).

title: danish pastry
directions: Blend 1/2
cup	oleo and 1 cup flour.
Add 1 tablespoon water. Press thin on cookie sheet.

title: peanut butter-banana crunch
directions: Melt
margarine and honey in large skillet.
Add banana slices and
saute 3 or 4 minutes, coating bananas with syrup. (Don't overcook bananas.) Place banana slices on crumb mixture and
pour over
the
remaining syrup.
Top with the remaining crumbs.
Bake for
minutes
at
Allow	to cool for easier serving.

title: best beef stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Use to coat meat.
In Dutch oven brown meat in hot Crisco.
Add soup, water, onion and basil. Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and cool. Pare and cube potatoes and carrots.
Boil 30 minutes.
Add to stew mixture with wine.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve with cornmeal muffins.

title: overnight yeast rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast onto water and stir to dissolve.
Pour hot milk over butter and stir to melt.
Let cool to lukewarm and add to yeast.
Beat in eggs and then add flour, sugar and salt.
Stir until smooth.
Transfer to a clean bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
(If apples are very ripe, add lemon juice.)
Mix 1/4 cup sugar with apple slices.
Place in unbaked crust.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar and 1 cup flour together and sprinkle over top of apples evenly.
Slice margarine into pats and arrange evenly over top of pie.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° until light brown.
(Flour, sugar and margarine form top crust of pie.)

title: remarkable (marshmallow) fudge
directions: Butter sides of heavy saucepan. Combine sugar, milk and margarine.
Cook to soft ball stage (236°), stirring frequently. Remove from heat and add chocolate pieces, marshmallow, vanilla and nuts. Beat until chocolate is melted and all ingredients are blended together.
Pour into greased pan and score while fudge is still warm.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla together until creamy.
Sift together the flour, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture.
Blend well. Stir in oats.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry relish(microwave)
directions: Mix in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake on High for 5 to 7 minutes, until skin pops, stirring once.
Add powdered sugar after removing from microwave.
Stir sugar until dissolved.
Cool, cover and refrigerate.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Sift the flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and ginger together.
(The spices depend on your personal taste, so add or not, as you prefer.)
Beat in the eggs, gradually adding the sugar.
Beat until thick and light in color. Beat in the oil, honey and coffee; stir in the flour mixture and the nuts.
Oil an 11 x 16 x 4-inch baking pan and line it with aluminum foil.
Or, if you want 2 smaller cakes, use 2 (9-inch) loaf pans.
Turn the batter into the pan or pans.

title: tostada dip
directions: For the bottom layer, mix taco seasoning with refried beans. The next layer is sour cream mixed with dry party seasoning mix. Top with lettuce, cheese, tomatoes, peppers, olives, onions as desired. Serve with nacho chips.

title: strawberry angel cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Mix in strawberries. Let set for 20 minutes stirring occasionally. In large mixing bowl put a baked angel food cake top side down into a bowl. Seal and refrigerate to set. Remove from mold. Serve with whip cream. Garnish with fresh berries if desired.

title: cream cheese roll-ups(low-fat)
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Let mixture chill in refrigerator overnight.
Spread mixture on room temperature tortillas.
Roll up and cut in 1-inch pieces.
Secure with a toothpick.
Dip in salsa or picante sauce.

title: non-alcoholic sangria
directions: Mix all ingredients.
You may wish to add ginger ale to make it fizzy.
Chill.

title: crunch cookies
directions: Wash hands.
Put peanut butter in a bowl.
Add honey to bowl. Add powdered sugar to bowl.
Mix well.
Use metal spoon.

title: clay cookies
directions: Leave out overnight, then eat in morning.

title: gorp
directions: Dump snacks into a large plastic bag.
Melt margarine; then add onion soup mix.
Mix well.
Pour over snack mix and shake to coat.
Place on flat sheet and heat in microwave on Medium-high for about 5 minutes.
Stir after 2 1/2 minutes.

title: burritos
directions: Brown the hamburger and onion; drain fat. Add in the Parmesan cheese, taco sauce, refried beans, cumin and salt and pepper. Heat over medium heat until warm.
Let cool.
Heat oven to 350°. Put a large spoonful on tortilla shell and roll into a burrito. Place in pan.

title: three bean bake
directions: Saute onion, ground beef and chopped bacon.
Add all ingredients together and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or put in a crock-pot for 4 hours.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together in saucepan or microwave the margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Pour over Crispix.
Stir until well coated and doesn't stick together.
Put powdered sugar into a brown grocery bag and shake until all sugar is absorbed.
Store in airtight container.
Be sure cereal is cool before storing.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine water, sugar, brown sugar, shortening and eggs.
Mix well.
In another bowl, mix baking soda, cinnamon, vanilla, flour and salt.
Mix well the oatmeal, chocolate or butterscotch chips and nuts.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: egg custard
directions: Blend together until well mixed.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in preheated 400° to 450° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef and onion.
In a large saucepan, pour in kidney beans, red beans, tomatoes, bouillon cube, chili powder and red pepper.
Heat.
Add browned beef to mixture.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer nine hours.

title: quick chocolate cake
directions: Bring to a boil oil, butter, cocoa and water.
Mix sugar and flour.
Pour boiled ingredients over sugar mix.
Add eggs, buttermilk, vanilla, soda and cinnamon; mix well.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan 25 to 30 minutes.
While cake bakes prepare topping.

title: chicken pecan salad
directions: Boil chicken, drain and cool.
Remove from bone in large pieces, 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Stir in diced celery, slice salad onions and green tops very thin and add to chicken and celery.
Stir in mayonnaise until desired wetness.
Add salt and pepper, grapes and pecan and toss carefully so as not to mash grapes.
Garnish with pecan pieces and more grapes on top.
Serve with croissant rolls and soup.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening, eggs and sugar.
Then mix remaining ingredients together.
Chill dough.

title: creamy clam chowder
directions: Combine contents into saucepan.
Stir slowly until hot.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Place sweet potatoes in kettle.
Cover with water; cook until tender.
Drain and cool slightly.
Peel and cut in chunks.
Place in a baking dish.
In a small saucepan, combine margarine, syrup, sugar, cinnamon and pineapple.
Cook and stir until mixture boils; pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and cream cheese in boiling water.
Add marshmallows while mixture is warm.
Add pineapple and chopped pecans (optional).
Mix all together.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: extra egg brunch
directions: Gently fold all ingredients together.
Pour into buttered pan (9 x 13-inch).
Mix night before and refrigerate.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds and place, cut sides up, in a baking pan with 1 inch water.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool slightly and remove pulp from shell.
Mash pulp with sugar, eggs and butter.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: giuseppe's italian
directions: Mix oil and vinegar with a whisk; whisk in egg yolk.
Add all other ingredients and beat until velvety.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° in oblong pan for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown hamburger and pour off grease.
Add tomatoes, tomato juice, onions and green pepper.
Let simmer 20 minutes.
Add kidney beans, tomato sauce and sugar.
Let boil, then add seasonings and water.
Cook until onions and peppers are tender.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, cook beef, salt and pepper and onion in shortening or oil until beef is slightly browned.
Add tomatoes or tomato juice, tomato paste and sugar. Simmer over low for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel sins
directions: Melt half of the chocolate bits and 1 tablespoon of shortening in a double boiler over hot (not boiling) water.
Stir until smooth.
Line an 8-inch square pan with wax paper.
Pour in melted chocolate; spread smoothly.
Refrigerate until firm (about 15 minutes).

title: lemon sponge pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour;
add
lemon
juice, butter and egg yolks. Mix.
Add milk.
Add
egg	whites	last.
Butter
pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Set in a pan of warm water.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar in bowl.
Beat in eggs, salt, and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add bananas, nuts, and flour.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cheese and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place sliced cheese on top covering whole casserole. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Add eggs, oil and strawberries.
Add nuts. Stir just until all ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into two well-greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes. Cool 5 minutes on rack.
Let drop out of pan by itself.

title: paprika potatoes and beans
directions: Place potatoes in a saucepan; cover with water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and cook for 8 minutes longer or until potatoes and beans are tender. Drain. Combine butter, salt, pepper and paprika; drizzle over potatoes and gently stir to coat.

title: any fruit cobbler
directions: Coat bottom of cake pan with butter.
Fill pan with fruit of your choice.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Combine the flour, sugar, baking pwd., butter, milk, and salt and pour over the fruit. Combine the last 3 ingredients sprinkle over this.
Pour 1 1/3 cups boiling water over it all.
BAKE at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, being sure to check the middle with a toothpick to make sure it's cooked and check crust.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and baking powder into a large mixing bowl.
Add shortening, vanilla and eggs.
Mix thoroughly with a wooden spoon; then add chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool and cut into 2-inch squares.

title: microwave choco-zucchini nut bread
directions: Blend together sugar and oil.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in zucchini and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.

title: quick quiche
directions: First, grease a 9 or 10-inch pan.
Next, spread in the pan 2 cups cooked meat or vegetable, 1 cup cheese (grated) and 1/2 cup chopped onion.
In a separate bowl, stir salt, evaporated milk, biscuit mix and eggs altogether.

title: dilly cream peas
directions: Cook carrots until crisp-tender (8 to 10 minutes).
Drain; set aside.

title: nancy's favorite chicken
directions: Place chicken breast halves between sheets of waxed paper. Pound slightly with mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon of oil and 1 tablespoon of butter in large skillet. Cook chicken over high heat for 4 minutes on each side.
Do not cook longer or they will be overcooked and dry.
Move to warm platter.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart microwave safe pitcher. Microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Let cider stand 5 minutes. Microwave on High an additional 3 to 4 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Make paste of flour and part of juice.
Add rest of juice, sugar, butter and salt.
Cook 10 minutes in top of double boiler. Add lemon juice.
Cool.
Add whipped cream and fruit.
Freeze.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients, cover and let stand 20 minutes or until cool.
Cream together next 5 ingredients.
Add oatmeal mixture to creamed mixture.
Sift together next 5 ingredients. Add sifted ingredients to creamed mixture; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Do not remove from pan.
Frost with brown sugar/coconut frosting.

title: grandma backhouse's special meatballs
directions: Combine venison, onion soup, cracker crumbs and eggs.
Form meatballs (large for main meal, small for appetizers).
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine remaining ingredients in separate bowl. Spread mixture over top of meatballs.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 hour.
Large meatballs serve 4 to 6; small serve 6 to 10.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour part of mix into well-greased Bundt pan, then mix a bag of chocolate chips in the rest of batter and pour into pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt margarine and mix with crumbs.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken sensational
directions: Mix all but last 2 ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with Stove Top dressing mix. Pour margarine over this.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 12 servings.

title: stew
directions: Cook vegetables in water and salt until almost tender; drain off most of water. Add V-8 juice and soup. Add hamburger; salt to taste and simmer.

title: fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese.
Add cocoa and sugar, mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts, mix well.
Pour into greased pan (with butter) let stand until cool.
Slice and serve.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Place bread cubes in bottom of buttered dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and pepper. Pour over bread cubes.
Place sausage on top and sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: ground beef burgundy
directions: In a wide frying pan over medium-high heat, cook beef until crumbly.
Stir in flour and cook until it browns slightly.
Add wine, instant onion, mushrooms, thyme, bay leaf and garlic. Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for about 5 minutes or until liquid is slightly reduced.
Remove bay leaf and turn meat mixture into a serving dish.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: daryll's stuffed shells
directions: Add oil to boiling water.
Cook shells only until flexible (12-15 minutes).
Place in cold water until cool.
Drain.
Brown beef and drain.
Add to Ragu sauce, beef, sugar, garlic salt, Italian seasoning.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Set aside.
Blend Ricotta, Mozzarella, and 1 cup of Parmesan in a large bowl with a mixer. Add eggs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Use 2 9x13 inch glass dishes. Place 1/2 cup meat sauce in bottom of pan. Stuff shells with 1 1/2 tablespoons of cheese mix.
Place in single layer on top of sauce.
Top with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes or until shells are tender.

title: quick mix(whenever a recipe calls for biscuit mix, use this versatile mix.)
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt, cream of tartar, baking soda and milk powder.
Stir with a wire whisk to blend.
Use a pastry blender, a heavy-duty mixer with a bowl cover or your fingers to blend in shortening until evenly distributed. Spoon into an 8-cup container with a tight-fitting lid.
Seal container.
Label with date and contents.
Store in a cool dry place.
Use within 10 to 12 weeks.
Makes about 7 cups Quick Mix.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Add raisins to chopped broccoli and onion.
Mix mayonnaise, milk, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over broccoli, onion and raisins. Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: glazed meat balls
directions: Mix meat,
eggs,
salt and pepper.
Add bread crumbs to consistency for making meat balls.
Make meat balls.
Brown in frypan.
Cool
and
freeze
until ready to use.
Combine chili sauce, jelly,
lemon
juice
and water.
Pour over meat balls. Bake at
until heated thoroughly.
If you do not wish to brown meat
balls,
place in casserole; pour sauce over.
Bake at 325°
for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, uncovered.
Makes approximately 40 meat balls.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat all ingredients, except walnuts and raisins, 30 seconds on low speed.
Then beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Fold in walnuts and raisins.
Grease and flour cake pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Peel and slice avocados.
Add all ingredients and beat on low speed with mixer until avocado slices are mashed and all ingredients are well combined.
Chill 1 hour.
Garnish with chopped tomatoes or green onions.

title: dorothy's zucchi-lash
directions: Cook onions, covered, in melted margarine for about 1 minute. Add sliced zucchini, cover and cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes.
Stir once or twice to make sure zucchini are equally cooked.
Cook to desired doneness (remainder of recipe will continue to cook, so unless you like this real mushy, don't cook zucchini completely).
Add diced ham, tomatoes and cheese.
Stir until cheese is completely melted.
Break bread into chunks and put into pan to soak up liquid.
Serves 4.

title: fried chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper in a mixing bowl.
Mix eggs and evaporated milk.
Dip chicken in flour and egg mixtures.
Fry in hot oil.

title: creamy broccoli delight
directions: Microwave Full powder the onion and celery in margarine for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir after 2 minutes.
Combine all ingredients evenly in a 2-quart microwave dish.
Cook 7 to 8 minutes, rotating dish 1/4 turn after 4 minutes.
Before last 2 minutes of cooking, top casserole with buttered bread crumbs.

title: crispy pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and shortening.
Add all nine eggs, mix together.
Add cake flour and flavoring.
Beat for 10 minutes. This is very important.
Pour into large tube pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: vegetables vinaigrette
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a jar; shake well.
Place larger half of each vegetable in a large bowl in the order given. Repeat layers with remaining vegetables.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine the cornmeal, corn and cheese in a mixing bowl and blend.
Add the melted butter, buttermilk, chiles, eggs, baking soda and salt; mix thoroughly.
Melt 1 tablespoon of butter in each of 2 (9-inch) cast-iron skillets or heavy 9-inch baking pans until hot, but not browned.
Divide the batter between the skillets or pans, smoothing with a spatula. Bake for about 45 minutes, or until done.
Serves 10.

title: pig under the apple tree
directions: Cook sausage in separate skillet.
Keep warm.
Make pancakes by directions; keep warm.
Warm apple filling in separate saucepan.
Wrap pancake around each sausage.
Put folded side down on plate.
Top with apple pie filling.
Makes a lot.

title: cheese cake
directions: Soften cheese, adding eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Then combine the sugar, salt and vanilla and mix well. Bake in a graham cracker crust shell at 350° about 35 to 40 minutes.
Take out of oven but leave oven on.
Spread topping of sour cream mixed with 3 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla (mixed well) on top of the cheese cake and put back in oven for 5 minutes.
Remove and cool at room temperature, then refrigerate.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken until tender in 8 to 10 cups water.
Remove chicken from broth.
While chicken is cooking, make dough.
Sift 2 cups flour and 1 teaspoon salt; add shortening, mixed until a meal texture.
Add milk to make dough.
Place dough on floured board and roll out very thin.
Cut in one-inch wide strips 4 to 6 inches long.
Drop in boiling broth until all dough is used.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup milk.
Cook until boiling again.
Remove from heat.
Add chicken if desired and serve.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta; set aside.
Chop in bite size pieces the onions, cucumber and tomato; add to pasta.
Pour dressing over entire salad and toss.

title: coconut creme cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat well. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done. Frost.

title: frozen dumplings
directions: Place dough in refrigerator until well chilled.
Take out, roll thin, cut in one-inch strips and freeze until ready to use.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry bacon until done; drain grease, leaving 1/2 of it in pan. Reserve grease.
Saute celery until almost tender.
Add white parts of onion and saute 5 more minutes.
Add rice, celery, salt and soy sauce.
Moisten with reserved bacon grease as needed.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir quickly and serve.

title: caribbean style red snapper
directions: Simmer olive oil, tomatoes and parsley for 5 minutes.
Combine next 14 ingredients and add to first mixture.
Simmer over high heat for 5 minutes.
Reserve.
Place snapper in a roasting pan. Season with salt and pepper.
Combine green olives, scallions, red bell peppers and capers.
Spread on fillets.
Pour reserved sauce over.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: fritos salad
directions: Mix in large salad bowl.
Just before serving, add 1 bottle Catalina salad dressing and toss.
Can add crumbled, cooked and drained hamburger meat (1 pound).

title: thick and creamy vegetable soup
directions: Saute onions and celery in 2 tablespoons butter 5 to 7 minutes. Cook chicken breast in 2 cups water to make chicken broth.
Chop tomatoes and mash them with salt, pepper, basil and parsley.
Add tomato mixture, potatoes, carrots and peas to chicken and broth. Bring to a boil.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
Ladle half of soup into blender and puree.
Pour back into saucepan.
Stir in milk. Heat over medium heat but don't let boil.
Sprinkle with chopped green onion before serving.
Good with any vegetable.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, cinnamon, soda and salt together.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Next, add blackberry jam.
Add fruit last (dust with wee bit of flour to keep from going to bottom of pan).
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: frosty fruit delight
directions: Blend all ingredients until ice is dissolved.
Serves 2.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Wash and slice unpeeled cucumbers.
Slice crosswise.
Mix salt and enough water to cover cucumbers in gallon container.
I use a glass gallon jug.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain and wash cucumber slices 4 or 5 times in cold water.
Pack in gallon jug.
Add 1 quart vinegar and 1 cup sugar (mixed).
Do not heat solution.
Let stand 24 hours.
Mix 1 cup sugar and part of the solution and pour back over cucumbers in jug.
Repeat this for 4 more days.
This takes 6 cups of sugar in all.
Keep refrigerated when vinegar and solution is used.
Keep refrigerated at all times until all is eaten.
After pickles are ready to eat, I put into smaller jars for table use, but keep refrigerated.

title: moist banana bread
directions: Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter; add sugar to butter slowly.
Add beaten eggs to butter and sugar, 1 at a time.
Add bananas to flour mixture; then add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Pour into a well-greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: turkey in bag
directions: Rub inside of turkey with spices.
Stuff inside of turkey with veggies.
Bake in foil 4 hours or until tender and done.

title: barbecued green beans
directions: Fry bacon and onions until done.
Drain grease.
Add ketchup and brown sugar.
Gently simmer 5 minutes.
Place beans in casserole dish.
Pour bacon mixture over top, don't stir.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a covered dish and bake for 5 hours at 250°.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add flour and eggs.
Beat well; add buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until sufficiently browned.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour, spice and salt in large bowl.
Stir in egg.
Beat in pumpkin and evaporated milk until smooth.
Pour into pastry crust.
Bake at 375° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted 2-inches from edge comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold.
Serves 8.

title: shish kebab marinade
directions: Blend all ingredients; pour over meat in shallow glass container.
Let stand 1 to 2 hours (won't hurt to let stand overnight).
Skewer meat (of choice) and broil, brushing with sauce as they cook in the oven or on an outdoor grill.

title: carrot and apple tzimmes
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan with a tight-fitting lid.
Cook over low heat for approximately 1 hour or until softened and cooked down.
Serves 4.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bake in uncooked pie crust at 300° for 1 hour.

title: apple butter
directions: Stem and quarter apples.
Cook apples and cider on low in slow cooker for 10 hours.
Blend in blender.
Add sugar and spices. Cook with lid off 1 more hour.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 3 to 4 pints.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits according to package directions; season with salt. Crumble into the hot, cooked grits the garlic cheese and butter. Stir until melted.
Add egg and milk.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take out and cover with grated cheese.
Put back into oven long enough to melt cheese. CORN PUDDING

title: vinegar and oil dressing
directions: Mince garlic.
Mix all ingredients all together with a wire whisk.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Serve over fresh salad greens. Shake well before using.

title: 2 e-z peach cobbler
directions: Place fruit in buttered dish.
Put bread fingers over fruit. Mix sugar, flour, egg and margarine.
Pour over fruit and bread. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: green tomato-raspberry jam
directions: Boil tomatoes for 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Continue to boil and add 4 cups of sugar.
Boil 15 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and add the jello and Kool-Aid.
Stir well.
Pour into heated jars and cover with wax.
Yields 8 cups.

title: boiled custard
directions: Beat 1/4 cup sugar into egg yolk.
Add 1/4 teaspoon salt and stir in milk slowly.
Take small amount of mixture and add to 1 tablespoon of flour.
Add to mixture and cook in double boiler until mixture coats spoon, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add dash of salt to egg whites and beat stiff; add remaining 1/4 cup sugar. Beat well and add to custard with vanilla.
Mix thoroughly and chill for 4 hours.
Pile lightly in punch cups.
Sprinkle with freshly grated nutmeg.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Pour in ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, egg and vanilla.
Mix in enough flour to make a dough.
Roll out dough on floured surface and cut out cookies.
Bake at 300° to 350° about 10 minutes until lightly browned.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and clean the spinach and bean sprouts.
Toss all with dressing.

title: corn oyster appetizers
directions: Grate raw corn	from
cob.
To	1
cup of pulp, add the egg, butter, crab, flour and seasonings.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot vegetable	shortening
after forming in small balls. Stick toothpick in top.
Serve hot.

title: real scottish shortbread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix confectioners sugar and granulated sugar in a small bowl.
Mix the flours together in a separate bowl.
In a large bowl, thoroughly cream butter and the sugar mixture.
Gradually add the flour mixture.
Mix with your hands until the dough is smooth.
Do not overwork.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Prick with a fork.
Cut into 2 inch squares.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet until medium brown, about 25 minutes.

title: duderstadt potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender, cool and chop.
Combine all ingredients and refrigerate 1 hour or so.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: Combine the sugar, egg, margarine, sour cream and rum flavoring.
Stir the dry ingredients together, then add the first mixture.
Add pineapple and coconut.
Put in 12 paper-lined or well-greased muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast and water.
Set aside.
Mix salt, sugar and oil in large bowl.
Add eggs, then yeast.
Mix and add flour.
Cover and let stand until doubled in size.
Punch down and place in refrigerator.
Take out as needed.
Make into rolls; place into pan and let rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine in a saucepan over low heat. Stir in vanilla and remove from heat.
Add powdered sugar; mix well and shape into 1-inch balls.

title: never fail frosting
directions: Boil sugar, butter and milk hard for 1 minute.
Take off stove and add chocolate chips.
Stir until cool and melted.
Beat until it loses its gloss; spread.

title: swedish coffee cake
directions: Mix melted butter and lukewarm milk into yeast, sugar, cardamom, unbleached flour and salt.
Knead until smooth dough. Let rise to double size (about 45 minutes).
Divide dough into two. Roll each part out to 1/2 x 12 x 15-inches (approximately).
Divide mixture of soft butter, almond paste or sugar and extra cardamom, if desired, in two.
Spread each half on rolled out dough.
Roll each part up like a jelly roll.
Place each on cookie sheet (seam on bottom).
With scissors make cuts halfway through dough rolls and fold cuts backwards to resemble leaves.
Brush with egg.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: whipped maple syrup sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and mash sweet potatoes.
Reheat.
Add butter, cider and maple syrup.
Beat with an electric mixer until very light.
Add more cider if needed.
Add nutmeg and citrus peel.
Serves 6.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Mix together sugar, sour cream, mayonnaise and vinegar.
Chop lettuce, put in bottom of bowl.
Slice onion and celery fine and spread over lettuce.
Pour on sugar and sour cream mixture.
Pour on mayonnaise mixture.
Top with crumbled bacon and package of shredded cheese.
Cover and let stand 12 to 24 hours.

title: cream of mushroom and spinach soup(linda's famous soup)
directions: Place 2 tablespoons of butter and mushrooms in 3-quart casserole. Cover and microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Add broth, celery, onion and parsley. Cover and microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes. Stir
and microwave on High for 5 minutes.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper, mixed, on both sides. Arrange seasoned chops in baking pan.
Put 1 tablespoon of brown sugar on each chop in a mound.
Pour 1 tablespoon of chili sauce on top of the brown sugar, then place a lemon slice on each sugar and chili sauce mound.
Pour 1/2 cup of water in the baking pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve hot.
Serves 8.

title: grandma's rice pudding
directions: Grease a 2 quart casserole. In casserole combine rice, sugar and milk. Dot with margarine or butter. Bake at 300 degrees for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally, until rice is tender and pudding is creamy. Cool. Sprinkle with cinnamon, nutmeg or raisins, if desired. This pudding is good served warm, but will set up and thicken as it cools.

title: peanut cluster
directions: Melt in oven. Turn oven to 325° to warm. Then turn down to 200° before melting, stirring a few times. Remove from oven and add 15 ounces salted Spanish peanuts and 3 cups Rice Krispies. Spoon onto wax paper.

title: boneless chicken with onions and green peppers
directions: Marinate chicken with salt, pepper and garlic.
Saute boneless chicken in vegetable oil, turning frequently to keep chicken from sticking.
Add 1/2 of pepper and onion.
Continue to cook on medium heat.
Sprinkle flour over mixture; cook for 5 minutes. Add water and cook for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Serve with white steamed rice. Makes 4 to 6 servings.
"Healthy meal; enjoy."

title: ellie's smothered sauce
directions: Place chicken or chops in baking dish.
Spread several tablespoons mushroom soup on top of each piece of meat.
Sprinkle each piece with remainder of ingredients.
Add enough water to half-cover the meat.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: crisp cherry pops
directions: You will also need 12 (5 ounce) drink cups and 12 flat wooden sticks.

title: 6 in 1 meal
directions: Place in buttered baking dish (a layer of each) or crock-pot. Start at 375° for 10 minutes, then increase to 400°.
Bake about 45 minutes.

title: dee's brownies
directions: Melt oleo, add sugar - beat eggs, adding one at a time.
Then add vanilla.
Last add flour, baking powder - nuts.
Spread into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle bits over top. Put into 350° oven for five minutes.
Take out and using a knife swirl the melted bits all through the batter. Return to oven and let bake 25 more minutes.

title: beet pickles
directions: Cook beets until tender (2 1/2 - 3 hours, check with fork). Slip skins under cold water.
Put beets into quart jars.
1 tsp. canning salt per qt.
Make vinegar brine mix (mix sugar and vinegar).
Put pickling spice and vinegar brine mix into boiling pot.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Pour over beets.
To help lids seal, put lids into a pan of water and boil.
Beets are now ready to seal.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl.
Stir well and set aside.
Combine sugar and oil in a medium bowl.
Beat at medium speed two minutes.
Add egg; beat.
Add flour alternately with bananas, beginning with flour and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla.

title: queen's party salad
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into dish and chill.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake as directed on box.
Crumble one layer and place in bottom of bowl.
Fix pudding as directed and place half on top of the cake, then half of the cherries, half of the Cool Whip and some nuts, if you want.
Repeat and add cherries to Cool Whip.
This wil make a salad bowl.
If you want to use a punch bowl, increase ingredients (double).
It is better if you make it the day before you serve it.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add 1 cup milk; mix smooth.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring briskly. Continue to stir and boil until smoothly thickened (about 2 minutes).
Remove from heat.
With fork, beat eggs with remaining 1 cup milk.
Gradually stir into hot mixture.
Then put back over heat.
Bring to a boil, stirring, and boil until mixture thickens a bit more, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat, stir in butter, chocolate bits and vanilla.
Stir until chocolate bits are completely melted.
Pour into baked shell and spread with sweetened whipped cream.
Garnish with shaved chocolate or top with meringue made with 3 eggs, beaten stiff, and 6 tablespoons sugar.
Bake in oven until brown.

title: grilled peanut butter chicken
directions: Blend together all ingredients except chicken in blender or food processor.
Set sauce aside.
Pound chicken breasts until they are between 1/4-inch and 1/2-inch thick.
Spread sauce over chicken; let sit 1 hour, turning over once.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spread rice over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken over rice, skin side up.
Mix the chicken and mushroom soup and water and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Seal with foil.
Bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 325°.

title: no bake orange pie
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in hot orange juice.
Chill until thick and syrupy.
Put Carnation milk in a small bowl and chill in freezer until soft crystals form.
Whip milk until stiff (1 minute).
Add lemon juice and whip until very stiff (2 to 3 minutes).
Fold whipped milk into jello mixture.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter until tender.
Stir in garlic and chili powder.
Add tomatoes and beans with salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add cheese and cook until cheese melts, stirring often.
Add rice and serve.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix the sugar, oil and eggs until smooth, then add dry ingredients, vanilla and milk to mixture and beat.
Bake in oven 30 minutes at 350°.
Very good.

title: greek chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine chicken, cucumber, Feta cheese, olives and parsley; set aside.
In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, yogurt and oregano.
Add to chicken mixture.
Toss mixture lightly until coated.
Cover and chill.
Serve on lettuce in whole wheat pita.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with raw vegetables, chips or Wheat Thins.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Use 3 small aluminum pans.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef, add other ingredients and cook 15 minutes.

title: cheese ring
directions: Spray ring mold with vegetable spray.
Mix all ingredients and place in ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Remove on serving plate. Fill center with preserves.
Serve with crackers.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Mix all vegetables together.

title: pink dessert
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip together.
Add pie filling, pineapple, oranges, nuts and marshmallows.
Let set overnight in refrigerator before serving.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: In large bowl place undrained crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle pistachio pudding powder over pineapple and fold in.
Then fold in Cool Whip.
Drain fruit cocktail and mandarin oranges and add to pineapple mixture.
This recipe can be doubled.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until it won't shake.

title: surprise angel pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch pie plate; line with foil and grease foil.
In small bowl with mixer at high speed beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form.
Gradually sprinkle in 1 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating well after each addition.
Whites should be standing in stiff peaks.
Lightly beat in 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Into egg white mixture, fold in pecans, crackers and baking powder.
Spread evenly in pie plate.
Bake for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire rack for 2 hours. Using foil, lift pie from plate.
Refrigerate until pie is thoroughly chilled, at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: country style potatoes
directions: Brown mushrooms and onion in oil in pressure cooker, then add all other ingredients.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Cool cooker at once.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Combine all 3 ingredients; roll into 1-inch balls.
Hands will get sticky; can dust with flour.
Put balls into freezer; let them get real firm, then deep fry.
They stay in shape better for serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain.
Place in bottom of large casserole dish.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour over top of broccoli.
Add cracker crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: crest cake
directions: Mix like pastry.
Add chopped pecans; mix well.
Press into a greased pan or baking dish.

title: southern "cracker" collards
directions: Cut smoked sausage in 1/4-inch slices.
Slice chorizos very thin.
Destem collards; cut each leaf up with paring knife.
Take wontons out of soup and save.
Put collards in Dutch oven.
Pour chicken broth over collards and bring to a boil.
Cover Dutch oven after adding sausage, sugar and garlic powder.
Simmer for 2 hours or until tender.
Add water if needed.
Add wontons and simmer 10 more minutes.
Serve with picante sauce and cornbread. Sprinkle collards with Tabasco if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: ham and cheddar potatoes
directions: Slice and parboil enough potatoes for a 9 x 13-inch pan; drain.
Gently stir in the cheese soup, ham, mushrooms and pimentos.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Do not add other liquid; this will be thick.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cover with foil the first 25 minutes of baking time.

title: aunt zizi's oregano chicken
directions: Sprinkle paprika on all chicken, onion and potatoes before you put in the oven.
Cook at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Pour wine over chicken mixture.
Season with rest of ingredients.
Turn 3 to 4 times during cooking process.

title: yummy-mandarin dessert
directions: Use juice
from
these;
in
all you should have 3 cups liquid.
Mix together and let stand until firm.

title: venita's taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; pour off liquid.
Add taco seasoning to your taste.
I use about 1/2 package.
Drain off juice from tomatoes and add enough water to make 1 cup.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
Chop and mix lettuce, tomatoes and onion.
When ready to serve, mix meat, salad and cheese.
Serve over Fritos.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
and put in a greased 9-inch black round skillet
or
baking
pan
(any shape).
Pour half of the ingredients in baking pan, then place the cheese squares on top (spread
around)
and
pour
remaining
ingredients
on
top of cheese.
Bake
to 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove and let cool. Slice and serve with meal.
This is very good to serve with any type
of
dried
beans, like pinto or navy.
Also good to serve with chili.
Great for a snack at work or school.

title: lasagna
directions: Prepare and refrigerate lasagna overnight.
It may also be frozen, then baked.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Cook the sugar, milk, butter and vanilla.
When it forms a soft ball stage, add the pecans.
Stir and drop on waxed paper or buttered plate.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix everything together except Doritos and ground beef and add these when you are ready to serve. Crumble the Doritos up.

title: hummus
directions: Process all ingredients in a blender until smooth and creamy. Add more water if necessary.
Use as spread or dip.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil water and sugar for about 3 minutes and cool.
Put lemon juice over bananas to keep nice color.
Add fruit juices and water mixture.
Freeze until mushy.
Add ginger ale and serve.

title: grilled chicken wings
directions: In a bowl, stir all ingredients together, except chicken. Place chicken in dish; pour sauce over chicken.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator about 1 hour.

title: gullivers cream corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil. Simmer for 5 minutes.
In separate pan, melt 2 tablespoons butter. Add 2 tablespoons flour to make a paste.
Remove corn from heat and add butter mixture.
Serve hot.

title: grass dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve with chips or vegetables.

title: humming bird cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla well. Add sifted dry ingredients; mix well. Add fruit and mix well. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Do Not Use Mixer!

title: green beans almondine
directions: Drain bean broth into a small saucepan.
Add extract and mushrooms.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and let set 10 minutes.
Add green beans.
Heat, add margarine, stir and serve. Or you may use 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon vegetable supreme instead of the margarine, just before you are ready to serve.

title: apricot bread
directions: Pour boiling water on apricots; let soak until tender.
Drain, reserving liquid; add additional water to measure 1 cup.
Chop apricots.
Mix liquid with baking soda, sugar and eggs; blend thoroughly.
Add apricots, flour and baking powder; mix well. Spread batter in 2 buttered and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Remove loaves from pans and cool on wire rack.

title: mocha balls
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla well. Add dry ingredients. Chill dough 1 hour.
Shape in 1-inch balls.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Cool on rack.
While still warm, dust with powdered sugar.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Mix next 3 ingredients together to make dressing.
Pour dressing over salad and let set 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: family picnic cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Cook slightly.
Sift sugar, flour and salt into large bowl.
Pour cocoa mixture over it; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for approximately 20 minutes.
Pour icing, while warm, over it.

title: easy layered mexican dip
directions: On 12 to 14-inch serving platter, spread refried beans in thin layer.
Carefully spread avocado dip over beans.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning together; spread over avocado dip.
Top with remaining ingredients; cover and refrigerate.
Serve with corn or tortilla chips.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: mozzarella meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, eggs, crumbs, milk, Parmesan cheese, onion, salt and oregano.
Shape into loaf and place in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours; drain.
Spoon pizza sauce over loaf and top with cheese.
Return to oven and bake until cheese is melted.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put sugar in glass bowl and put butter on top of sugar.
Put cocoa on butter and milk on cocoa.
Put in microwave for 3 minutes.
Take out and mix until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Pour into buttered dish.
Let cool, then cut into squares.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until done; drain.
Place in casserole dish along with flaked tuna.
Peel hard-boiled eggs and cut into quarters. In a pot, heat soup along with cheese and Worcestershire sauce until hot.
Pour into casserole dish and top with cereal crumbs. Heat 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 6 servings.

title: homemade play dough
directions: In a saucepan, mix flour, salt and cream of tartar.
Add water, cooking oil and food coloring (oil of wintergreen is optional).
Cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Mixture will pull away from sides of pan.
Knead immediately.
Store in airtight container.
Keeps 6 months or more.

title: canned cucumbers
directions: You will need 6 to 8 wide mouthed quart jars with seals.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Melt shortening and cream with sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time, mixing well.
Have spices, soda and salt sifted together saving 1 c. flour to pour over fruit, raisins, pecans and cherries.
Add O.J. and milk then add fruit, raisins, nuts and cherries.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Bake 15 - 20 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies dropped by heaping spoon full onto cookie sheet.

title: casserole
directions: Spray Pam on 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: spicy frankfurter skillet
directions: Cook onions and peppers in butter in iron skillet until transparent. Add franks, tomatoes and tomato sauce. Cover skillet and simmer for 20 minutes. Add salt, pepper and bitters. Serve hot over
rice or spaghetti.

title: becnel peas and tomatoes
directions: Saute onion in butter until clear.
Add small amount of flour for light roux.
Add tomatoes (chopped) and cook down.
Add peas with liquid from one can only.
Cook down.
Add sliced, boiled eggs before serving.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a large cake pan or glass dish.
Layer in pan the cherry pie filling, pineapple and cake mix.
Slice butter on top of dry mix.
You can add pecans and flaked coconut over dry mix if desired.
Bake at 350° until firm and top is brown.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Line pan with a mixture of graham crackers and melted butter. (Keep some for crumbs on top of Jell-O.)
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Combine crushed pineapple, sugar and lemon juice and bring to a boil.
Add to Jell-O and let congeal (not too stiff).
Add whipped Dream Whip.
Pour over graham mixture in pan and sprinkle with reserved graham crumbs.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: mexican dish
directions: Spread cream cheese in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Brown sausage.
Mix sausage and tomatoes.
Put mixture over cream cheese.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until cheese is golden at 400°.

title: turkey hash
directions: Coat a large skillet with spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add mushrooms, onions and peppers.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Remove from skillet and set aside.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cut all cheese into small mixable pieces or use grater.
Mix into 1 large bowl; set aside.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Put milk in medium bowl and put in freezer (let it almost get frozen).
Add 1 cup hot water to jello.
Let cool until syrupy. Whip the cream until it stands in peaks. Add jello and other ingredients.

title: sweet potato yum yum
directions: Cook syrup, pineapple and sugar just until sugar melts. Shred yams. Put in a large bowl. Pour mixture over the potatoes. Dot with butter.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Slice and cook squash; salt to taste.
Beat eggs; add mayonnaise, cheese, onion and peppers.
Mix with squash.
Pour into greased dish.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Put in a large airtight container.
Store in a cool, dry place.
Use within 6 months.
Take 3 tablespoons of hot chocolate mix and add to 1 cup of hot water.
Stir to dissolve.

title: sweet & sour pork
directions: Brown pork in hot fat. Add 1/2 cup water; cover and simmer till tender, about 1 hour. Drain pineapple, reserving syrup. Combine sugar, cornstarch, syrup, vinegar, soy sauce & salt. Add to pork. Cook and stir until gravy thickens; add pineapple, green pepper and onion;
cook 2 or 3 minutes. Serve overrice (hot) or brown noodles.

title: pork chop skillet meal
directions: Season pork chops and roll in flour, then brown in hot oil. Arrange in skillet; sprinkle with salt and pepper and rice over the chops.
Cover tightly and simmer over low heat for one hour.

title: caramel sticky buns(yield: about 15 servings)
directions: 1. Butter large pyrex rectangular baking dish.

title: chocolate chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding 1/2 of chocolate chips.
Pour into lightly greased and floured tube pan, alternating layers and chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes. Invert pan and let cool.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Transfer dip into tray.
Serve with assorted vegetables.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms; remove stems and save.
Chop onion and saute in cooking oil with garlic.
Chop stems of mushrooms and add to softened golden looking sauteed onions and garlic.
Saute additionally until chopped mushroom stems are softened.

title: millionaire's cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together; spread into a greased and floured 12 x 9-inch pan.
Mix the remaining ingredients together; pour over first mixture.
Bake at 275° to 300° for 1 hour.

title: sausage and potato au gratin
directions: Reserve 3 sausage links.
Slice remaining sausage and set aside in small mixing bowl.
Beat together Cheez Whiz and sour cream until mixture is smooth.
Add onions, parsley flakes and salt. Fold cheese mixture into the potatoes and sausage.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes. Cut reserved whole sausage in half, arrange in pinwheel fashion on top of casserole.
Bake 10 minutes more or until sausages are heated through and mixture is hot.

title: vidalia corn muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in greased muffin tins for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Blend margarine and peanut butter in large bowl.
Work in sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Line cookie sheet with foil (dull side up).
Press mixture in pan.
Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Spread over top.
Cut into squares and put into refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: princess soup
directions: Saute vegetables in butter.
Add flour; mix well.
Add hot chicken stock; add seasoning and check for taste.
Mix well.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add strained scalded milk.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and freshly chopped parsley.

title: easy chicken gumbo
directions: In large saucepan, cook and stir okra, onion and pepper in 3 tablespoons margarine until onion is tender.
Stir in chicken broth and tomatoes.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in chicken; heat through.
Serve in bowls over scoops of rice.

title: cheese nuggets
directions: Mix butter and flour together well.
Add cheese and work in well.
Shape into small marble size balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for about 10 minutes.
Makes 36.

title: scripture cake
directions: Season to taste with 1 Kings 10:2.
Follow Solomon's prescription for a good boy in Proverbs 23:14 and bake.
Each scripture verse contains one or more ingredients used in making a cake.
Follow carefully.

title: everyday meat loaf
directions: In a bowl, combine eggs and milk.
Stir in bread crumbs, onion, parsley, salt, sage and pepper.
Add beef and remaining ingredients.
Shape into desired shape.
Bake meat loaf uncovered in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours for 50 minutes.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy and 1 stick butter; set aside.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, soda and buttermilk alternately until well mixed.
Add candy mixture and nuts.
Pour into Bundt pan and bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Mix last four ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour first mixture on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix butter, mustard, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Split package of rolls horizontally through the center. Spread butter mixture on both sides of rolls.
Layer bottom half with ham.
Sprinkle Swiss cheese on top of ham.
Replace tops. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
These freeze well.

title: butter sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks with sugar until light and lemon colored. Add milk and flavoring. Add sifted dry ingredients, then fold in melted butter. Bake in 2 waxed paper-lined 9-inch cake pans in a 350° oven 40 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: dieters delight
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix in dry Jell-O.
Drain oranges.
Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Place half of onions in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with half of the crackers and half of the Parmesan cheese.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Pour melted margarine over casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broiled tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in half.
Sprinkle with pepper, sugar and garlic, crushed with salt.
Add onion.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese.
Dot with butter; brown under broiler.

title: chicken and cornbread casserole
directions: Mix above ingredients. Bake at 350° about a 20 to 25 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain all juices off. Add together all ingredients.
Mix well. Refrigerate.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken into pieces; mix together with cabbage, onions, almonds, Top Ramen noodles and seasoning packet (from noodles). Mix dressing and pour over salad mixture; toss to coat all well. Let set at least 2 hours, stirring once or twice to coat well.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all together very well.
Then pour 1/2 of the mixture in one pie shell and the other 1/2 in the second pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pork chop white bean supper
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper on both sides of pork chops.
Brown pork chops on both sides in a skillet.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with milk and pour over pork chops.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until done.
Serve beans on the side or mixed with pork chops.

title: baked pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in drained pineapple. Fold in bread.
Pour in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour. Good hot or cold with ham.
Will feed 4 to 6 people.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until set.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter; mix all ingredients together. (Important do not add salt to recipe.)
Put in crock-pot, cook on low up to 6 hours.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all together in large salad bowl.
You may reserve chips and add just before serving.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Drain pineapple reserving juice.
Add water to juice to make 2 1/4 cups (for rice).
Saute onion in shortening in large skillet until tender.
Add water or chicken broth; add carrots.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and ginger.
Add catsup, vinegar and soy sauce and stir into vegetable mixture. Cook until clear and thickened.
Add chicken, green pepper and pineapple; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, bring measured liquid, salt and pepper and butter to a boil.
Stir in rice. Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Serve chicken over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lake charles dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve immediately or refrigerate.
This is delicious with chips or as a dip for raw vegetables.

title: noby hill apple cake
directions: Pare apples and cut into half-inch cubes.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Add apples, nuts, vanilla and sifted dry ingredients.
Bake in greased 8-inch square pan in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 9.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and soda; beat well.
Add oats and nuts; mix well.
Chill after making in rolls.
Slice 1/4-inch thick and bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: fried rice
directions: After dicing carrots, celery and bacon, cook eggs in skillet and put into another container.
Stir together on medium heat the rice, soy sauce and seasonings.
Then add vegetables, bacon and eggs.
Leave on low for about 1/2 hour.

title: green pea salad
directions: This may be layered or mixed all together.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Scatter lipton's in bottom of 9 X 13 baking dish.
Add rice and pieces of chicken.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix soup with water and heat to boiling.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 300 for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.
If dry at the end of the first 1 1/2 hours an a little water.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix together. Refrigerate several hours. Serve. This dish freezes well.

title: gene-"o"s barbecue sauce
directions: Melt stick of butter.
Add packed brown sugar and mix.
Add vinegar, water and garlic powder.
Let simmer to boil.
(For pork and chicken; put on at end of cooking time.)

title: eggplant with yogurt
directions: Peel eggplant and slice lengthwise.
Salt lightly and set aside for 10 minutes to remove bitter juice.
Squeeze slices between paper towels to remove liquid.
Fry eggplant; drain on paper towel.
Mash in a bowl.
Add garlic and yogurt to eggplant and mix well.
Add salt to taste, if necessary.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix ground beef with Lipton onion soup mix.
Form into patties and fry until desired doneness.
Drain.
Add soups to patties and simmer for 10 minutes and serve.

title: sara's strawberry surprise
directions: Mix pretzels, melted butter and sugar to form crust in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish or cake pan.
Put in freezer approximately one hour.
Blend Cool Whip and softened cream cheese until smooth. Spread enough of cream cheese mixture to cover pretzel crust. Reserve the rest to top jello.
Mix jello according to package directions.
Add frozen strawberries.
Pour gently over pretzel crust; refrigerate until jello is set, then top with remaining cream cheese mixture.
Refreshing and delicious!

title: carrot-pineapple bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon together.
Combine with first mixture and add pecans, carrots and pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Combine
chicken
and juices in 9-inch baking dish with soup. Mix
in remaining ingredients.
Top with crushed potato chips. Bake 15 minutes in 450° oven.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: company french toast
directions: Mix sugar, melted butter and cinnamon and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Place the bread slices on top, 2 on top of each other.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Pour mixture over all the bread slices.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake 3/4 hour at 350° or until lightly browned.
Take out of pan and invert on plate.
Can be eaten with maple syrup or powdered sugar.

title: ruby tuna mousse
directions: Brush mould with oil.
Soften 2 teaspoons gelatin in 1/8 cup cold water, then dissolve over heat.
Add to tomato cocktail, lemon juice and Tabasco and stir until mixed.
Add red pepper; pour into mould and place in refrigerator to set.
Place remaining ingredients in blender or food processor.
Soften remaining gelatin in a little cold water; dissolve over heat and add to mixture in blender.
Mix very well and spoon over set tomato layer.
Place in refrigerator until set.
Carefully turn out and decorate with parsley leaves or fresh basil.
Serves 10 to 12 as first course or side dish.

title: piquant cocktail meatballs
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine beef, cornflake crumbs, parsley flakes, eggs, soy sauce, pepper, garlic powder, catsup and minced onion. Blend well. Form mixture into small meatballs, about the size of walnuts.

Arrange meatballs in a baking dish. In medium size saucepan, combine cranberry sauce, chili sauce, brown sugar and lemon juice. Cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until smooth. Pour over meatballs. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes. Makes 60.

title: gladys' chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a large buttered casserole bowl; top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: toffee trifle
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions.
Use a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool cake and cut or break cake into bite size pieces. Set aside.
Prepare pudding mix as directed; do not chill. Place half of cake pieces into large bowl; top with half of pudding, then top with half of whipped topping and chopped candy bars.
Repeat layers, ending with chopped candy bars.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight.
Makes 16 to 18 servings.

title: carrot-pineapple cake(diabetic)
directions: Beat margarine until creamy; blend in eggs, pineapple juice and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, spices and salt.
Gradually add to egg mixture, beating until well blended.
Stir in carrots.
Spread batter into greased 12 x 8-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: lemon rounds
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt onto waxed paper.
Cream shortening with sugar until fluffy in a medium sized bowl; beat in egg, lemon juice and rind and pecans.
Add dry ingredients, blending to make a soft dough.
Shape into 2 long rolls; wrap in waxed paper.
Chill overnight.
To bake, slice dough 1/4-inch thick; place on cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 8 minutes or until golden around edges.
Remove from cookie sheet; cool completely on wire racks.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: vegetable bar appetizers
directions: Press crescent rolls to cover bottom of a 15 x 11 x 1-inch pan. Bake in 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix until smooth.
Spread on cooled crust.
Sprinkle vegetables on filling.
Press vegetables into filling slightly.
Refrigerate and cut into squares.

title: schaum torte
directions: Do not use fresh eggs.
They must be room temperature.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar for 15 minutes until very dry. Reduce speed and add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time until all is used.
Beat an additional 10 minutes.
Reduce speed again to slow and add the vinegar, then the vanilla.
Turn into a large size metal cake pan, ungreased.
Gently smooth the top, do not handle too much.
Put into a 450° oven for one minute.
Turn oven off, but leave in the oven overnight or for 8 hours.
Do not open oven door! Do not make on a humid day or egg whites will not hold.
Also be sure utensils and pan are very clean.
Serve with fresh berries or ice cream.

title: shrimp and grits
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in oil until tender.
Stir in the flour until smooth.
Gradually add the chicken broth and stir until thick.
Add the bacon, spices and shrimp and heat until the shrimp is cooked.
Serve over creamy grits.

title: cinnamon sledges
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In large mixer bowl with mixer at medium speed, cream butter or margarine, sugars and egg yolk until light and fluffy.
In separate bowl, combine flour, cinnamon and salt. Add to creamed mixture and continue beating just until blended (the dough will be stiff).

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Wash and drain blueberries.
Combine sugar, baking powder and salt in mixing bowl.
Beat eggs with butter, milk and vanilla in separate bowl.
Combine liquid and dry ingredients; stir only long enough to moisten well.
Fold in berries.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin cups and bake in preheated 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve with cornbread or Fritos and top with cheese.

title: chicken spaghetti *
directions: Stew hen until meat falls from bones.
