Remove chicken from broth and cool broth.
Skim 2 tablespoons fat and put in skillet. In fat, brown onion, green pepper and celery.
Add tomstoes and tomato sauce.
Add sauce can full of hot water.
Add small bud of garlic.
Season to taste with salt, paprika and peppers.
Add 2 cups broth and simmer about 1 hour.
Keep adding broth to keep it at 2 cups.
About 1/2 hour before you finish simmering, add diced chicken and cooked, drained spaghetti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: squash and egg casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in a small amount of boiling water until tender (about 8 to 10 minutes); drain.
Combine squash, onion, Thick White Sauce and eggs; stir well.
Spoon into a lightly greased deep 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine breadcrumbs and butter; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: pecan-coconut balls
directions: Mix powdered sugar with condensed milk and oleo.
Add pecans, coconut and vanilla.
Refrigerate mixture for 2 hours.
Form into small balls.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture and place on waxed paper.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Layer ingredients, bake 350 for 45 minutes.

title: sweetest potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil potatoes until very soft; peel. Place in food processor or beat with mixer.
Beat potatoes until mushy.
Add all ingredients as mixing; after 2 minutes should have a smooth texture.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake for 30 minutes; allow to cool.
Before cutting, top with whipped topping, if desired.

title: homemade whipped cream
directions: Beat together all ingredients with electric hand mixer until whipped cream consistency.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place dressing
on
bottom
of
12 x 8-inch dish.
Melt butter or
margarine
in
water
or broth.
Mix diced chicken, onion, chives,
celery
(or
celery seed to taste), sour cream and salt. Spread
in
dish
over herb dressing and cover with remaining stuffing and store in refrigerator.
One hour before baking, cover with
a can of mushroom soup.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Sprinkle jello over cottage cheese.
Drain oranges and pineapple very well and add to cottage cheese.
Fold in cool whip. Chill in refrigerator for several hours before serving.

title: memere's rolled sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour.
Add flour gradually.
Roll on floured surface about 1/2-inch thick.
Use cookie cutters or cut into various shapes.
Bake in a 375° oven.

title: lemon lime frost
directions: Put crushed ice into 8 ounce glass.
Blend water, sugar, lemon and lime juice well.
Pour mixture over ice.
Add straw.

title: no bake pineapple cream cake
directions: Line the sides and bottom of 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan with ladyfingers.
Set pan aside.
Whip the cream stiff.
In another bowl, beat sugar and cream cheese.
Fold in whipped cream and beat slightly.
Spread 1/3 of cream mixture over ladyfingers, then spread 1/4 of pineapple filling.
Add another layer of ladyfingers.
Spread last 1/3 of cream on top of cake and top with pineapple.
Chill overnight.

title: school house yeast rolls
directions: Combine water, sugar and yeast in large bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Mix well and add shortening.
Sift and add dry milk, salt and flour.
Knead until mixture is spongy.
Let rise to double size.
Make into rolls and let rise again to double size. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
(Be sure and place on greased baking sheet.)

title: dip for raw vegies
directions: Mix all and refrigerate.

title: sauerbraten
directions: You will need 1 roasting bag and freezer bag.

title: orange candy cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk.
Roll nuts, candy and dates in 1/2 cup flour.
Add to cake with coconut.
Bake in 300° oven for 2 hours in well-greased Bundt pan.

title: full meal muffins
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine
other ingredients in separate bowl, adding ham and cheese last.
Stir in dry ingredients until just moistened.
Makes 9 Texas size muffins. Fill tin to rim.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: recipe for all seasons
directions: Sweeten with charity.
Let simmer well and take daily.
In extreme cases, an hourly dose is suggested.
Always keep a supply on hand!

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Let come to boil.
Cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add small amount of mixture into egg yolks.
Return to saucepan.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Add 1 1/2 cups shredded coconut.
Pour mixture into baked pie shell.
Add 1/2 cup coconut to meringue.
(I use Cool Whip instead of meringue.)
Pour meringue mixture on top of pie.

title: grandmother's jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and cream well.
Blend in jam.
Sift together the flour, salt and spices.
Add the soda to the buttermilk.
Add the sifted dry ingredients to the creamed mixture alternately with the buttermilk, ending with the dry mixture.
Fold in 1 cup pecans and the raisins.
Turn the batter into 4 greased and floured 8-inch pans and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool layers on racks and use frosting only on top of cake layers leaving sides plain.
Sprinkle with remaining pecans.

title: homemade loaf bread
directions: Mix yeast in the 1 1/4 cups of water. Add shortening and stir; add sugar. Add flour all at once. Let rise 1 hour in warm place. Punch down and put in a loaf pan that has been well-greased. Let rise 1 hour and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all together on medium speed of mixer.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and salt until a ball is formed when dropped in cool water.
Add peanut butter, butter and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed and then pour into a buttered dish.

title: chicken with snow peas
directions: Stir-fry chicken and garlic in oil over high heat.
When chicken turns white, add soy sauce and cook 5 minutes longer.
Add snow peas, mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Cover and simmer 3 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and water.
Then add to other ingredients.
Cook an additional minute while stirring.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: scalloped tomatoes and artichokes
directions: Drain tomatoes and artichokes. Saute onions in butter and add veggies. Heat 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper and turn into casserole. Cook 15 minutes in greased casserole at 325°.

title: applesauce con cheree
directions: Thin slice lemons after cutting off stem and blossom ends. Place in large pot with enough water to cover the fruit.
Stew until rinds are very soft.
Remove lemons from the water.
Peel, core and thinly slice apples and put into lemon water.
Cook until mushy, adding water if necessary.
Use beater until no lumps.
Add can of cherries.
Stir in sugar to taste.
Simmer until sugar is dissolved.
Chill before serving.

title: mound candy
directions: Mix together sugar, milk and coconut and spread on a cookie sheet.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook medium broccoli flowerets until crisp-tender (check at 3 minutes).
Lay drained broccoli in bake/serve dish.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, Swiss cheese and lemon juice and spread mixture over broccoli.
Combine bread crumbs, butter and Parmesan cheese. Toss to blend.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese is melted well.
Can then brown a few seconds under broiler until tinged brown.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Chop onions and combine with rest of ingredients.
Simmer until well blended.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix flour and butter in saucepan. Add milk to make a white sauce. Add spices.
Mix chicken and spaghetti.
Pour into a buttered casserole and top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until bubbly.

title: oriental fried squirrel
directions: Cut the squirrels into serving size pieces.
Marinate for 2 hours in soy sauce, garlic powder, paprika, ginger and salt. Drain and roll in flour.
Heat margarine in a skillet and fry the pieces until meat is brown.
Remove the meat and fry pineapple in the skillet.
Serve with the meat.

title: hoppin' johns
directions: In a large pot, cook peas until 2/3 done.
Add remaining ingredients to peas and simmer until peas are tender, about 45 minutes.
Add warm water to make enough soup if needed.
Serve with corn bread.
Serve as one pot meal.

title: marinated carrots (copper coins)
directions: Slice carrots. Place in saucepan and cover with water; bring to a boil, and continue boiling for additional 5 minutes, or until slightly tender. Should be a little crisp. Remove from heat and drain. Mix in rest of the ingredients and bring to a boil. Remove from heat, cool and refrigerate.

title: frank's kraut with pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in skillet.
Slice apple and brown with chops.
Place chops and apple in casserole.
Cover with kraut.
Sprinkle brown sugar over top.
Put 1/2 cup hot water in skillet.
Stir until fryings are released.
Pour over kraut. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit yogurt smoothies
directions: Puree all ingredients until smooth.
Any kind of juice can be used and 2 to 3 strawberries can be added.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir meat and onion in margarine until meat is brown and onion tender.
Drain off fat; add 2 tablespoons of fat or vegetable oil to skillet.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper, mushrooms and soup.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat through.
Do not allow to boil.
Serve over noodles.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: sweet ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and combine with sugar. Chop cherries and squeeze dry with paper towel. Drain pineapple and squeeze dry. Mix fruit with cream cheese mixture. Serve with crackers.

title: okra casserole
directions: Cook onion and okra in oil for about 10 minutes or until onion wilts.
Spread into baking dish. Pour tomatoes over top, then sprinkle rice and salt, pepper and garlic.
Cover with water.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pepperoni-prosciutto quiche
directions: Chop pepperoni and Prosciutto into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix flour and cinnamon.
Add chopped apples and chopped nuts. Mix oil, sugar and eggs together.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour in	greased
pan
(13 x 9-inch), sprinkle butterscotch chips on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: steak and potatoes casserole
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dip in flour and brown in oil in skillet.
Alternate layer of steak, potatoes and onion in a casserole and cover.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: potato chip bars
directions: Cream butter, margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla and flour; mix until it forms a ball.
Work in potato chips and nuts.
Pat into 9 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Cut before cooled too much.
Makes 36 squares.

title: old fashion pound cake
directions: (Butter should be at room temperature, soft, but not melted.)

title: linguine calamarettial burro(linguine or angel hair, squid and butter)
directions: Heat oil and butter in saucepan.
Add cut up squid and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Saute (uncovered) for 15 minutes, until squid are tender.
Cook pasta al dente; drain and place in hot bowl.
Pour squid with their liquid over the pasta.
Toss well, but gently, with wooden forks.
Serve in hot soup bowls. You may add shrimp, scallops or fish.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pineapple skillet cake
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in skillet; remove from stove.
Put in 1 cup brown sugar; spread evenly.
Then place sliced pineapple on this sugar; fill center of rings with nuts.
Pour cake batter over pineapple and bake in moderate oven for about 30 minutes.

title: herb and butter sauce
directions: Melt butter on stove top or in a microwave in a medium bowl. Add rosemary, sage, oregano, crushed bay leaves and parsley.
Pour over new potatoes, beans or whatever you may use butter on.

title: monte cristo sandwiches
directions: Line large, shallow baking dish with double-duty aluminum foil (or use a Teflon lined pan).
Melt 6 tablespoons butter in bottom of pan.
Remove crust from bread.
Thoroughly beat eggs, water, pepper and 2 to 3 drops lemon juice (optional).
Butter bread. Cover 6 slices of bread with thinly sliced chicken or turkey, a slice of cheese and a slice of ham.
Cover with other slice of bread, butter side down.
Soak both sides of bread in beaten egg mixture until bread absorbs egg.
Brush all with more melted butter, including sides and top.
With wide spatula, place in a moderately hot preheated oven (375°) for about 15 minutes or until lightly browned and slightly puffy.

title: yogurt popsicles
directions: Whisk yogurt and jam together in bowl.
Mixture doesn't need to be smooth.
Spoon yogurt mixture into popsicle molds or small paper cups with a stick inserted in center.
Freeze until firm. Serves 2 to 3.

title: berries
directions: Wash berries carefully in cold water.
Drain in colander. Dissolve sugar substitute in water.
Fill 4-pint sized containers with fruit.
Add solution to cover berries, allowing 1/2-inch in headspace.
Seal tightly and freeze.
Makes 4 pints.
Calories per cup: 105 original recipe made with Sweet 'N Low.

title: lima bean soup crock-pot
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Pour tomatoes into crock.
Fill tomato can one and a half times with water.
Add to crock.
Add remaining ingredients.
Either cook eight hours on high or start the afternoon before and cook all night on low.
Stir every few hours.
(Can be started at 3 p.m. one day and served 6 p.m. the next.)
Serve with French or Italian bread.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients 1 to 2 minutes at medium speed with electric mixer.
Pour in 2 loaf pans or Bundt pan. Bake 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Allow to cool 5 minutes before glazing.

title: curried chicken spread
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream, green onions, nuts, curry powder and salt.
Stir in chicken.
Spread mixture over bread.
Sprinkle with parsley if desired.
Makes 12 servings.

title: broiled grapefruit
directions: Halve grapefruit and loosen sections by running knife between each section and membrane on each side.

Place each side on broiler pan and top with brown sugar, spices and pat of butter. Follow with splash of orange juice. Place under broiler for 15 to 20 minutes or until tops of fruit are lightly browned.
Garnish centers with fresh berries.
Serve as a tropical first course for a meal or a new twist on breakfast.
Serves 2.

title: ron's yeast bread
directions: Melt shortening (do not get too hot).
Put 2 cups of warm water in a large bowl.
Add sugar, salt and shortening.
Stir to mix.
Add yeast and mix well until yeast dissolves.
Use a wooden spoon and add flour until mixture is elastic and pulls away from sides of bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm, dry place until doubled.
(Microwave works well.) Turn out on floured board and knead 2 to 3 minutes, working out air bubbles.
Divide into 3 equal parts.
Melt a teaspoon of butter in loaf pans (3).
Turn dough in pans to coat with butter.
Let rise again until doubled. Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: frozen daiquiris
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in large plastic container.
Cover and freeze.
When ready to serve, spoon some of mixture into glasses and add the same amount of extra 7-Up.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Stir in flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in Bundt pan.
When cool, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: catalina salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Put in a blender and mix.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cook cauliflower in boiling water 2 minutes.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: glazed vegetables
directions: In a 10-inch skillet or wok, stir-fry carrots, celery, peppers and onion in hot
oil for 3 or 4 minutes until tender-crisp.
Add broccoli, snow peas, ginger and garlic.
Add cornstarch and stir in broth. Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Reduce heat to low and cook 2 minutes until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: lynn's baked hash browns
directions: Mix ingredients together; pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Beat together cake mix, jello, oil, water and eggs.
Pour into a tube pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Before unmolding, mix sugar and lemon juice together and pour over cake.

title: inger's beef rouladen
directions: Cut meat into 6 parts.
Sprinkle with seasonings, onion and diced bacon.
Roll tightly and fasten with a toothpick.
Dip in flour.

title: microwave cheeseburger-vegetable casserole
directions: In large bowl, crumble ground beef.
Add the chopped onions. Micro-cook covered until meat is brown (5 minutes), stirring several times to break up meat.
Drain off fat.
Melt butter. Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in milk. Micro-cook uncovered 1 minute.
Stir.
Cook again until thickened and bubbly, about 3 minutes more, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir in 1 cup cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Add meat mixture.
Turn mixture into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook covered 10 minutes, turning after 5 minutes.
Prepare potatoes using directions except decrease water by 1/4 cup.
Spoon potatoes around edge of casserole.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over potatoes.
Cook until cheese is melted, about 1 minute.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal and flour.
Add eggs, butter and both the buttermilk and sweet milk.
Should have a soupy consistency.
Pour into a greased pan and bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: make ahead breakfast
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet; cook over medium heat until brown, stirring occasionally.
Drain well.
Spread bread cubes in a buttered 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; top with sausage and cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until set.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Measure sugar, corn syrup and peanut butter into large saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until peanut butter melts and mixture is well blended.
Remove from heat.
Add raisins, peanuts and cereal, mixing until well coated.
Press into a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Yields 16 squares, 2 x 2-inch.

title: ginger crinkles
directions: Mix oil and sugar; add eggs.
Stir in molasses.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon in sugar; form into sugar balls. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: pickled pork hocks
directions: Boil as many clean hocks as you want, with skin on, in kettle. Cover with water; add salt and allspice.
When meat comes off bones, cool until you can handle; take meat from bones.
Cut into bits; put in bowl or pan.
Cover generously with juice, made from broth left from boiling hocks and vinegar (3/4 cup broth to 1/4 cup vinegar).

title: cherry torte delight
directions: Mix and beat egg whites, sugar and cream of tartar.
Add to soda crackers and nuts. Mix well and spread on well greased cookie sheet or 2 pie pans. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Cool well. Add cherry pie filling and Cool Whip.

title: chicken naranja
directions: Arrange chicken in a single layer in a large shallow baking dish.
Mix orange juice, soy sauce and brown sugar; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle ginger and celery around chicken.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Remove chicken from pan; stir cornstarch mixture into pan juices; replace chicken in pan.
Bake about 10 minutes longer until sauce thickens.
Serve garnished with orange and parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: grape-nut bread
directions: Soak Grape-Nuts in buttermilk for an hour. Beat eggs; blend in sugar and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together. Add dry ingredients alternately with Grape-Nut-buttermilk mixture to the beaten eggs and sugar. Add chopped nuts and raisins. Batter will be quite thick. Bake in a well-greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crushed wafers and 1 stick melted butter thoroughly.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Then beat together eggs, 1 stick butter and confectioners sugar.
Put this on top of crust and chill.

title: cream cheese fruit squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Prepare pie crust. In a medium pan, place 1/4 cup sugar and butter.
Heat until butter is melted. Stir in graham cracker crumbs.
Press mixture over bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain and save liquid.
Flake salmon.
Combine bread crumbs and seasonings with liquid.
Mix thoroughly.
Pack into small greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle generously with paprika.
Bake 45 minutes in moderate oven (350°).
Makes 4 servings.

title: german apple pudding
directions: Beat egg.
Add milk, melted butter, flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir well and pour into buttered, shallow dish.
Press quartered apples into the mixture.
Dust with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Bake until apples are tender.

title: chicken manicotti
directions: Cook shells until tender.
Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream; mix well.
Combine 1/2 of soup mixture with chicken.
Mix well.
Stuff shells and place into a greased dish.
Saute onions and mushrooms and butter in large skillet until tender; set aside. Combine water and chicken bouillon cube stirring until dissolved. Add to the remaining soup mixture.
Add mushrooms and onions. Pour over shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with your favorite shredded cheese.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a lightly greased casserole dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked potato soup
directions: (To microwave potatoes, prick them several times with a fork. Cook 1 inch apart on paper towels on High for 14 minutes or until done, turning after 5 minutes.
Cool.)

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and put in hot butter.
Salt to taste. Sprinkle sugar over potatoes; cover.
Fry on low heat until tender.

title: herbed salad dressing
directions: In a jar with tight-fitting lid, combine the first 10 ingredients; shake well.
Refrigerate.
Serve over salad.
Yields 3 cups.

title: cinnamon flop
directions: Mix all together.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 (8-inch) layers or one 8 x 13-inch pan.

title: spinach stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells as per directions on box.
Drain well.
Cook creamed spinach, open packages into large bowl and cool slightly. Stir in Ricotta and Mozzarella cheese.
Add salt and pepper.
Stuff shells and put into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with your favorite homemade spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle grated parmesan cheese on top if you like!

title: donna's oven caramel corn
directions: Combine sugar, butter, syrup and salt.
Boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in soda.
Pour immediately over corn and nuts in large roasting pan.
Bake in slow oven 250°
for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool.
Store in tightly covered container.
Also freezes well.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In
8-inch nonstick skillet heat margarine over medium heat
until
bubbly
and hot;
add onion and garlic and saute until
onion is tender.
Pour into medium bowl; add remaining
ingredients
except
zucchini and cheese. Mix well. Spray 8 x 8
x 2-inch casserole with nontick spray. Put zucchini slices in
bottom.
Spread
cottage
cheese
over zucchini;
top with cheese
slices.
Bake
until
zucchini
is tender and cheese is melted.

title: hershey's prize choco cake
directions: Generously grease and flour 3 (9-inch) round cake pans; set aside.
Cream butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs.
In a bowl, combine baking soda, cocoa and flour.
Add dry mixture alternately with milk to batter. Blend well.
Pour into prepared cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Separate ingredients into fourths.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook the chicken and save the broth.
Melt the butter and mix with the stuffing.
Put half of the stuffing in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Layer rest of ingredients.
Add rest of stuffing crust and sprinkle with stuffing.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt margarine and Velveeta cheese together. Add cocoa and vanilla. Beat in powdered sugar. Add nuts, if desired.

title: pauline's puppy chow
directions: *Can be added when melting chips and margarine.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until thickened.
Add jello and food coloring. Let mixture set until cold. Fold in sliced strawberries.
If berries are frozen, drain and use instead of water. If there isn't 2 1/2 cups of juice, use what juice you have and add the rest water.
Pour into baked pie shells.
Top with whipped cream.
Makes 2 pies.

title: applesauce bran muffins
directions: Mix bran cereal, applesauce, egg, butter and brown sugar; let stand for 5 minutes.
In a large bowl, blend flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add the bran mixture and mix until blended.
Stir in the raisins.
Spoon batter into 12 greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Boil milk and sugar together for 3 minutes.
Remove from fire. Stir in marshmallows until melted; add vanilla, crumbs and nuts. Drop by spoon on wax paper.

title: impossible pie
directions: In blender, mix all the ingredients on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour in greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let set 5 minutes, then sprinkle 1 cup coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until coconut on top is brown.

title: marinating sauce(for steak)
directions: Mix above ingredients in medium bowl.
Up to 4 fillet mignons may be placed in sauce.
Marinate for 3 hours in refrigerator.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Mix together.
Pour in greased 9 x 12-inch dish and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
(May use ham instead of sausage.)

title: reuben casserole
directions: Mix sour cream, chopped onion and sauerkraut.
Spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread crumbled corned beef over that.
Spread cheese on top of that layer.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Drizzle melted margarine over bread crumbs.

title: quicky cheesecakes
directions: Place 18 paper cupcake liners in muffin tins.
Put one wafer in each liner.
Mix eggs, sugar, cream cheese and vanilla together at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Spoon into each liner until 3/4 full. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool, then spoon pie filling onto each.

title: irene's chicken and dressing
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour chicken broth over bread mixture. Add chicken.
Have plenty of broth so dressing will be soupy. Salt if needed.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Bake 1 hour or until started to brown a little.

title: marshmallow fruit salad
directions: In a large serving bowl, combine the fruit, pecans and sour cream.
Fold in whipped topping and marshmallows.
Cover and refrigerate until serving.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: crunchy cheese tidbits
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll small balls of dough, about 1/2 inch in diameter, between palms of the hands until smooth. Place on cookie sheet, about 1 inch apart.
Press lightly with tines of fork for crisscross pattern on each.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not brown!
Yields 100 tidbits.
They freeze well.

title: cornbread wraps
directions: Separate dough into 16 strips.
Cut each strip in half.
Wrap dough around little link sausage and press ends together to seal. Bake following directions on dough package.

title: creamed corn
directions: Pour corn in crock-pot on top of all other ingredients. Cook at low setting, mixing periodically. Yield: a whole bunch!

title: olive cheese balls
directions: Beat together cheese and butter with a mixer.
Stir in flour. Wrap a teaspoonful of dough around each olive, covering completely. Place 1 inch apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: chocolate crisp cookies
directions: Use a 350° oven.
Stir together the flour, salt and soda; set aside.
Beat butter and sugar until smooth.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour mixture, then stir in cereal and morsels. Drop by teaspoon onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: 7-up brownies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add 7-Up and cocoa.
Bring to a boil.
Add sugar and flour mixture.
Mix in buttermilk.
Pour batter into slightly buttered shallow pan (12 x 6-inch cookie sheet).
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Frost while still hot.

title: chicken breasts with mushrooms and cheese
directions: Cut breasts into large pieces. Sprinkle with salt and pepper and immerse in beaten eggs 2 to 3 hours. Drain. Roll in bread crumbs and brown in butter. Place chicken in single layer in a baking dish. Cover with mushrooms and top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, basting with chicken broth several times. Squeeze fresh lemon juice over chicken just before serving. Serves 4 generously.

title: salmon salad
directions: Cool the cans of salmon and empty contents into a mixing bowl. Be sure to add all the oil in the can.
Chop salmon fine and mix with the potatoes.
Soak the diced celery in cold water for 1 hour. Chop up the peppers and add to the mixture.
Add the mayonnaise and thoroughly mix. Garnish with sprigs of parsley or lettuce and serve cold on lettuce leaves with the lemons cut in thin slices and laid across the top of the salad.

title: sawmill stew
directions: Chop cabbage and place in boiler with water and salt.
Cook about 15 minutes. Then add potato soup and caraway seeds.
Saute cubed smoked beef sausage in vegetable oil until slightly brown. Add to cabbage mixture and simmer for 20 minutes or until hot. Serves 4.

title: stir-fry cabbage casserole
directions: Combine oil, onion, hamburger meat and sausage in skillet. Stir-fry until meat is brown. Add cabbage and about 1/2 cup water, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer slowly, stirring often, until cabbage is tender and water has evaporated.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: overnight malasadas
directions: Pour boiling water over butter, sugar and salt in a large bowl. Add milk and let stand until lukewarm.
Add yeast, then eggs and flour last.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Fry in hot oil next morning.

title: holiday green bean casserole
directions: *Or two 9 ounce packages frozen cut green beans, cooked and drained.

title: lemon squares for kids
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly the flour, margarine and powdered sugar.
Press evenly with hands in bottom and about 5/8-inch
up sides of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
(If dough is sticky, flour fingers.)

Bake 20 minutes. Beat remaining ingredients with mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy. Pour over hot crust. Bake just until no indentation remains when touched lightly in center, about 25 minutes.
Let stand until cool, then cut into about 1 1/2-inch squares.
If desired, stir in 1/2 cup flaked coconut when mixing batter, when light and fluffy.

title: lemon dessert
directions: This dessert is made in three layers.

title: happiness cake
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Add tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy, flavored with love and kindly service.
Fold in 4 cups of prayerful faith.
Pour into your daily life and bake well with the heat of human kindness.
Serve with a smile anytime, and it will satisfy the hunger of many souls.

title: paul's best tater salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and then make a dressing of the remaining ingredients.
Blend until smooth.
Pour over potato mixture.
Toss lightly until mixed well.
Garnish with sliced hard-cooked eggs and slices of stuffed olives.

title: mom's bread pudding
directions: Blend scalded milk, butter, sugar, eggs, salt, cinnamon/nutmeg and raisins. Pour over bread crumbs in baking dish. Put baking dish in pan of hot water (1-inch deep). Bake until silver knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve with or without sauce or cream.

title: cream pie
directions: Cook flour, sugar, salt, milk, egg whites and butter in double boiler until thick.

title: shaker flank steak
directions: Cut or score both sides of steak diagonally and dust with flour.
Saute in heated butter until well browned on both sides. Season with salt and pepper, then add vegetables; last of all, add lemon juice and ketchup.
Cover tightly and simmer gently for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
The vegetables cook down to a rich sauce to be served with the meat.
Serves 6.

title: spaghetti surprise
directions: Boil spaghetti in water according to directions on package. Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp, then crumble bacon and set aside.
Pour off fat and crumble sausage and place it and minced garlic and parsley in skillet and cook until sausage is done.
Stir in bacon and tomatoes, then add drained spaghetti. Quickly scramble eggs and then add eggs and 1/2 cup milk to spaghetti mixture.
Stir all this together and put in a pretty bowl and serve.

title: grape nut custard pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, salt, sugar, vanilla and grape nuts.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degree until knife when inserted comes out clean, approximately 45 minutes.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in butter until tender.
Stir in soup, milk, mushrooms and cheese.
Cook until blended.
Place half the noodles in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with half each of sauce, cottage cheese and chicken.
Repeat layers and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pasta with tomato and mozzarella sauce
directions: Combine tomatoes, juice, cheese, basil, oil, garlic, parsley, salt and pepper in a bowl and blend well.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Cook pasta and drain.
Combine hot pasta and sauce in large bowl and toss until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add chicken and put into a large baking pan.
Bake at 375-400 degrees until brown and bubbly.

title: buckeyes or easter eggs
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients.
Form into balls or eggs.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler and dip each one.
Cool on wax paper.

title: microwave sugar cream pie
directions: Beat together margarine and sugar.
Add cornstarch, milk and vanilla; stir together.
Microwave on High 3 1/2 minutes.
Whisk and put back in for 1 1/2 minutes.
Keep doing 1 minute at a time for 2 more times.
Pour into baked pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in eggs and oil.
Stir in carrots. Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Grease a 2-quart baking dish; cook onions and beef together. Pour off fat.
Season and spread mixture in baking dish.
Cover with soup and top with single layer of frozen Tater Tots.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes, covered; then bake 20 minutes, uncovered. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken asparagus rolls
directions: Slightly flatten chicken breasts and cut each half into 3 equal strips lengthwise.
Wash asparagus and trim ends to make all about 7-inches long.
Place spears in flat pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and let sit 10 to 15 minutes.
Wrap chicken in spiral fashion around each spear and secure with toothpicks.
In shallow, wide skillet heat chicken broth and enough wine or water to barely cover chicken rolls.
Heat to gentle boil.
Add chicken rolls and poach 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove toothpicks.
Arrange on platter and pour hollandaise down center.
Serve left hollandaise on side.

title: roast possum
directions: First thing you do is catch the possum.
You'll want to cage him and fatten him before you eat him.
If you can't catch a possum, you can substitute pork instead.

title: mom's cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries coarsely. Add finely ground oranges and mix well with sugar. Let stand overnight.

title: tomatoes
directions: Peel
and
cut
tomatoes in quarters.
Stuff in jars in their own
juice
and
add
teaspoon
salt per quart and 1 teaspoon sugar per quart.
Seal and bake on a cookie sheet for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 250°.
Let cool in oven.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Put all ingredients in blender in given order.
Cover and blend only until all potatoes have gone through blades.
Pour 1/4 cup onto hot, greased griddle.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup powdered sugar; add margarine, mixing well.
Spoon into a 9-inch square baking pan; press into pan evenly.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Combine 2 tablespoons flour and baking powder; set aside.
Combine eggs, sugar, lemon rind and lemon juice; beat well.
Stir dry ingredients into egg mixture and pour over baked crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned and set.
Sprinkle lightly with powdered sugar.
Let cool; sprinkle again with powdered sugar and cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: lemon coolers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Ingredients do not need to be room temperature.
Mix cake mix, Cool Whip and egg in large bowl by hand.
Drop mixture by teaspoon into powdered sugar to coat. Place on greased cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool on sheet for 5 minutes before removing.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: egg rolls
directions: Brown beef in large frying pan or pot.
Remove beef and add 2 tablespoons oil to pan. Then add cabbage, onions, bamboo shoots and chestnuts and cook 5 minutes on medium heat while stirring.
Add mushrooms and bean sprouts and cook about 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add cooked beef, soy sauce and sherry; season with salt and pepper to taste. Let cool about 30 minutes.
Put about 2 tablespoons filling in each roll and wrap following directions for wrapping on package.
Seal edges of wrapper with beaten egg yolks. Heat vegetable oil to medium-high in a large pot.
Fry 3 rolls at a time.
Takes about 2 minutes to fry.
Drain on paper towels.

title: microwave toasted nuts
directions: Spread nuts in a single layer in a shallow plate or pie plate. Allow 6 minutes for almonds, pine nuts, peanuts, pecans, blanched walnuts and fresh pumpkin and winter squash seeds.
Allow 6 minutes for dried seeds and 10 minutes for cashews and filberts.
